      1   !<
      2       ==============================================================
      3       Global Trade Analysis Project
      4       An Energy-Environmental Version of the GTAP Modeling Framework
      5       GTAP-E Version 6-pre2
      6       July 2007
      7       ==============================================================
      8    
      9       For documentation see:
     10       (a) Hertel, T.W. and M.E. Tsigas, "Structure of the Standard GTAP Model",
     11       Chapter 2 in T.W. Hertel (editor) "Global Trade Analysis: Modeling and
     12       Applications", Cambridge University Press, 1997.
     13    
     14       (b) McDougall, R.A., "A New Regional Household Demand System for GTAP",
     15       GTAP Technical Paper #20, Center for Global Trade Analysis, Purdue
     16       University
     17    
     18       (c) Hertel T.W., K. Itakura and R.A. McDougall, "GTAP.TAB: The Standard
     19       GTAP Model" (yet to be drafted), GTAP Technical Paper, Center for Global
     20       Trade Analysis, Purdue University,
     21       http://www.agecon.purdue.edu/gtap/techpapr/.  This technical paper
     22       documents all of the changes since the GTAP book TAB file.
     23    
     24       (d) Burniaux, J.-M. and Truong, T.P., "GTAP-E: An Energy-Environmental
     25       Version of the GTAP Model", GTAP Technical Paper #16, Center for Global
     26       Trade Analysis, Purdue University
     27    
     28    
     29       -----------------------------------
     30       HISTORY of the GTAP-E modifications
     31       -----------------------------------
     32    
     33       Version 6-pre2 developed by A.A. Golub and R.A. McDougall, July 2007:
     34           - Reimplement emissions trading with trading blocs.
     35           - Calculate carbon dioxide emissions from the bottom up.
     36           - Reimplement carbon taxation, not converting rates from specific to
     37             ad valorem.
     38           - Reorganize production structure to group equations by nest, and
     39             equip with complete set of technological change variables.
     40           - Introduce energy nest in private and government consumption.
     41           - Revise calculation of "CNTco2trd", contribution of net permit
     42             trading revenue to welfare change.
     43           - Introduce change in ratio of current account to regional income to
     44             maintain homogeneity in the presence of a fixed current account
     45           - Introduce new tax-income ratio variables, change in ratio of
     46             carbon-exclusive taxes to INCOME, del_tnctaxr(r), and change in
     47             ratio of carbon tax to INCOME, del_ctaxr(r).
     48           - Introduce new variable del_ctgshr(r) representing government share
     49             of carbon tax payments/permits revenue.
     50    
     51       Version 6-pre1 developed by R.A. McDougall, April 2006:
     52           -   resync with standard GTAP release 6.2
     53           -   format and module structure fixes
     54    
     55       Version 5 developed by JM Burniaux, September 2001
     56           - includes carbon emissions, emission taxes and trading.
     57           - with a value-added + energy bundle
     58           - plus substitution nesting with capital and a composite energy good
     59           - plus substitution between electricity and energy sources
     60           - plus substitution between coal and liquid fuels boundle
     61           - plus substitution between liquid fuels
     62    
     63    
     64       ----------------------------
     65       HISTORY of the standard file
     66       ----------------------------
     67    
     68       Version 6.2 fixes bugs and provides minor enhancements:
     69           - EV_ALT, CNTdpar fix
     70           - SX_IR fix
     71           - new treatment of export and import tariffs
     72           - original levels defined for power-of-tax variables
     73           - CNTalleffir range extended from TRAD_COMM to DEMD_COMM
     74           - INCOME formula, quantity index equations more AnalyzeGE-friendly
     75    
     76       Version 6.1 fixes bugs in 6.0:
     77           - Computation of tax receipts ratio is now separately done for total
     78             tax and indirect tax (equation DTAXRATIO and DINDTAXRATIO).
     79           - Computation of DTBALR, the ratio of the trade balance to regional
     80             income, has been corrected (equation DTBALRATIO).
     81           - Computation of EV_ALT, the summary variable for EV, has been
     82             corrected (equation EV_DECOMPOSITION).
     83       Also the notation has been changed for the tax-income ratio variables:
     84           TGCR -> del_taxrgc,    TPCR -> del_taxrpc,    TIUR -> del_taxriu,
     85           TFUR -> del_taxrfu,    TOUTR -> del_taxrout,  TEXPR -> del_taxrexp
     86           TIMPR -> del_taxrimp,  TINCR -> del_taxrinc,  DTAXR -> del_ttaxr.
     87    
     88       Version 6.0 replaces version 5.0 used in the August 2000 short course, but
     89       never formally released.  The subsequent changes have been quite
     90       significant (primarily focused on final demand and welfare decomposition),
     91       so we decided to give it a new version number.  This also prevents
     92       confusion with the soon to be released version 5.0 GTAP data set.
     93    
     94       The differences with the previous publicly released version of GTAP.TAB,
     95       Version 4.1, dated November 1998, are numerous.  One goal of this version
     96       is to reorganize the TAB file which had not be redesigned since its
     97       inception.  In addition, there is a long list of substantive changes that
     98       have been made between Version 4.1 and 6.0.  These include:
     99    
    100           - provision for multiple margins sectors (to accommodate post version
    101             5 GTAP data)
    102           - introduction of the new theory of final demand following McDougall's
    103             GTAP Technical Paper #20
    104           - modification of the welfare decomposition following McDougall's
    105             Technical Paper #20
    106           - correction to the treatment of technical change, ao, in the presence
    107             of ESUBT > 0 (affects equations VADEMAND and INTDEMAND)
    108           - addition of import-augmenting "technical change" in the Armington
    109             nest: ams which can be used to lower the effective price of imported
    110             products
    111           - specification of Baldwin-type capital accmulation effects following
    112             Francois' Technical Paper #7
    113           - introduction of uniform consumption tax instrument, tp(r)
    114    
    115    
    116       ----------------------------------
    117       Overview of the GTAP.TAB Structure
    118       ----------------------------------
    119       Preliminaries:
    120           FILES
    121           SETS
    122           READ statements of Base Data
    123           Common VARIABLES
    124           Common COEFFICIENTS
    125    
    126       Modules:
    127           1.  Government Consumption
    128           2.  Private Consumption
    129           3.  Firms
    130           4.  Investment, Global Bank, and Savings
    131           5.  International Trade
    132           6.  International Transport Services
    133           7.  International Emissions Trade
    134           8.  Regional Household
    135           9.  Equilibrium Conditions
    136    
    137       Appendices:
    138           A.  Summary Indices
    139           B.  Equivalent Variation
    140           C.  Welfare Decomposition
    141           D.  Terms of Trade Decomposition
    142   >!
    143    
    144    
    145   !<
    146       -----
    147       FILES
    148       -----
    149   >!
    150    
    151   File
    152       GTAPSETS # file with set specification #;
    153   File
    154       GTAPDATA # file containing all base data #;
    155   File
    156       GTAPPARM # file containing behavioral parameters #;
    157    
    158    
    159   !<
    160       ----
    161       SETS
    162       ----
    163    
    164       Sets define relevant groupings of entities over which we will be
    165       performing operations in the model.  SUBSETS are defined in order to
    166       facilitate summation over only a portion of a given group, e.g., tradeable
    167       commodities.  Users with access to GEMPACK can increase the maximum set
    168       sizes to permit larger aggregations, provided you have sufficient RAM for
    169       implementing them The standard model (10x10 aggregation with decomposition
    170       code) is designed to run with 16 Mb of RAM.
    171    
    172    
    173       Aide-Memoire for Sets
    174       ---------------------
    175    
    176       |--------------------------------------|
    177       |         DEMD_COMM                    |
    178       |----------------------------------------------------|
    179       | ENDW_COMM |       TRAD_COMM          |  CGDS_COMM  |
    180       |----------------------------------------------------|
    181       |                     NSAV_COMM                      |
    182       |----------------------------------------------------|
    183                   |                     PROD_COMM          |
    184                   |----------------------------------------|
    185    
    186       For Endowments,
    187       |-------------------------|
    188       | ENDW_COMM               |
    189       |-------------------------|
    190       | ENDWM_COMM | ENDWS_COMM |
    191       |-------------------------|
    192   >!
    193    
    194   Coefficient
    195       VERNUM # version of GTAP data #;
    196   Read
    197       VERNUM from file GTAPDATA header "DVER";
    198   Update
    199       VERNUM = 0.0; ! force it to be copied to update file !
 
 %%WARNING.Update for "VERNUM" defined at line number 198.
  This really should be an Update(Change).
  [Since RHS equals zero, the Update will not change value.]
  [Strictly speaking, only Linear Variables (and *) are
    allowed on RHS of a Product UPDATE.]
 
    200    
    201   Set
    202       REG # regions in the model #
    203       maximum size 10 read elements from file GTAPSETS header "H1";
    204   Set
    205       TRAD_COMM # traded commodities #
    206       maximum size 10 read elements from file GTAPSETS header "H2";
    207   Set
    208       MARG_COMM # margin commodities #
    209       maximum size 10 read elements from file GTAPSETS header "MARG";
    210   Subset
    211       MARG_COMM is subset of TRAD_COMM;
    212   Set
    213       NMRG_COMM # non-margin commodities # = TRAD_COMM - MARG_COMM;
    214   Set
    215       CGDS_COMM # capital goods commodities #
    216       maximum size 1 read elements from file GTAPSETS header "H9";
    217   Set
    218       ENDW_COMM # endowment commodities #
    219       maximum size 5 read elements from file GTAPSETS header "H6";
    220   Set
    221       PROD_COMM # produced commodities # = TRAD_COMM union CGDS_COMM;
    222   Set
    223       DEMD_COMM # demanded commodities # = ENDW_COMM union TRAD_COMM;
    224   Set
    225       NSAV_COMM # non-savings commodities # = DEMD_COMM union CGDS_COMM;
    226   Subset
    227       PROD_COMM is subset of NSAV_COMM;
    228    
    229   !<
    230       Check for non-overlapping sets (users can't use the same name for elements
    231       of ENDW_COMM, TRAD_COMM or CGDS_COMM).
    232   >!
    233    
    234   Coefficient
    235       SIZE_TRAD # size of TRAD_COMM set #;
    236   Formula
    237       SIZE_TRAD = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, 1);
    238   Coefficient
    239       SIZE_ENDW # size of ENDW_COMM set #;
    240   Formula
    241       SIZE_ENDW = sum(i,ENDW_COMM, 1);
    242   Coefficient
    243       SIZE_DEMD # size of DEMD_COMM set #;
    244   Formula
    245       SIZE_DEMD = sum(i,DEMD_COMM, 1);
    246   Assertion (initial)
    247       SIZE_DEMD = SIZE_TRAD + SIZE_ENDW;
    248    
    249   Coefficient
    250       SIZE_CGDS # size of CGDS_COMM set #;
    251   Formula
    252       SIZE_CGDS = sum(i,CGDS_COMM, 1);
    253   Coefficient
    254       SIZE_PROD # size of PROD_COMM set #;
    255   Formula
    256       SIZE_PROD = sum(i,PROD_COMM, 1);
    257   Assertion (initial)
    258       SIZE_PROD = SIZE_TRAD + SIZE_CGDS;
    259    
    260   !<
    261       The sluggish endowments are now defined dynamically, based on the variable
    262       SLUG.  SLUG is a binary variable that is zero for mobile endowments and
    263       one for sluggish endowments.  We must define and read in this variable
    264       before proceeding further.
    265   >!
    266   Coefficient (integer,parameter) (all,i,ENDW_COMM)
    267       SLUG(i) # sluggish primary factor endowments #;
    268   Read
    269       SLUG from file GTAPPARM header "SLUG";
    270    
    271   Set
    272       ENDWS_COMM
    273       # sluggish endowment commodities # = (all,i,ENDW_COMM: SLUG(i)>0);
    274   Set
    275       ENDWM_COMM
    276       # mobile endowment commodities # = ENDW_COMM - ENDWS_COMM;
    277   Set
    278       ENDWC_COMM # capital endowment commodity # (capital);
    279   !<
    280       This single element set is defined for the sake of convenience.
    281   >!
    282   Subset
    283       ENDWC_COMM is subset of ENDW_COMM;
    284    
    285   Set
    286       ENDWNA_COMM
    287       # non-accumulatable endowment commodity #  = ENDW_COMM - ENDWC_COMM;
    288    
    289   !<
    290       Energy Usage and Carbon Taxation
    291       --------------------------------
    292   >!
    293    
    294   Set
    295       CTAX_COMM # commodities subject to carbon tax # (coal, oil, gas, oil_pcts);
    296   Subset
    297       CTAX_COMM is subset of TRAD_COMM;
    298    
    299   Set
    300       EGY_COMM # energy commodities # (coal, oil, gas, oil_pcts, electricity);
    301   Subset
    302       EGY_COMM is subset of TRAD_COMM;
    303    
    304   !<
    305       Emissions Trading
    306       -----------------
    307   >!
    308    
    309   Set BLOC #trading blocs#
    310       maximum size 10 read elements from file GTAPPARM header "TRBL";
    311    
    312   Mapping
    313       REGTOBLOC from REG to BLOC;
    314   Read (by_elements)
    315       REGTOBLOC from file GTAPPARM header "MAPB";
    316   !<
    317    
    318       ----------------------------
    319       READ Statements of Base Data
    320       ----------------------------
    321    
    322       We read in here almost all the base data, and define variables and
    323       coefficients associated with them.  A few data arrays used each in a
    324       single module are read in those modules: VKB, VTMFSD, and DPARSUM.
    325    
    326       The READ statements are divided into six sections:
    327    
    328       Saving
    329       Government Consumption
    330       Private Consumption
    331       Firms
    332       Global Bank
    333       International Trade and Transport
    334       Carbon Dioxide Emissions
    335       Carbon Taxation
    336    
    337       Since these are invariant for each solution of the model, they are termed
    338       coefficients.  Coefficients are assigned upper case to distinguish them
    339       from variables.  (This is purely cosmetic, as GEMPACK is not
    340       case-sensitive.) Variables in GEMPACK are assigned lower case labels to
    341       denote the fact that they are percentage changes.  In some cases, original
    342       levels values for selected variables are defined to permit the user to
    343       compare post-simulation levels values across several simulations.
    344    
    345       The updating command indicates how the new level of the coefficient will
    346       be computed based on the previous solution of the linearized equations.
    347       Note that the notation used in the update commands is a shorthand for
    348       total differentials of these coefficient values.  Thus, w * v indicates
    349       that we want to take the total differential of W * V, plug in the
    350       calculated values of w and v, and add this to the base level in order to
    351       obtain a revised value for this product.
    352   >!
    353    
    354    
    355   !<
    356       Saving
    357       ------
    358   >!
    359    
    360   Variable (all,r,REG)
    361       psave(r) # price of savings in region r #;
    362   Variable (all,r,REG)
    363       qsave(r) # regional demand for NET savings #;
    364   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
    365       SAVE(r) # expenditure on NET savings in region r valued at agent's prices #;
    366   Update (all,r,REG)
    367       SAVE(r) = psave(r) * qsave(r);
    368   Read
    369       SAVE from file GTAPDATA header "SAVE";
    370    
    371    
    372   !<
    373       Government Consumption
    374       ----------------------
    375   >!
    376    
    377   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
    378       pgd(i,s) # price of domestic i in government consumption in s #;
    379   Variable (orig_level=VDGM)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
    380       qgd(i,s) # government hhld demand for domestic i in region s #;
    381   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    382       VDGA(i,r) # government consumption expenditure on domestic i in r #;
    383   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    384       VDGA(i,r) = pgd(i,r) * qgd(i,r);
    385   Read
    386       VDGA from file GTAPDATA header "VDGA";
    387    
    388   Variable (orig_level=1.0)(all,i,NSAV_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    389       pm(i,r) # market price of commodity i in region r #;
    390   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    391       tgd(i,r) # tax on domestic i purchased by government hhld in r #;
    392   Coefficient (ge 0) (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    393       VDGANC(i,r)
    394       # carbon-tax-excl. value of government consumption of domestic i in r #;
    395   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    396       VDGANC(i,r) = tgd(i,r) * pm(i,r) * qgd(i,r);
    397   Read
    398       VDGANC from file GTAPDATA header "DGNC";
    399    
    400    
    401   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    402       VDGM(i,r) # government consumption expenditure on domestic i in r #;
    403   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    404       VDGM(i,r) = pm(i,r) * qgd(i,r);
    405   Read
    406       VDGM from file GTAPDATA header "VDGM";
    407    
    408   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
    409       pgm(i,s) # price of imports of i in government consumption in s #;
    410   Variable (orig_level=VIGM)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
    411       qgm(i,s) # government hhld demand for imports of i in region s #;
    412   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    413       VIGA(i,r) # government consumption expenditure on imported i #;
    414   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    415       VIGA(i,r) = pgm(i,r) * qgm(i,r);
    416   Read
    417       VIGA from file GTAPDATA header "VIGA";
    418    
    419   Variable (orig_level=1.0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    420       pim(i,r) # market price of composite import i in region r #;
    421   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    422       tgm(i,r) # tax on imported i purchased by gov't hhld in r #;
    423   Coefficient (ge 0) (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    424       VIGANC(i,r)
    425       # carbon-tax-excl. value of government consumption of imported i in r #;
    426   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    427       VIGANC(i,r) = tgm(i,r) * pim(i,r) * qgm(i,r);
    428   Read
    429       VIGANC from file GTAPDATA header "IGNC";
    430    
    431    
    432   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    433       VIGM(i,r) # gov't consumption expenditure on i in r #;
    434   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    435       VIGM(i,r) = pim(i,r) * qgm(i,r);
    436   Read
    437       VIGM from file GTAPDATA header "VIGM";
    438    
    439    
    440   !<
    441       Private Consumption
    442       -------------------
    443   >!
    444    
    445   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
    446       ppd(i,s) # price of domestic i to private households in s #;
    447   Variable (orig_level=VDPM)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
    448       qpd(i,s) # private hhld demand for domestic i in region s #;
    449   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    450       VDPA(i,r) # private consumption expenditure on domestic i in r #;
    451   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    452       VDPA(i,r) = ppd(i,r) * qpd(i,r);
    453   Read
    454       VDPA from file GTAPDATA header "VDPA";
    455    
    456   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    457       atpd(i,r) # power of tax on domestic i purchased by private hhld in r #;
    458   Coefficient (ge 0) (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    459       VDPANC(i,r)
    460       # carbon-tax-exclusive value of private consumption of domestic product #;
    461   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    462       VDPANC(i,r) = atpd(i,r) * pm(i,r) * qpd(i,r);
    463   Read
    464       VDPANC from file GTAPDATA header "DPNC";
    465    
    466   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    467       VDPM(i,r) # private consumption expenditure on domestic i in r #;
    468   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    469       VDPM(i,r) = pm(i,r) * qpd(i,r);
    470   Read
    471       VDPM from file GTAPDATA header "VDPM";
    472    
    473   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
    474       ppm(i,s) # price of imports of i by private households in s #;
    475   Variable (orig_level=VIPM)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
    476       qpm(i,s) # private hhld demand for imports of i in region s #;
    477   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    478       VIPA(i,r) # private consumption expenditure on imported i in r #;
    479   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    480       VIPA(i,r) = ppm(i,r) * qpm(i,r);
    481   Read
    482       VIPA from file GTAPDATA header "VIPA";
    483    
    484   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    485       atpm(i,r) # power of tax on imported i purchased by private hhld in r #;
    486   Coefficient (ge 0) (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    487       VIPANC(i,r)
    488       # carbon-tax-exclusive value of private consumption of imported i in r #;
    489   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    490       VIPANC(i,r) = atpm(i,r) * pim(i,r) * qpm(i,r);
    491   Read
    492       VIPANC from file GTAPDATA header "IPNC";
    493    
    494   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    495       VIPM(i,r) # private consumption expenditure on i in r #;
    496   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    497       VIPM(i,r)= pim(i,r) * qpm(i,r);
    498   Read
    499       VIPM from file GTAPDATA header "VIPM";
    500    
    501    
    502   !<
    503       Firms
    504       -----
    505   >!
    506    
    507   Variable (all,i,NSAV_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    508       ps(i,r) # supply price of commodity i in region r #;
    509   Variable (orig_level=VOM)(all,i,NSAV_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    510       qo(i,r) # industry output of commodity i in region r #;
    511   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    512       EVOA(i,r) # value of commodity i output in region r #;
    513   Update (all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    514       EVOA(i,r) = ps(i,r) * qo(i,r);
    515   Read
    516       EVOA from file GTAPDATA header "EVOA";
    517    
    518   Variable (all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    519       pfe(i,j,r) # firms' price for endowment commodity i in ind. j, region r #;
    520   Variable (orig_level=VFM)(all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    521       qfe(i,j,r)  # demand for endowment i for use in ind. j in region r #;
    522   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    523       EVFA(i,j,r) # producer expenditure on i by j in r at agent's prices #;
    524   Update (all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    525       EVFA(i,j,r) = pfe(i,j,r) * qfe(i,j,r);
    526   Read
    527       EVFA from file GTAPDATA header "EVFA";
    528    
    529   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
    530       pfd(i,j,s) # price index for domestic purchases of i by j in region s #;
    531   Variable (orig_level=VDFM)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
    532       qfd(i,j,s)  # domestic good i demanded by industry j in region s #;
    533   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    534       VDFA(i,j,r) # purchases of domestic i for use by j in region r #;
    535   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    536       VDFA(i,j,r) = pfd(i,j,r) * qfd(i,j,r);
    537   Read
    538       VDFA from file GTAPDATA header "VDFA";
    539    
    540   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    541       tfd(i,j,r) # tax on domestic i purchased by j in r #;
    542   Coefficient (ge 0) (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    543       VDFANC(i,j,r)
    544       # carbon-tax-exclusive value of domestic i for use by j in region r #;
    545   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    546       VDFANC(i,j,r) = tfd(i,j,r) * pm(i,r) * qfd(i,j,r);
    547   Read
    548       VDFANC from file GTAPDATA header "DFNC";
    549    
    550   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
    551       pfm(i,j,s) # price index for imports of i by j in region s #;
    552   Variable (orig_level=VIFM)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
    553       qfm(i,j,s) # demand for i by industry j in region s #;
    554   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    555       VIFA(i,j,r) # purchases of imported i for use by j in region r #;
    556   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    557       VIFA(i,j,r) = pfm(i,j,r) * qfm(i,j,r);
    558   Read
    559       VIFA from file GTAPDATA header "VIFA";
    560    
    561   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    562       tfm(i,j,r) # tax on imported i purchased by j in r #;
    563   Coefficient (ge 0) (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    564       VIFANC(i,j,r)
    565       # carbon-tax-exclusive value of imported i for use by j in region r #;
    566   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    567       VIFANC(i,j,r) = tfm(i,j,r) * pim(i,r) * qfm(i,j,r);
    568   Read
    569       VIFANC from file GTAPDATA header "IFNC";
    570    
    571   Variable (all,i,ENDWS_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    572       pmes(i,j,r) # market price of sluggish endowment i used by j in r #;
    573   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    574       VFM(i,j,r) # producer expenditure on i by j in r valued at mkt prices #;
    575   Update (all,i,ENDWM_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    576       VFM(i,j,r) = pm(i,r) * qfe(i,j,r);
    577   Update (all,i,ENDWS_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    578       VFM(i,j,r) = pmes(i,j,r) * qfe(i,j,r);
    579   Read
    580       VFM from file GTAPDATA header "VFM";
    581    
    582   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    583       VIFM(i,j,r) # purchases of imports i for use by j in region r #;
    584   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    585       VIFM(i,j,r) = pim(i,r) * qfm(i,j,r);
    586   Read
    587       VIFM from file GTAPDATA header "VIFM";
    588    
    589   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    590       VDFM(i,j,r) # purchases of domestic i for use by j in region r #;
    591   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    592       VDFM(i,j,r) = pm(i,r) * qfd(i,j,r);
    593   Read
    594       VDFM from file GTAPDATA header "VDFM";
    595    
    596    
    597   !<
    598       Global Bank
    599       -----------
    600   >!
    601    
    602   Variable (all,r,REG)
    603       kb(r) # beginning-of-period capital stock in r #;
    604   Variable (all,r,REG)
    605       pcgds(r) # price of investment goods = ps("cgds",r) #;
    606   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,r,REG)
    607       VDEP(r) # value of capital depeciation in r (exogenous) #;
    608   Update (all,r,REG)
    609       VDEP(r) = kb(r) * pcgds(r);
    610   Read
    611       VDEP from file GTAPDATA header "VDEP";
    612   !<
    613       Value of capital depreciation is used to compute the (exogenous)
    614       depreciation rate and therefore does not appear in update.
    615   >!
    616    
    617    
    618   !<
    619       International Trade and Transport
    620       ---------------------------------
    621   >!
    622    
    623   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
    624       pms(i,r,s) # domestic price for good i supplied from r to region s #;
    625   Variable (orig_level=VXMD)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
    626       qxs(i,r,s) # export sales of commodity i from r to region s #;
    627   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
    628       VIMS(i,r,s) # imports of i from r to s valued at domestic mkt prices #;
    629   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
    630       VIMS(i,r,s) = pms(i,r,s) * qxs(i,r,s);
    631   Read
    632       VIMS from file GTAPDATA header "VIMS";
    633    
    634   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
    635       pcif(i,r,s) # CIF world price of commodity i supplied from r to s #;
    636   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
    637       VIWS(i,r,s) # imports of i from r to s valued CIF (tradeables only) #;
    638   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
    639       VIWS(i,r,s) = pcif(i,r,s) * qxs(i,r,s);
    640   Read
    641       VIWS from file GTAPDATA header "VIWS";
    642    
    643   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
    644       pfob(i,r,s) # FOB world price of commodity i supplied from r to s #;
    645   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
    646       VXWD(i,r,s) # exports of i from r to s valued FOB (tradeables only) #;
    647   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
    648       VXWD(i,r,s) = pfob(i,r,s) * qxs(i,r,s);
    649   Read
    650       VXWD from file GTAPDATA header "VXWD";
    651    
    652   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
    653       VXMD(i,r,s)
    654       # exports of i from r to s valued at mkt prices (tradeables only) #;
    655   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
    656       VXMD(i,r,s) = pm(i,r) * qxs(i,r,s);
    657   Read
    658       VXMD from file GTAPDATA header "VXMD";
    659    
    660   Variable (orig_level=VST)(all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    661       qst(m,r) # sales of m from r to international transport #;
    662   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    663       VST(m,r)
    664       # exprts of m from r for int'l trnsport valued at mkt p (tradeables only) #;
    665   Update (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    666       VST(m,r) = pm(m,r) * qst(m,r);
    667   Read
    668       VST from file GTAPDATA header "VST";
    669    
    670    
    671   !<
    672       Carbon Dioxide Emissions
    673       ------------------------
    674   >!
    675    
    676   !Emissions generated by intermediates use!
    677   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    678       gco2fd(i,j,r)
    679       # carbon dioxide emissions from firms' usage of domestic product #;
    680   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM) (all,r,REG)
    681       CO2DF(i,j,r)
    682       # carbon dioxide emissions from firms' usage of domestic product #;
    683   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    684       CO2DF(i,j,r) = gco2fd(i,j,r);
    685   Read
    686       CO2DF from file GTAPDATA header "CODF";
    687    
    688   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    689       gco2fm(i,j,r)
    690       # carbon dioxide emissions from firms' usage of imports #;
    691   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    692       CO2IF(i,j,r)
    693       # carbon dioxide emissions from firms' usage of imports #;
    694   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    695       CO2IF(i,j,r) = gco2fm(i,j,r);
    696   Read
    697       CO2IF from file GTAPDATA header "COIF";
    698    
    699   !Emissions generated by government consumption!
    700   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    701       gco2gd(i,r)
    702       # carbon dioxide emissions from government consumption of dom. product #;
    703   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    704       CO2DG(i,r)
    705       # carbon dioxide emissions from government consumption of dom. product #;
    706   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    707       CO2DG(i,r) = gco2gd(i,r);
    708   Read
    709       CO2DG from file GTAPDATA header "CODG";
    710    
    711   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    712       gco2gm(i,r)
    713       # carbon dioxide emissions from government consumption of imports #;
    714   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    715       CO2IG(i,r)
    716       # carbon dioxide emissions from government consumption of imports #;
    717   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    718       CO2IG(i,r) = gco2gm(i,r);
    719   Read
    720       CO2IG from file GTAPDATA header "COIG";
    721    
    722   !Emissions generated by private consumption!
    723   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    724       gco2pd(i,r)
    725       # carbon dioxide emissions from private consumption of domestic product #;
    726   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    727       CO2DP(i,r)
    728       # carbon dioxide emissions from private consumption of domestic product #;
    729   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    730       CO2DP(i,r) = gco2pd(i,r);
    731   Read
    732       CO2DP from file GTAPDATA header "CODP";
    733    
    734   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    735       gco2pm(i,r)
    736       # carbon dioxide emissions from private consumption of imports #;
    737   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    738       CO2IP(i,r)
    739       # carbon dioxide emissions from private consumption of imports #;
    740   Update (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    741       CO2IP(i,r) = gco2pm(i,r);
    742   Read
    743       CO2IP from file GTAPDATA header "COIP";
    744    
    745   !<
    746       Carbon Taxation
    747       ---------------
    748   >!
    749    
    750   Variable (change) (all,b,BLOC)
    751       NCTAXB(b) # nominal carbon tax rate (current USD per tonne of CO2) #;
    752   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
    753       NCTAXLEV(r) # nominal carbon tax rate (current USD per tonne of CO2) #;
    754   Update (change) (all,r,REG)
    755       NCTAXLEV(r) = NCTAXB(REGTOBLOC(r));
    756   Read
    757       NCTAXLEV from file GTAPDATA header "NTAX";
    758    
    759    
    760   !<
    761       ----------------
    762       Common VARIABLES
    763       ----------------
    764    
    765       Common variables are defined as variables which are used in more than one
    766       module.  For example, the variable y(r) is used in the Goverment
    767       Consumption, Private Consumption, Firms, Regional Household and
    768       Investment, Global Bank and Savings modules.  Appendices, e.g., Summary
    769       Indices, are not included in this definition.
    770   >!
    771    
    772   Variable (all,r,REG)
    773       y(r) # regional household income in region r #;
    774   Variable (all,r,REG)
    775       p(r) # income deflator #;
    776   Variable (all,r,REG)
    777       pop(r) # regional population #;
    778   Variable (all,i,ENDWS_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    779       qoes(i,j,r) # supply of sluggish endowment i used by j in r #;
    780   Variable (all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    781       endwslack(i,r) # slack variable in endowment market clearing condition #;
    782   !<
    783       This is exogenous, unless the user wishes to employ a partial equilibrium
    784       closure in which the price of one or more of the primary factors is fixed.
    785   >!
    786    
    787   Variable (all,r,REG)
    788       pgov(r) # price index for gov't hhld expenditure in region r #;
    789   Variable (all,r,REG)
    790       yg(r)
    791       # regional government consumption expenditure in region r #;
    792   Variable (all,r,REG)
    793       ug(r) # per capita utility from gov't expend. in region r #;
    794   Variable (all,r,REG)
    795       ppriv(r)
    796       # price index for private consumption expenditure in region r #;
    797   Variable (all,r,REG)
    798       uepriv(r)
    799       # elasticity of cost wrt utility from private consumption #;
    800   Variable (all,r,REG)
    801       yp(r) # regional private consumption expenditure in region r #;
    802   Variable (all,r,REG)
    803       up(r) # per capita utility from private expend. in region r #;
    804   Variable (all,i,NSAV_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    805       to(i,r) # output (or income) tax in region r #;
    806   !<
    807       Note:  It is important that the user NOT shock the tax on capital goods
    808       output, as this will cause an inconsistency in the update relationship for
    809       VOM(cgds).
    810   >!
    811   Variable (orig_level=VIM)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
    812       qim(i,s) # aggregate imports of i in region s, market price weights #;
    813   Variable
    814       globalcgds # global supply of capital goods for NET investment #;
    815   Variable
    816       pcgdswld # world average price of capital goods (net investment weights) #;
    817   Variable (all,r,REG)
    818       gco2t(r) # carbon dioxide emissions #;
    819   Variable (change) (all,r,REG)
    820       DVCO2TRA(r) # net emissions trading revenue #;
    821    
    822   !<
    823       The following variables could be dropped when converting to levels
    824       equation for income.  They are only needed for the linearized equation.
    825       The idea here is to look at the ratio of taxes to income in order to
    826       preserve homogeneity in prices.  (We could also look at changes in tax
    827       revenue, but then a uniform price increase would change this variable.)
    828       Obviously a simple percentage change variable doesn't work, since many
    829       taxes are initially zero.  The basic logic of this approach is as follows:
    830    
    831       Let R be the ratio of taxes to income: R = T/Y, then:
    832           dR = d(T/Y) = R(t - y)/100
    833       multiply through by Y to get:
    834           YdR = dT - Ty/100
    835       This ratio change is computed for each tax type and for total taxes.  Then
    836       the change in tax revenue itself may be computed as:
    837           dT = YdR + Ty/100
    838       in order to determine regional income.
    839   >!
    840    
    841   Variable (change) (all,r,REG)
    842       del_taxrgc(r) # change in ratio of government consumption tax to INCOME #;
    843   Variable (change) (all,r,REG)
    844       del_taxrpc(r) # change in ratio of private consumption tax to INCOME #;
    845   Variable (change) (all,r,REG)
    846       del_taxriu(r) # change in ratio of tax on intermediate usage to INCOME #;
    847   Variable (change) (all,r,REG)
    848       del_taxrfu(r) # change in ratio of tax on primary factor usage to INCOME #;
    849   Variable (change) (all,r,REG)
    850       del_taxrout(r) # change in ratio of output tax to INCOME #;
    851   Variable (change) (all,r,REG)
    852       del_taxrexp(r) # change in ratio of export tax to INCOME #;
    853   Variable (change) (all,r,REG)
    854       del_taxrimp(r) # change in ratio of import tax to INCOME #;
    855   Variable (change) (all,r,REG)
    856       del_taxrinc(r) # change in ratio of income tax to INCOME #;
    857   Variable (change)(all,r,REG)
    858       del_ctaxr(r) # change in ratio of carbon tax to INCOME #;
    859    
    860    
    861   !<
    862       -------------------
    863       Common COEFFICIENTS
    864       -------------------
    865    
    866       Key Derivatives of the Base Data
    867       Regional Expenditure and Income
    868       Indirect Tax Receipts
    869       Miscellaneous Coefficients
    870    
    871       Common Coefficients are defined as coefficients which are used in more
    872       than one module.  For example, ESUBD(i) is used in the Goverment
    873       Household, Private Household, and Firms modules.
    874   >!
    875    
    876    
    877   !<
    878       Key Derivatives of the Base Data
    879       --------------------------------
    880   >!
    881    
    882   Coefficient (all,i,DEMD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    883       VFAD(i,j,r) # producer expend. on i by j in r valued at agent's prices #;
    884   Formula (all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    885       VFAD(i,j,r) = EVFA(i,j,r);
    886   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
    887       VFAD(i,j,s) = VDFA(i,j,s) + VIFA(i,j,s);
    888    
    889   Coefficient (all,i,NSAV_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    890       VOA(i,r) # value of commodity i output in region r at agent's prices #;
    891   Formula (all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    892       VOA(i,r) = EVOA(i,r);
    893   Formula (all,i,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    894       VOA(i,r) = sum(j,DEMD_COMM, VFAD(j,i,r));
    895    
    896   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    897       VDM(i,r) # domestic sales of i in r at mkt prices (tradeables only) #;
    898   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    899       VDM(i,r) = VDPM(i,r) + VDGM(i,r) + sum(j,PROD_COMM, VDFM(i,j,r));
    900    
    901   Coefficient (all,i,NSAV_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    902       VOM(i,r) # value of commodity i output in region r at market prices #;
    903   Formula (all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    904       VOM(i,r) = sum(j,PROD_COMM, VFM(i,j,r));
    905   Formula (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    906       VOM(m,r) = VDM(m,r) + sum(s,REG, VXMD(m,r,s)) + VST(m,r);
    907   Formula (all,i,NMRG_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    908       VOM(i,r) = VDM(i,r) + sum(s,REG, VXMD(i,r,s));
    909   Formula (all,h,CGDS_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    910       VOM(h,r) = VOA(h,r);
    911    
    912    
    913   !<
    914       Regional Expenditure and Income
    915       -------------------------------
    916    
    917       Regional income is allocated between private consumption expenditure,
    918       government consumption expenditure, and saving.
    919    
    920    
    921       Expenditure of Regional Household
    922       .................................
    923    
    924                  Regional household(h.h.)
    925                   Expenditure = Income
    926                            _/|\_
    927                          _/  |  \_
    928                        _/    |    \_
    929                      _/      |      \_
    930                    _/        |        \_
    931          Private h.h.        |        Government h.h.
    932          ( PRIVEXP )         |          ( GOVEXP )
    933             _/\_             |              _/\_
    934           _/    \_           |            _/    \_
    935          /        \          |           /        \
    936       Domestic  Imported   Savings    Domestic    Imported
    937        Goods     Goods     ( SAVE )    Goods       Goods
    938       ( VDPA )  ( VIPA )              ( VDGA )    ( VIGA )
    939    
    940       Note: The coefficients at the ends of branches are
    941             Base Data, e.g., VDPA, SAVE.
    942   >!
    943    
    944   ! government consumption expenditure, GOVEXP !
    945   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    946       VGAT(i,r) # government consn expenditure on i in r at agent's prices #;
    947   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
    948       VGAT(i,s) = VDGA(i,s) + VIGA(i,s);
    949   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
    950       GOVEXP(r) # government expenditure in region r #;
    951   Formula (all,r,REG)
    952       GOVEXP(r) = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, VGAT(i,r));
    953    
    954   ! private consumption expenditure, PRIVEXP !
    955   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    956       VPAT(i,r) # private hhld expenditure on i in r valued at agent's prices #;
    957   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
    958       VPAT(i,s) = VDPA(i,s) + VIPA(i,s);
    959   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
    960       PRIVEXP(r) # private consumption expenditure in region r #;
    961   Formula (all,r,REG)
    962       PRIVEXP(r) = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, VPAT(i,r));
    963    
    964   ! aggregate expenditure + saving = aggregate income !
    965   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
    966       INCOME(r) # level of expenditure, which equals NET income in region r #;
    967   Formula (all,r,REG)
    968       INCOME(r) = PRIVEXP(r) + GOVEXP(r) + SAVE(r);
    969    
    970    
    971   !<
    972       Indirect Tax Receipts
    973       ---------------------
    974   >!
    975    
    976   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    977       DFTAX(i,j,r) # ordinary tax on intermediate usage of domestic product #;
    978   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    979       DFTAX(i,j,r) = VDFANC(i,j,r) - VDFM(i,j,r);
    980    
    981   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    982       DFCTAX(i,j,r) # carbon tax on intermediate usage of domestic product #;
    983   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    984       DFCTAX(i,j,r) = VDFA(i,j,r) - VDFANC(i,j,r);
    985    
    986   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    987       IFTAX(i,j,r) # ordinary tax on intermediate usage of imports #;
    988   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    989       IFTAX(i,j,r) = VIFANC(i,j,r) - VIFM(i,j,r);
    990    
    991   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    992       IFCTAX(i,j,r) # carbon tax on intermediate usage of imports #;
    993   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
    994       IFCTAX(i,j,r) = VIFA(i,j,r) - VIFANC(i,j,r);
    995    
    996   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
    997       TIU(r) # ordinary tax on intermediate usage #;
    998   Formula (all,r,REG)
    999       TIU(r) = sum(j,PROD_COMM, sum(i,TRAD_COMM, DFTAX(i,j,r) + IFTAX(i,j,r)));
   1000    
   1001    
   1002   !<
   1003       Taxes on Private Consumption
   1004       - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
   1005   >!
   1006    
   1007   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1008       DPTAX(i,r) # ordinary tax on private consumption of domestic product #;
   1009   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1010       DPTAX(i,r) = VDPANC(i,r) - VDPM(i,r);
   1011    
   1012   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1013       DPCTAX(i,r) # carbon tax on private consumption of domestic product #;
   1014   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1015       DPCTAX(i,r) = VDPA(i,r) - VDPANC(i,r);
   1016    
   1017   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1018       IPTAX(i,r) # ordinary tax on private consumption of imports #;
   1019   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1020       IPTAX(i,r) = VIPANC(i,r) - VIPM(i,r);
   1021   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1022       IPCTAX(i,r) # carbon tax on private consumption of imports #;
   1023   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1024       IPCTAX(i,r) = VIPA(i,r) - VIPANC(i,r);
   1025    
   1026   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   1027       TPC(r) # ordinary tax on private consumption #;
   1028   Formula (all,r,REG)
   1029       TPC(r) = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, DPTAX(i,r) + IPTAX(i,r));
   1030    
   1031    
   1032   !<
   1033       Taxes on Government Consumption
   1034       - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
   1035   >!
   1036    
   1037   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1038       DGTAX(i,r) # ordinary tax on government consumption of domestic product #;
   1039   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1040       DGTAX(i,r) = VDGANC(i,r) - VDGM(i,r);
   1041    
   1042   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1043       DGCTAX(i,r) # carbon tax on gov. cons. of domestic good i in region r #;
   1044   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1045       DGCTAX(i,r) = VDGA(i,r) - VDGANC(i,r);
   1046    
   1047   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1048       IGTAX(i,r) # ordinary tax on government consumption of imports #;
   1049   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1050       IGTAX(i,r) = VIGANC(i,r) - VIGM(i,r);
   1051    
   1052   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1053       IGCTAX(i,r) # carbon tax on government consumption of imports #;
   1054   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1055       IGCTAX(i,r) = VIGA(i,r) - VIGANC(i,r);
   1056    
   1057   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   1058       TGC(r) # ordinary tax on government consumption #;
   1059   Formula (all,r,REG)
   1060       TGC(r) = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, DGTAX(i,r) + IGTAX(i,r));
   1061    
   1062    
   1063   !<
   1064       Other Taxes
   1065       - - - - - -
   1066   >!
   1067    
   1068   Coefficient (all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1069       ETAX(i,j,r) # tax on use of endowment good i by industry j in region r #;
   1070   Formula (all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1071       ETAX(i,j,r) = VFAD(i,j,r) - VFM(i,j,r);
   1072   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   1073       TFU(r) # firms' tax payments on primary factor usage in r #;
   1074   Formula (all,r,REG)
   1075       TFU(r) = sum(i,ENDW_COMM, sum(j,PROD_COMM, ETAX(i,j,r)));
   1076    
   1077   Coefficient (all,i,NSAV_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1078       PTAX(i,r) # output tax on good i in region r #;
   1079   Formula (all,i,NSAV_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1080       PTAX(i,r) = VOM(i,r) - VOA(i,r);
   1081   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   1082       TOUT(r) # production tax payments in r #;
   1083   Formula (all,r,REG)
   1084       TOUT(r) = sum(i,PROD_COMM, PTAX(i,r));
   1085    
   1086   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   1087       XTAXD(i,r,s) # tax on exports of good i from source r to destination s #;
   1088   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   1089       XTAXD(i,r,s) = VXWD(i,r,s) - VXMD(i,r,s);
   1090   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   1091       TEX(r) # export tax payments in r #;
   1092   Formula (all,r,REG)
   1093       TEX(r) = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(s,REG, XTAXD(i,r,s)));
   1094    
   1095   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   1096       MTAX(i,r,s) # tax on imports of good i from source r in destination s #;
   1097   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   1098       MTAX(i,r,s) = VIMS(i,r,s) - VIWS(i,r,s);
   1099   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   1100       TIM(r) # import tax payments in r #;
   1101   Formula (all,r,REG)
   1102       TIM(r) = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(s,REG, MTAX(i,s,r)));
   1103    
   1104    
   1105   !<
   1106       Miscellaneous Coefficients
   1107       --------------------------
   1108   >!
   1109    
   1110   ! domestic/imported substitution elasticity !
   1111   Coefficient (parameter)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   1112       ESUBD(i)
   1113       # region-generic el. of sub. domestic/imported for all agents #;
   1114   Read
   1115       ESUBD from file GTAPPARM header "ESBD";
   1116    
   1117   ! net global investment expenditure !
   1118   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   1119       REGINV(r) # regional GROSS investment in r (value of "cgds" output) #;
   1120   Formula (all,r,REG)
   1121       REGINV(r) = sum(k,CGDS_COMM, VOA(k,r));
   1122   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   1123       NETINV(r) # regional NET investment in region r #;
   1124   Formula (all,r,REG)
   1125       NETINV(r) = sum(k,CGDS_COMM, VOA(k,r)) - VDEP(r);
   1126   Coefficient
   1127       GLOBINV # global expenditures on net investment #;
   1128   Formula
   1129       GLOBINV = sum(r,REG, NETINV(r));
   1130    
   1131   ! elasticity of cost wrt utility from private consumption !
   1132   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   1133       UELASPRIV(r) # elasticity of cost wrt utility from private consumption #;
   1134    
   1135   ! carbon dioxide emissions !
   1136   Coefficient(all,r,REG)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   1137       CO2(r,i) # carbon dioxide emissions (millions of tonnes of CO2) #;
   1138   Formula (all,r,REG)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   1139       CO2(r,i) = sum(j,PROD_COMM, CO2DF(i,j,r)) + sum(j,PROD_COMM, CO2IF(i,j,r))
   1140           + CO2DG(i,r) + CO2IG(i,r) + CO2DP(i,r) + CO2IP(i,r);
   1141    
   1142   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   1143       CO2T(r) # carbon dioxide emissions (millions of tonnes of CO2) #;
   1144   Formula (all,r,REG)
   1145       CO2T(r) = sum(i,CTAX_COMM, CO2(r,i));
   1146    
   1147   Coefficient (all,b,BLOC)
   1148       CO2TB(b)# carbon dioxide emissions (millions of tonnes of CO2) #;
   1149   Formula (all,b,BLOC)
   1150       CO2TB(b) = sum(r,REG: REGTOBLOC(r) = b, CO2T(r));
   1151    
   1152    
   1153   !<
   1154       =======
   1155       Modules
   1156       =======
   1157    
   1158       1. Government Consumption
   1159       2. Private Consumption
   1160       3. Firms
   1161       4. Investment, Global Bank, and Savings
   1162       5. International Trade
   1163       6. International Transport Services
   1164       7. International Emissions Trade
   1165       8. Regional Household
   1166       9. Equilibrium Conditions
   1167   >!
   1168    
   1169    
   1170   !<
   1171       -------------------------
   1172       1. Government Consumption
   1173       -------------------------
   1174    
   1175       1-0. Module-Specific Variables
   1176       1-1. Composite Tradeables
   1177       1-2. Notational Links
   1178       1-3. Energy Nest
   1179       1-4. Non-Energy Nest
   1180       1-5. Top of the Government Consumption Structure
   1181    
   1182    
   1183   >!
   1184    
   1185   !<
   1186       1-0. Module-Specific Variables
   1187       ------------------------------
   1188    
   1189       only used in this Government Consumption module
   1190   >!
   1191    
   1192   Set
   1193       SUBG_COMM # subutilities in government consumption #
   1194       (eny, neny);
   1195   Set
   1196       GOV_COMM # commodities demanded by government #
   1197       = TRAD_COMM union SUBG_COMM;
   1198    
   1199   Variable (all,i,GOV_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1200       pg(i,r) # government consumption price for commodity i in region r #;
   1201   Variable (all,i,GOV_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1202       qg(i,r) # government hhld demand for commodity i in region r #;
   1203   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1204       pgt(i,r) # government consumption price for commodity i in region r #;
   1205   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1206       qgt(i,r) # government hhld demand for commodity i in region r #;
   1207    
   1208   Coefficient (all,i,GOV_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1209       VGA(i,r) # government expend. on i in r valued at agent's prices #;
   1210   Coefficient (all,i,SUBG_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1211       VGAS(i,r) # government expend. on i in r valued at agent's prices #;
   1212    
   1213    
   1214   !<
   1215       1-1. Composite Tradeables
   1216       -------------------------
   1217   >!
   1218    
   1219   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) default 1;
   1220   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1221       SHVDGANC(i,r)
   1222       # share of carbon-tax-excl. value of gov. consumption of domestic i in r #;
   1223   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1224       SHVDGANC(i,r) = VDGANC(i,r) / VDGA(i,r);
   1225   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) off;
   1226    
   1227   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) default 0;
   1228   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1229       CO2DGVDGA(i,r)
   1230       # emissions intensity of government consumption of domestic i in r #;
   1231   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1232       CO2DGVDGA(i,r) = CO2DG(i,r) / VDGA(i,r);
   1233   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) off;
   1234    
   1235   Equation GHHDPRICE
   1236   # taxation of government consumption of domestic product #
   1237   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1238       pgd(i,r)= SHVDGANC(i,r) * (pm(i,r) + tgd(i,r))
   1239           + 100.0 * CO2DGVDGA(i,r) * NCTAXB(REGTOBLOC(r));
   1240    
   1241   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) default 1;
   1242   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1243       SHVIGANC(i,r)
   1244       # share of carbon-tax-excl. value of gov. consumption of imported i in r #;
   1245   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1246       SHVIGANC(i,r)=VIGANC(i,r) / VIGA(i,r);
   1247   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) off;
   1248    
   1249   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) default 0;
   1250   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1251       CO2IGVIGA(i,r)
   1252       # emissions intensity of government consumption of imported i in r #;
   1253   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1254       CO2IGVIGA(i,r) = CO2IG(i,r) / VIGA(i,r);
   1255    
   1256    
   1257   Equation GHHIPRICES
   1258   # taxation of government consumption of imports #
   1259   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1260       pgm(i,r) = SHVIGANC(i,r) * (pim(i,r) + tgm(i,r))
   1261           + 100.0 * CO2IGVIGA(i,r) * NCTAXB(REGTOBLOC(r));
   1262    
   1263   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   1264       GMSHR(i,s) # share of imports for gov't hhld at agent's prices #;
   1265   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   1266       GMSHR(i,s) = VIGA(i,s) / VGAT(i,s);
   1267   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) off;
   1268   Equation GCOMPRICE
   1269   # government consumption price for composite commodities (HT 42) #
   1270   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   1271       pgt(i,s) =  GMSHR(i,s) * pgm(i,s) + [1 - GMSHR(i,s)] * pgd(i,s);
   1272    
   1273   Equation GHHLDAGRIMP
   1274   # government consumption demand for aggregate imports (HT 43) #
   1275   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   1276       qgm(i,s) = qgt(i,s) + ESUBD(i) * [pgt(i,s) - pgm(i,s)];
   1277    
   1278   Equation GHHLDDOM
   1279   # government consumption demand for domestic goods (HT 44) #
   1280   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   1281       qgd(i,s) = qgt(i,s) + ESUBD(i) * [pgt(i,s) - pgd(i,s)];
   1282    
   1283   Equation TGCRATIO
   1284   # change in ratio of government consumption tax payments to regional income #
   1285   (all,r,REG)
   1286       100.0 * INCOME(r) * del_taxrgc(r) + TGC(r) * y(r)
   1287           = sum(i,TRAD_COMM,
   1288               VDGANC(i,r) * tgd(i,r) + DGTAX(i,r) * [pm(i,r) + qgd(i,r)])
   1289           + sum(i,TRAD_COMM,
   1290               VIGANC(i,r) * tgm(i,r) + IGTAX(i,r) * [pim(i,r) + qgm(i,r)]);
   1291    
   1292    
   1293   !<
   1294       1-2. Notational Links
   1295       ---------------------
   1296   >!
   1297    
   1298   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1299       VGA(i,r) = VGAT(i,r);
   1300    
   1301   Equation PGTEQ # prices into the government consumption system #
   1302   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1303       pgt(i,r) = pg(i,r) ;
   1304    
   1305   Equation QGTEQ # quantities from the government consumption system #
   1306   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1307       qgt(i,r) = qg(i,r) ;
   1308    
   1309    
   1310   !<
   1311       1-3. Energy Nest
   1312       ----------------
   1313   >!
   1314   Set
   1315       ENY_GCOMM # inputs into government energy subutility #
   1316       (coal, oil, gas, oil_pcts, electricity);
   1317   Subset
   1318       ENY_GCOMM is subset of TRAD_COMM;
   1319    
   1320   Formula (all,r,REG)
   1321       VGAS("eny",r) = sum(i,ENY_GCOMM, VGA(i,r));
   1322   Formula (all,r,REG)
   1323       VGA("eny",r) = VGAS("eny",r);
   1324    
   1325   Coefficient
   1326       GSIZE_ENY # size of ENY_GCOMM set #;
   1327   Formula
   1328       GSIZE_ENY = sum(i,ENY_GCOMM, 1);
   1329    
   1330   Coefficient (all,i,ENY_GCOMM)(all,r,REG)
   1331       GSHENY(i,r) # share of i in cost of energy subutility #;
   1332   Formula (all,i,ENY_GCOMM)(all,r,REG: VGAS("eny",r) = 0)
   1333       GSHENY(i,r) = 1.0 / GSIZE_ENY;
   1334   Formula (all,i,ENY_GCOMM)(all,r,REG: VGAS("eny",r) > 0)
   1335       GSHENY(i,r) = VGA(i,r) / VGAS("eny",r);
   1336    
   1337   Equation ENYGPRICE # price of energy subutility #
   1338   (all,r,REG)
   1339       pg("eny",r) = sum(k,ENY_GCOMM, GSHENY(k,r)* pg(k,r));
   1340    
   1341   Coefficient (parameter) (all,r,REG)
   1342       ELGENY(r) # elasticity of substitution in energy subconsumption #;
   1343   Read
   1344       ELGENY from file GTAPPARM header "EGEN";
   1345    
   1346   Equation ENYGDEMAND # demand for inputs into energy subconsumption #
   1347   (all,i,ENY_GCOMM)(all,r,REG)
   1348       qg(i,r) = qg("eny",r) - ELGENY(r) * [pg(i,r) - pg("eny",r)];
   1349    
   1350    
   1351   !<
   1352       1-4. Non-Energy Nest
   1353       --------------------
   1354   >!
   1355    
   1356   Set
   1357       NENY_GCOMM # non-energy subutility commodities # = TRAD_COMM - ENY_GCOMM;
   1358    
   1359   Formula (all,r,REG)
   1360       VGAS("neny",r) = sum(i,NENY_GCOMM, VGA(i,r));
   1361   Formula (all,r,REG)
   1362       VGA("neny",r) = VGAS("neny",r);
   1363    
   1364   Coefficient
   1365       GSIZE_NENY # size of NENY_GCOMM set #;
   1366   Formula
   1367       GSIZE_NENY = sum(i,NENY_GCOMM, 1);
   1368    
   1369   Coefficient (all,i,NENY_GCOMM)(all,r,REG)
   1370       GSHNENY(i,r)
   1371       # share of i in cost of non-energy subutility #;
   1372   Formula (all,i,NENY_GCOMM)(all,r,REG: VGAS("neny",r) = 0)
   1373       GSHNENY(i,r) = 1.0 / GSIZE_NENY;
   1374   Formula (all,i,NENY_GCOMM)(all,r,REG: VGAS("neny",r) > 0)
   1375       GSHNENY(i,r) = VGA(i,r) / VGAS("neny",r);
   1376    
   1377   Equation NENYGPRICE # price of non-energy subutility #
   1378   (all,r,REG)
   1379       pg("neny",r) = sum(k,NENY_GCOMM, GSHNENY(k,r)* pg(k,r));
   1380    
   1381   Coefficient (parameter) (all,r,REG)
   1382       ELGNENY(r)
   1383       # elasticity of substitution in non-energy subconsumption #;
   1384   Read
   1385       ELGNENY from file GTAPPARM header "EGNN";
   1386    
   1387   Equation NENYGDEMAND
   1388   # demand for inputs into non-energy subconsumption #
   1389   (all,i,NENY_GCOMM)(all,r,REG)
   1390       qg(i,r) = qg("neny",r) - ELGNENY(r) * [pg(i,r) - pg("neny",r)];
   1391    
   1392    
   1393   !<
   1394       1-5. Top of the Government Consumption Structure
   1395       ------------------------------------------------
   1396   >!
   1397    
   1398   Set
   1399       UG_COMM # inputs into top of government consumption structure #
   1400       (eny, neny);
   1401   Subset
   1402       UG_COMM is subset of GOV_COMM ;
   1403    
   1404   Equation GPRICEINDEX
   1405   # definition of price index for aggregate gov't purchases (HT 40) #
   1406   (all,r,REG)
   1407       pgov(r) = sum(i,UG_COMM, [VGA(i,r) / GOVEXP(r)] * pg(i,r));
   1408    
   1409   Coefficient (parameter) (all,r,REG)
   1410       ELGUG(r)
   1411       # elasticity of substitution in the top of government consumption nest #;
   1412   Read
   1413       ELGUG from file GTAPPARM header "EGUG";
   1414    
   1415   Equation GOVDMNDS
   1416   # government consumption demands for top nest commodities (HT 41) #
   1417   (all,i,UG_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1418       qg(i,r) - pop(r) = ug(r) - ELGUG(r) * [pg(i,r) - pgov(r)];
   1419    
   1420   Equation GOVU
   1421   # utility from government consumption in r #
   1422   (all,r,REG)
   1423       yg(r) - pop(r) = pgov(r) + ug(r);
   1424    
   1425    
   1426   !<
   1427       -----------------------------
   1428       2. Private Consumption Module
   1429       -----------------------------
   1430    
   1431       2-0. Module-Specific Variables
   1432       2-1. Composite Tradeables
   1433       2-2. Notational Links
   1434       2-3. Energy Nest
   1435       2-4. Top of the Private Consumption Structure
   1436    
   1437   >!
   1438    
   1439    
   1440   !<
   1441       2-0. Module-Specific Variables
   1442       ------------------------------
   1443    
   1444       only used in this Private Consumption module
   1445   >!
   1446    
   1447   Set
   1448       SUBP_COMM # subutilities in private consumption # (eny);
   1449   Set
   1450       PRIV_COMM # commodities demanded in private consumption #
   1451       = TRAD_COMM union SUBP_COMM;
   1452    
   1453   Variable (all,i,PRIV_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1454       pp(i,r) # private consumption price for commodity i in region r #;
   1455   Variable (all,i,PRIV_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1456       qp(i,r) # private hhld demand for commodity i in region r #;
   1457   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1458       ppt(i,r) # private consumption price for commodity i in region r #;
   1459   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1460       qpt(i,r) # private hhld demand for commodity i in region r #;
   1461    
   1462   Coefficient (all,i,PRIV_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1463       VPA(i,r) # private hhld expend. on i in r valued at agent's prices #;
   1464   Coefficient (all,i,SUBP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1465       VPAS(i,r) # private hhld expend. on i in r valued at agent's prices #;
   1466    
   1467    
   1468   !<
   1469       2-1. Composite Tradeables
   1470       -------------------------
   1471   >!
   1472    
   1473   Variable (all,r,REG)
   1474       tp(r) # comm.-, source-gen. shift in tax on private cons. #;
   1475   !<
   1476       The variable tp(r) can be swapped with del_ttaxr(r) in order to generate a
   1477       tax replacement scenario, whereby taxes remain a constant share of
   1478       national income.
   1479   >!
   1480    
   1481   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1482       tpd(i,r) # comm.-, source-spec. shift in tax on private cons. of dom. #;
   1483   Equation TPDSHIFT
   1484   # permits uniform consumption tax change #
   1485   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1486       atpd(i,r) = tpd(i,r) + tp(r);
   1487    
   1488   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) default 1;
   1489   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1490       SHVDPANC(i,r)
   1491       # share of carbon-tax-excl. value of priv. consumption of dom. product #;
   1492   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1493       SHVDPANC(i,r) = VDPANC(i,r) / VDPA(i,r);
   1494   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) off;
   1495    
   1496   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) default 0;
   1497   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1498       CO2DPVDPA(i,r)
   1499       # emissions intensity of private consumption of domestic product #;
   1500   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1501       CO2DPVDPA(i,r) = CO2DP(i,r) / VDPA(i,r);
   1502   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) off;
   1503    
   1504   Equation PHHDPRICE
   1505   # taxation of private consumption of domestic product #
   1506   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1507       ppd(i,r) = SHVDPANC(i,r) * (pm(i,r) + atpd(i,r))
   1508           + 100.0 * CO2DPVDPA(i,r) * NCTAXB(REGTOBLOC(r));
   1509    
   1510   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1511       tpm(i,r) # comm.-, source-spec. shift in tax on private cons. of imp. #;
   1512   Equation TPMSHIFT
   1513   # permits uniform consumption tax change #
   1514   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1515       atpm(i,r) = tpm(i,r) + tp(r);
   1516    
   1517   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) default 1;
   1518   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1519       SHVIPANC(i,r)
   1520       # share of carbon-tax-excl. value of priv. consumption of imports #;
   1521   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1522       SHVIPANC(i,r) = VIPANC(i,r) / VIPA(i,r);
   1523   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) off;
   1524    
   1525   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) default 0;
   1526   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1527       CO2IPVIPA(i,r)
   1528       # emissions intensity of private consumption of imports #;
   1529   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1530       CO2IPVIPA(i,r) = CO2IP(i,r) / VIPA(i,r);
   1531   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) off;
   1532    
   1533   Equation PHHIPRICES
   1534   # taxation of private consumption of imports #
   1535   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1536       ppm(i,r) = SHVIPANC(i,r) * (pim(i,r) + atpm(i,r))
   1537           + 100.0 * CO2IPVIPA(i,r) * NCTAXB(REGTOBLOC(r));
   1538    
   1539   Equation TPCRATIO
   1540   # change in ratio of private consumption tax payments to regional income #
   1541   (all,r,REG)
   1542       100.0 * INCOME(r) * del_taxrpc(r) + TPC(r) * y(r)
   1543           = sum(i,TRAD_COMM,
   1544               VDPANC(i,r) * atpd(i,r) + DPTAX(i,r) * [pm(i,r) + qpd(i,r)])
   1545           + sum(i,TRAD_COMM,
   1546               VIPANC(i,r) * atpm(i,r) + IPTAX(i,r) * [pim(i,r) + qpm(i,r)]);
   1547    
   1548   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   1549       PMSHR(i,s) # share of imports for priv hhld at agent's prices #;
   1550   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   1551       PMSHR(i,s) = VIPA(i,s) / VPAT(i,s);
   1552    
   1553   Equation PCOMPRICE
   1554   # private consumption price for composite commodities (HT 47) #
   1555   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   1556       ppt(i,s) = PMSHR(i,s) * ppm(i,s) + [1 - PMSHR(i,s)] * ppd(i,s);
   1557    
   1558   Equation PHHLDDOM
   1559   # private consumption demand for domestic goods (HT 48) #
   1560   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   1561       qpd(i,s) = qpt(i,s) + ESUBD(i) * [ppt(i,s) - ppd(i,s)];
   1562    
   1563   Equation PHHLDAGRIMP
   1564   # private consumption demand for aggregate imports (HT 49) #
   1565   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   1566       qpm(i,s) = qpt(i,s) + ESUBD(i) * [ppt(i,s) - ppm(i,s)];
   1567    
   1568    
   1569   !<
   1570       2-2. Notational Links
   1571       ---------------------
   1572   >!
   1573    
   1574   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1575       VPA(i,r) = VPAT(i,r);
   1576    
   1577   Equation PPTEQ # prices into the private consumption system #
   1578   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1579       ppt(i,r) = pp(i,r) ;
   1580    
   1581   Equation QPTEQ # quantities from the private consumption system #
   1582   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1583       qpt(i,r) = qp(i,r) ;
   1584    
   1585    
   1586   !<
   1587       2-3. Energy Nest
   1588       ----------------
   1589   >!
   1590    
   1591   Set
   1592       ENY_PCOMM #inputs into private energy subutility#
   1593       (coal, oil, gas, oil_pcts, electricity);
   1594   Subset
   1595       ENY_PCOMM is subset of TRAD_COMM;
   1596    
   1597   Formula (all,r,REG)
   1598       VPAS("eny",r) = sum(i,ENY_PCOMM, VPA(i,r));
   1599   Formula (all,r,REG)
   1600       VPA("eny",r) = VPAS("eny",r);
   1601    
   1602   Coefficient
   1603       PSIZE_ENY # size of ENY_PCOMM set #;
   1604   Formula
   1605       PSIZE_ENY = sum(i,ENY_PCOMM, 1);
   1606    
   1607   Coefficient (all,i,ENY_PCOMM)(all,r,REG)
   1608       PSHENY(i,r) # share of i in cost of energy subutility #;
   1609   Formula (all,i,ENY_PCOMM)(all,r,REG: VPAS("eny",r) = 0)
   1610       PSHENY(i,r) = 1.0 / PSIZE_ENY;
   1611   Formula (all,i,ENY_PCOMM)(all,r,REG: VPAS("eny",r) > 0)
   1612       PSHENY(i,r) = VPA(i,r) / VPAS("eny",r);
   1613    
   1614   Equation ENYPPRICE # price of energy subutility #
   1615   (all,r,REG)
   1616       pp("eny",r) = sum(k,ENY_PCOMM, PSHENY(k,r) * pp(k,r));
   1617    
   1618   Coefficient (parameter) (all,r,REG)
   1619       ELPENY(r) # elasticity of substitution in energy subconsumption #;
   1620   Read
   1621       ELPENY from file GTAPPARM header "EPEN";
   1622    
   1623   Equation ENYPDEMAND # demand for inputs into energy subconsumption #
   1624   (all,i,ENY_PCOMM)(all,r,REG)
   1625       qp(i,r) = qp("eny",r) - ELPENY(r) * [pp(i,r) - pp("eny",r)];
   1626    
   1627    
   1628   !<
   1629       2-4. Top of the Private Consumption Structure
   1630       ---------------------------------------------
   1631   >!
   1632    
   1633   Set NENY_PCOMM
   1634       #inputs into private non-energy subutility# = TRAD_COMM - ENY_PCOMM;
   1635    
   1636   Set ENY # private energy composite # (eny);
   1637    
   1638   Set
   1639       UP_COMM
   1640       # inputs into top of private consumption structure # = ENY + NENY_PCOMM;
   1641    
   1642   Subset
   1643       UP_COMM is subset of PRIV_COMM ;
   1644    
   1645   Coefficient (parameter)(all,i,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1646       INCPAR(i,r)
   1647       # expansion parameter in the CDE minimum expenditure function #;
   1648   Read
   1649       INCPAR from file GTAPPARM header "INCP";
   1650    
   1651   Coefficient (parameter)(all,i,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1652       SUBPAR(i,r)
   1653       # substitution parameter in CDE minimum expenditure function #;
   1654   Read
   1655       SUBPAR from file GTAPPARM header "SUBP";
   1656    
   1657   Coefficient (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1658       PSHUP(i,r) # share of private hhld consumption devoted to good i in r #;
   1659   Formula (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1660       PSHUP(i,r) = VPA(i,r) / sum(k,UP_COMM, VPA(k,r));
   1661    
   1662   Formula (all,r,REG)
   1663       UELASPRIV(r) = sum(i,UP_COMM, PSHUP(i,r) * INCPAR(i,r));
   1664    
   1665   !<
   1666       (HT F1 - F3)
   1667   >!
   1668   Coefficient (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1669       ALPHA(i,r) # 1 - sub. parameter in the CDE minimum expenditure function #;
   1670   Formula (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1671       ALPHA(i,r) = 1 - SUBPAR(i,r);
   1672    
   1673   Coefficient (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,k,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1674       APE(i,k,r) # Allen partial elst. of sub. between composite i and k in r #;
   1675   Formula (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,k,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1676       APE(i,k,r)
   1677           = ALPHA(i,r) + ALPHA(k,r) - sum(n,UP_COMM, PSHUP(n,r) * ALPHA(n,r));
   1678   Formula (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1679       APE(i,i,r)
   1680           = 2.0 * ALPHA(i,r)
   1681           - sum(n,UP_COMM, PSHUP(n,r) * ALPHA(n,r))
   1682           - ALPHA(i,r) / PSHUP(i,r);
   1683    
   1684   Coefficient (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1685       EY(i,r) # income elast. of private hhld demand for i in r (HT F4) #;
   1686   Formula (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1687       EY(i,r)
   1688           =   [1.0 / sum(n,UP_COMM, PSHUP(n,r) * INCPAR(n,r))]
   1689               * [INCPAR(i,r) * [1.0 - ALPHA(i,r)]
   1690                   + sum(n,UP_COMM, PSHUP(n,r) * INCPAR(n,r) * ALPHA(n,r))]
   1691           + [ALPHA(i,r) - sum(n,UP_COMM, PSHUP(n,r) * ALPHA(n,r))];
   1692    
   1693   Coefficient (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,k,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1694       EP(i,k,r)
   1695       # uncomp. elast. of private hhld demand for i wrt price of k in r (HT F5) #;
   1696   Formula (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,k,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1697       EP(i,k,r) = 0;
   1698   Formula (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,k,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1699       EP(i,k,r) = [APE(i,k,r) - EY(i,r)] * PSHUP(k,r);
   1700    
   1701   Equation PRIVDMNDS
   1702   # private consumption demands for composite commodities (HT 46) #
   1703   (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1704       qp(i,r) - pop(r)
   1705           = sum(k,UP_COMM, EP(i,k,r) * pp(k,r)) + EY(i,r) * [yp(r) - pop(r)];
   1706   !<
   1707       Private consumption demands for composite commodities.  Demand system is
   1708       on a per capita basis.  Here, yp(r) - pop(r) is % change in per capita
   1709       income.  (HT 46)
   1710   >!
   1711    
   1712   Equation PHHLDINDEX
   1713   # price index for private consumption expenditure #
   1714   (all,r,REG)
   1715       ppriv(r) = sum(i,UP_COMM, PSHUP(i,r) * pp(i,r));
   1716    
   1717   Equation PRIVATEU
   1718   # computation of utility from private consumption in r (HT 45) #
   1719   (all,r,REG)
   1720       yp(r) - pop(r) = ppriv(r) + UELASPRIV(r) * up(r);
   1721   !<
   1722       This equation determines private consumption utility for a representative
   1723       household in region r, based on the per capita private expenditure
   1724       function.  (HT 45)
   1725   >!
   1726    
   1727   Coefficient (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1728       XWCONSHR(i,r)
   1729       # expansion-parameter-weighted consumption share #;
   1730   Formula (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1731       XWCONSHR(i,r) = PSHUP(i,r) * INCPAR(i,r) / UELASPRIV(r);
   1732    
   1733   Equation UTILELASPRIV
   1734   # elasticity of expenditure wrt utility from private consumption #
   1735   (all,r,REG)
   1736       uepriv(r)
   1737           = sum(i,UP_COMM, XWCONSHR(i,r) * [pp(i,r) + qp(i,r) - yp(r)]);
   1738    
   1739    
   1740   !<
   1741       --------
   1742       3. Firms
   1743       --------
   1744    
   1745       To implement the production system, we define a set "SUBF_COMM" of
   1746       subproducts, corresponding to the various composites of TP-16, the
   1747       value-added-energy composite, the capital-energy composite, and so on
   1748       (we call them "subproducts" not "composites" to avoid confusion with the
   1749       domestic-import and import-import composites).  We include subproducts
   1750       with endowments and tradables in a set "FIRM_COMM" of commodities
   1751       demanded by firms.
   1752    
   1753    
   1754       Set structure
   1755       -------------
   1756    
   1757       |--------------------------------------------------|
   1758       |                    FIRM_COMM                     |
   1759       |--------------------------------------------------|
   1760       |              DEMD_COMM               | SUBF_COMM |
   1761       |--------------------------------------|-----------|
   1762       | ENDW_COMM |       TRAD_COMM          |
   1763       |---------------------------------------
   1764    
   1765    
   1766       Production structure
   1767       --------------------
   1768    
   1769                                        qo(j,r)  [ao(j,r)]     TOTAL OUTPUT NEST
   1770                                        /\
   1771                                       /  \  <----- CES
   1772                                      /    \
   1773                                     /      \
   1774                                    /        \
   1775                       endowment-energy       non-energy inputs
   1776   Val.-add.-en. nest    /| \                                 /\
   1777       CES ----->       / |  \                               /  \  <------ CES
   1778                       /  |   \                             /    \
   1779                      /   |    \                           /      \
   1780                     /    |     \                         /        \
   1781                  Land  Labor  K-E subproduct         Domestic     Foreign
   1782                                 /\
   1783                                /  \
   1784                               /    \                  Capital-energy nest
   1785                              /      \     <--------- CES (subst. el. ELFKEN)
   1786                             /        \
   1787                            /          \
   1788                           /            \
   1789                          /              \
   1790                         K             energy subproduct
   1791                                                   /\         Energy nest
   1792                                                  /  \ <--- CES (subst. el. ELFENY)
   1793                                                 /    \
   1794                                                /      \
   1795                                               /        \
   1796                                              /          \
   1797                                         electricity  non-electr. energy
   1798                                                           /\
   1799       Non-electricity energy nest                        /  \
   1800       CES (subst. el. ELFNELY)  ---------------->       /    \
   1801                                                        /      \
   1802                                                       /        \
   1803                                              non-coal energy   coal
   1804                                                   /\
   1805       Non-coal energy nest     ------------>     /  \
   1806       CES (subst. el. ELFNCOAL)                 /    \
   1807                                                /      \
   1808                                               /        \
   1809                                              /          \
   1810                                    crude oil, gas, petr. products
   1811    
   1812    
   1813    
   1814       3-0. Module-Specific Variables
   1815       3-1. Factor Employment Taxation
   1816       3-2. Composite Intermediates Nest
   1817       3-3. Notational Links
   1818       3-4. Input-Augmenting Technological Change
   1819       3-5. Non-Coal Energy Nest
   1820       3-6. Non-Electricity Energy Nest
   1821       3-7. Energy Nest
   1822       3-8. Capital-Energy Nest
   1823       3-9. Value-Added-Energy Nest
   1824       3-10. Top of the Production Structure
   1825       3-11. Output Taxation
   1826   >!
   1827    
   1828    
   1829   !<
   1830       3-0. Module-Specific Variables
   1831       ------------------------------
   1832    
   1833       only used in this Firms Module or the Summary Indices or Welfare
   1834       appendices
   1835   >!
   1836    
   1837   Set
   1838       SUBF_COMM # subproducts in demand by firms #
   1839       (vaen, ken, eny, nely, ncoal);
   1840   Set
   1841       FIRM_COMM # commodities demanded by firms # = DEMD_COMM union SUBF_COMM;
   1842    
   1843   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1844       pft(i,j,r) # firms' price for commodity i for use by j in r #;
   1845   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1846       qft(i,j,r) # demand for commodity i for use by j in region r #;
   1847   Variable (all,i,FIRM_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1848       pf(i,j,r) # firms' price for commodity i for use by j in r #;
   1849   Variable (all,i,FIRM_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1850       qf(i,j,r) # demand for commodity i for use by j in r #;
   1851   Variable (all,i,FIRM_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1852       af(i,j,r) # factor i augmenting tech change in sector j of r #;
   1853   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   1854       ams(i,r,s) # import i from region r augmenting tech change in region s #;
   1855    
   1856   Coefficient (all,i,FIRM_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1857       VFA(i,j,r) # producer expend. on i by j in r valued at agent's prices #;
   1858    
   1859   Coefficient (all,i,SUBF_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1860       VFAS(i,j,r) # producer expend. on i by j in r valued at agent's prices #;
   1861    
   1862    
   1863   !<
   1864       3-1. Factor Employment Taxation
   1865       -------------------------------
   1866   >!
   1867    
   1868   Variable (all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1869       tf(i,j,r) # tax on primary factor i used by j in region r #;
   1870   Equation MPFACTPRICE # eq'n links domestic and firm demand prices (HT 16) #
   1871   (all,i,ENDWM_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1872       pfe(i,j,r) = tf(i,j,r) + pm(i,r);
   1873    
   1874   Equation SPFACTPRICE # eq'n links domestic and firm demand prices (HT 17) #
   1875   (all,i,ENDWS_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1876       pfe(i,j,r) = tf(i,j,r) + pmes(i,j,r);
   1877    
   1878   Equation TFURATIO
   1879   # change in ratio of tax payments on factor usage to regional income #
   1880   (all,r,REG)
   1881       100.0 * INCOME(r) * del_taxrfu(r) + TFU(r) * y(r)
   1882           = sum(i,ENDWM_COMM, sum(j,PROD_COMM, VFAD(i,j,r) * tf(i,j,r)))
   1883           + sum(i,ENDWM_COMM, sum(j,PROD_COMM,
   1884               ETAX(i,j,r) * [pm(i,r) + qfe(i,j,r)]))
   1885           + sum(i,ENDWS_COMM, sum(j,PROD_COMM, VFAD(i,j,r) * tf(i,j,r)))
   1886           + sum(i,ENDWS_COMM, sum(j,PROD_COMM,
   1887               ETAX(i,j,r) * [pmes(i,j,r) + qfe(i,j,r)]));
   1888    
   1889    
   1890   !<
   1891       3-2. Composite Intermediates Nest
   1892       ---------------------------------
   1893   >!
   1894    
   1895   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) default 1;
   1896   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1897       SHVDFANC(i,j,r)
   1898       # share of carbon-tax-excl. value of domestic i for use by j in region r #;
   1899   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1900       SHVDFANC(i,j,r) = VDFANC(i,j,r) / VDFA(i,j,r);
   1901   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) off;
   1902    
   1903   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) default 0;
   1904   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1905       CO2DFVDFA(i,j,r)
   1906       # emissions intensity of domestic i for use by j in region r #;
   1907   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1908       CO2DFVDFA(i,j,r) = CO2DF(i,j,r) / VDFA(i,j,r);
   1909   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) off;
   1910    
   1911   Equation DMNDDPRICE
   1912   # taxation of intermediate usage of domestic product #
   1913   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1914       pfd(i,j,r) = SHVDFANC(i,j,r) * (pm(i,r) + tfd(i,j,r))
   1915           + 100.0 * CO2DFVDFA(i,j,r) * NCTAXB(REGTOBLOC(r));
   1916    
   1917   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) default 1;
   1918   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1919       SHVIFANC(i,j,r)
   1920       # share of carbon-tax-excl. value of imported i for use by j in region r #;
   1921   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1922       SHVIFANC(i,j,r) = VIFANC(i,j,r) / VIFA(i,j,r);
   1923   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) off;
   1924    
   1925   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) default 0;
   1926   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1927       CO2IFVIFA(i,j,r)
   1928       # emissions intensity of imported i for use by j in region r #;
   1929   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1930       CO2IFVIFA(i,j,r) = CO2IF(i,j,r) / VIFA(i,j,r);
   1931    
   1932    
   1933   Equation DMNDIPRICES
   1934   # taxation of intermediate usage of imports #
   1935   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1936       pfm(i,j,r) = SHVIFANC(i,j,r) * (pim(i,r) + tfm(i,j,r))
   1937           + 100.0 * CO2IFVIFA(i,j,r) * NCTAXB(REGTOBLOC(r));
   1938    
   1939   Equation TIURATIO
   1940   # change in ratio of tax payments on intermediate goods to regional income #
   1941   (all,r,REG)
   1942       100.0 * INCOME(r) * del_taxriu(r) + TIU(r) * y(r)
   1943           = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(j,PROD_COMM,
   1944               VDFANC(i,j,r) * tfd(i,j,r)
   1945                   + DFTAX(i,j,r) * [pm(i,r) + qfd(i,j,r)]))
   1946           + sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(j,PROD_COMM,
   1947               VIFANC(i,j,r) * tfm(i,j,r)
   1948                   + IFTAX(i,j,r) * [pim(i,r) + qfm(i,j,r)]));
   1949    
   1950   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   1951       FMSHR(i,j,s) # share of firms' imports in dom. composite, agent's prices #;
   1952   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   1953       FMSHR(i,j,s) = VIFA(i,j,s) / VFAD(i,j,s);
   1954   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) off;
   1955   Equation ICOMPRICE
   1956   # industry price for composite commodities (HT 30) #
   1957   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1958       pft(i,j,r) = FMSHR(i,j,r) * pfm(i,j,r) + [1 - FMSHR(i,j,r)] * pfd(i,j,r);
   1959    
   1960   Equation INDIMP
   1961   # industry j demands for composite import i (HT 31) #
   1962   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   1963       qfm(i,j,s) = qft(i,j,s) - ESUBD(i) * [pfm(i,j,s) - pft(i,j,s)];
   1964    
   1965   Equation INDDOM
   1966   # industry j demands for domestic good i (HT 32) #
   1967   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   1968       qfd(i,j,s) = qft(i,j,s) - ESUBD(i) * [pfd(i,j,s) - pft(i,j,s)];
   1969    
   1970    
   1971   !<
   1972       3-3. Notational Links
   1973       ---------------------
   1974   >!
   1975    
   1976   Formula (all,i,DEMD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1977       VFA(i,j,r) = VFAD(i,j,r);
   1978    
   1979   Equation PFEEQ # Input endowment prices into the production system. #
   1980   (all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1981       pf(i,j,r) = pfe(i,j,r);
   1982    
   1983   Equation PFTEQ # Input tradables prices into the production system. #
   1984   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1985       pf(i,j,r) = pft(i,j,r);
   1986    
   1987   Equation QFEEQ # Output endowment quantities from the production system. #
   1988   (all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1989       qfe(i,j,r) = qf(i,j,r);
   1990    
   1991   Equation QFTEQ # Output tradables quantities from the production system. #
   1992   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   1993       qft(i,j,r) = qf(i,j,r);
   1994    
   1995    
   1996   !<
   1997       3-4. Input-Augmenting Technological Change
   1998       ------------------------------------------
   1999   >!
   2000    
   2001   Variable (all,i,FIRM_COMM)
   2002       afcom(i) # factor i augmenting tech change, worldwide #;
   2003   Variable (all,j,PROD_COMM)
   2004       afsec(j) # factor augmenting tech change in sector j, worldwide #;
   2005   Variable (all,r,REG)
   2006       afreg(r) # factor augmenting tech change in region r #;
   2007   Variable (all,i,FIRM_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2008       afall(i,j,r) # input i augmenting tech change in sector j of r #;
   2009    
   2010   Equation AFWORLD
   2011   # sector/region specific rate of factor i augmenting tech change #
   2012   (all,i,FIRM_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2013       af(i,j,r) = afcom(i) + afsec(j) + afreg(r) + afall(i,j,r);
   2014    
   2015    
   2016   !<
   2017       3-5. Non-Coal Energy Nest
   2018       -------------------------
   2019   >!
   2020    
   2021   Set
   2022       NCOAL_FCOMM # inputs into non-coal energy subproduction #
   2023       (oil, gas, oil_pcts);
   2024   Subset
   2025       NCOAL_FCOMM is subset of FIRM_COMM;
   2026    
   2027   Formula (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2028       VFAS("ncoal",j,r) = sum(i,NCOAL_FCOMM, VFA(i,j,r));
   2029   Formula (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2030       VFA("ncoal",j,r) = VFAS("ncoal",j,r);
   2031    
   2032   Coefficient
   2033       FSIZE_NCOAL # size of NCOAL_FCOMM set #;
   2034   Formula
   2035       FSIZE_NCOAL = sum(i,NCOAL_FCOMM, 1);
   2036    
   2037   Coefficient (all,i,NCOAL_FCOMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2038       FSHNCOAL(i,j,r)
   2039       # share of i in cost to j of non-coal energy subproduct #;
   2040   Formula (all,i,NCOAL_FCOMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG: VFAS("ncoal",j,r) = 0)
   2041       FSHNCOAL(i,j,r) = 1.0 / FSIZE_NCOAL;
   2042   Formula (all,i,NCOAL_FCOMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG: VFAS("ncoal",j,r) > 0)
   2043       FSHNCOAL(i,j,r) = VFA(i,j,r) / VFAS("ncoal",j,r);
   2044    
   2045   Equation NCOALFPRICE # price of non-coal energy #
   2046   (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2047       pf("ncoal",j,r)
   2048           = sum(k,NCOAL_FCOMM, FSHNCOAL(k,j,r) * [pf(k,j,r) - af(k,j,r)]);
   2049    
   2050   Coefficient (parameter) (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2051       ELFNCOAL(j,r)
   2052       # elasticity of substitution in non-coal energy subproduction #;
   2053   Read
   2054       ELFNCOAL from file GTAPPARM header "EFNC";
   2055    
   2056   Equation NCOALFDEMAND
   2057   # demand for inputs into non-coal energy subproduction #
   2058   (all,i,NCOAL_FCOMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2059       qf(i,j,r) = -af(i,j,r) + qf("ncoal",j,r)
   2060           - ELFNCOAL(j,r) * [pf(i,j,r) - af(i,j,r) - pf("ncoal",j,r)];
   2061    
   2062    
   2063   !<
   2064       3-6. Non-Electricity Energy Nest
   2065       --------------------------------
   2066   >!
   2067    
   2068   Set
   2069       NELY_FCOMM # inputs into non-electricity energy subproduction #
   2070       (coal, ncoal);
   2071   Subset
   2072       NELY_FCOMM is subset of FIRM_COMM;
   2073    
   2074   Formula (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2075       VFAS("nely",j,r) = sum(i,NELY_FCOMM, VFA(i,j,r));
   2076   Formula (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2077       VFA("nely",j,r) = VFAS("nely",j,r);
   2078    
   2079   Coefficient
   2080       FSIZE_NELY # size of NELY_FCOMM set #;
   2081   Formula
   2082       FSIZE_NELY = sum(i,NELY_FCOMM, 1);
   2083    
   2084   Coefficient (all,i,NELY_FCOMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2085       FSHNELY(i,j,r)
   2086       # share of i in cost to j of non-electricity energy subproduct #;
   2087   Formula (all,i,NELY_FCOMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG: VFAS("nely",j,r) = 0)
   2088       FSHNELY(i,j,r) = 1.0 / FSIZE_NELY;
   2089   Formula (all,i,NELY_FCOMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG: VFAS("nely",j,r) > 0)
   2090       FSHNELY(i,j,r) = VFA(i,j,r) / VFAS("nely",j,r);
   2091    
   2092   Equation NELYFPRICE # price of non-electricity energy subproduct #
   2093   (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2094       pf("nely",j,r) =
   2095           sum(k,NELY_FCOMM, FSHNELY(k,j,r) * [pf(k,j,r) - af(k,j,r)]);
   2096    
   2097   Coefficient (parameter) (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2098       ELFNELY(j,r)
   2099       # elasticity of substitution in non-electricity energy subproduction #;
   2100   Read
   2101       ELFNELY from file GTAPPARM header "EFNL";
   2102    
   2103   Equation NELYFDEMAND
   2104   # demand for inputs into non-electricity energy subproduction #
   2105   (all,i,NELY_FCOMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2106       qf(i,j,r) = -af(i,j,r) + qf("nely",j,r)
   2107           - ELFNELY(j,r) * [pf(i,j,r) - af(i,j,r) - pf("nely",j,r)];
   2108    
   2109    
   2110   !<
   2111       3-7. Energy Nest
   2112       ----------------
   2113   >!
   2114    
   2115   Set
   2116       ENY_FCOMM # inputs into energy subproduction # (electricity, nely);
   2117   Subset
   2118       ENY_FCOMM is subset of FIRM_COMM;
   2119    
   2120   Coefficient
   2121       FSIZE_ENY # size of ENY_FCOMM set #;
   2122   Formula
   2123       FSIZE_ENY = sum(i,ENY_FCOMM, 1);
   2124    
   2125   Formula (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2126       VFAS("eny",j,r) = sum(i,ENY_FCOMM, VFA(i,j,r));
   2127   Formula (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2128       VFA("eny",j,r) = VFAS("eny",j,r);
   2129    
   2130   Coefficient (all,i,ENY_FCOMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2131       FSHENY(i,j,r) # share of i in cost to j of energy subproduct #;
   2132   Formula (all,i,ENY_FCOMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG: VFAS("eny",j,r) = 0)
   2133       FSHENY(i,j,r) = 1.0 / FSIZE_ENY;
   2134   Formula (all,i,ENY_FCOMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG: VFAS("eny",j,r) > 0)
   2135       FSHENY(i,j,r) = VFA(i,j,r) / VFAS("eny",j,r);
   2136    
   2137   Equation ENYFPRICE # price of energy subproduct #
   2138   (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2139       pf("eny",j,r) = sum(k,ENY_FCOMM, FSHENY(k,j,r) * [pf(k,j,r) - af(k,j,r)]);
   2140    
   2141   Coefficient (parameter) (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2142       ELFENY(j,r) # elasticity of substitution in energy subproduction #;
   2143   Read
   2144       ELFENY from file GTAPPARM header "EFEN";
   2145    
   2146   Equation ENYFDEMAND # demand for inputs into energy subproduction #
   2147   (all,i,ENY_FCOMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2148       qf(i,j,r) = -af(i,j,r) + qf("eny",j,r)
   2149           - ELFENY(j,r) * [pf(i,j,r) - af(i,j,r) - pf("eny",j,r)];
   2150    
   2151    
   2152   !<
   2153       3-8. Capital-Energy Nest
   2154       ------------------------
   2155   >!
   2156    
   2157   Set
   2158       KEN_FCOMM # inputs into capital-energy subproduction # (capital, eny);
   2159   Subset
   2160       KEN_FCOMM is subset of FIRM_COMM;
   2161    
   2162   Formula (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2163       VFAS("ken",j,r) = sum(i,KEN_FCOMM, VFA(i,j,r));
   2164   Formula (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2165       VFA("ken",j,r) = VFAS("ken",j,r);
   2166    
   2167   Coefficient
   2168       FSIZE_KEN # size of KEN_FCOMM set #;
   2169   Formula
   2170       FSIZE_KEN = sum(i,KEN_FCOMM, 1);
   2171    
   2172   Coefficient (all,i,KEN_FCOMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2173       FSHKEN(i,j,r) # share of i in cost to j of capital-energy subproduct #;
   2174   Formula (all,i,KEN_FCOMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG: VFAS("ken",j,r) = 0)
   2175       FSHKEN(i,j,r) = 1.0 / FSIZE_KEN;
   2176   Formula (all,i,KEN_FCOMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG: VFAS("ken",j,r) > 0)
   2177       FSHKEN(i,j,r) = VFA(i,j,r) / VFAS("ken",j,r);
   2178    
   2179   Equation KENFPRICE # price of capital-energy subproduct #
   2180   (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2181       pf("ken",j,r)
   2182           = sum(k,KEN_FCOMM, FSHKEN(k,j,r) * [pf(k,j,r) - af(k,j,r)]);
   2183    
   2184   Coefficient (parameter) (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2185       ELFKEN(j,r)
   2186       # elasticity of substitution in capital-energy subproduction #;
   2187   Read
   2188       ELFKEN from file GTAPPARM header "EFKE";
   2189    
   2190   Equation KENFDEMAND # demand for inputs into capital-energy subproduction #
   2191   (all,i,KEN_FCOMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2192       qf(i,j,r)= -af(i,j,r) + qf("ken",j,r)
   2193           - ELFKEN(j,r) * [pf(i,j,r) - af(i,j,r) - pf("ken",j,r)];
   2194    
   2195    
   2196   !<
   2197       3-9. Value-Added-Energy Nest
   2198       ----------------------------
   2199   >!
   2200    
   2201   Set KEN # capital-energy subproduction # (ken);
   2202    
   2203   Set
   2204       VAEN_FCOMM # inputs into value-added-energy subproduction #
   2205       = ENDWNA_COMM + KEN;
   2206    
   2207   Subset
   2208       VAEN_FCOMM is subset of FIRM_COMM;
   2209    
   2210   Formula (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2211       VFAS("vaen",j,r) = sum(i,VAEN_FCOMM, VFA(i,j,r));
   2212   Formula (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2213       VFA("vaen",j,r) = VFAS("vaen",j,r);
   2214    
   2215   Coefficient
   2216       FSIZE_VAEN # size of VAEN_FCOMM set #;
   2217   Formula
   2218       FSIZE_VAEN = sum(i,VAEN_FCOMM, 1);
   2219    
   2220   Coefficient (all,i,VAEN_FCOMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2221       FSHVAEN(i,j,r)
   2222       # share of i in cost to j of value-added-energy subproduct #;
   2223   Formula (all,i,VAEN_FCOMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG: VFAS("vaen",j,r) = 0)
   2224       FSHVAEN(i,j,r) = 1.0 / FSIZE_VAEN;
   2225   Formula (all,i,VAEN_FCOMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG: VFAS("vaen",j,r) > 0)
   2226       FSHVAEN(i,j,r) = VFA(i,j,r) / VFAS("vaen",j,r);
   2227    
   2228   Equation VAENFPRICE # price of value-added-energy subproduct #
   2229   (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2230       pf("vaen",j,r)
   2231           = sum(k,VAEN_FCOMM, FSHVAEN(k,j,r) * [pf(k,j,r) - af(k,j,r)]);
   2232    
   2233   Coefficient (parameter) (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2234       ELFVAEN(j,r)
   2235       # elasticity of substitution in value-added-energy subproduction #;
   2236   Read
   2237       ELFVAEN from file GTAPPARM header "EFVE";
   2238    
   2239   Equation VAENFDEMAND
   2240   # demand for inputs into value-added-energy subproduction #
   2241   (all,i,VAEN_FCOMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2242       qf(i,j,r) = -af(i,j,r) + qf("vaen",j,r)
   2243           - ELFVAEN(j,r) * [pf(i,j,r) - af(i,j,r) - pf("vaen",j,r)];
   2244    
   2245    
   2246   !<
   2247       3-10. Top of the Production Structure
   2248       -------------------------------------
   2249   >!
   2250    
   2251   Set NENY_FCOMM # inputs into non-energy subproduction # = TRAD_COMM - EGY_COMM;
   2252    
   2253   Set VAEN # value-added-energy subproduction # (vaen);
   2254    
   2255   Set
   2256       OUT_COMM # inputs into top of production structure # = NENY_FCOMM + VAEN;
   2257    
   2258   Subset
   2259       OUT_COMM is subset of FIRM_COMM;
   2260    
   2261   Variable (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2262       ao(j,r) # output augmenting technical change in sector j of r #;
   2263   Variable (all,j,PROD_COMM)
   2264       aosec(j) # output augmenting tech change of sector j, worldwide #;
   2265   Variable (all,r,REG)
   2266       aoreg(r) # output augmetning tech change in region r #;
   2267   Variable (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2268       aoall(j,r) # output augmenting technical change in sector j of r #;
   2269   Equation AOWORLD
   2270   # sector/region specific average rate of output augmenting tech change #
   2271   (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2272       ao(j,r) = aosec(j) + aoreg(r) + aoall(j,r);
   2273    
   2274   Coefficient (Parameter)(all,j,PROD_COMM)
   2275       ESUBT(j) # elasticity of substitution at top of production structure #;
   2276   Read
   2277       ESUBT from file GTAPPARM header "ESBT";
   2278    
   2279   Variable (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2280       profitslack(j,r) # slack variable in the zero profit equation #;
   2281   !<
   2282       This is exogenous, unless the user wishes to specify output in a given
   2283       region exogenously.
   2284   >!
   2285    
   2286   Coefficient (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2287       VFATOT(j,r) # total cost of inputs into j in r #;
   2288   Formula (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2289       VFATOT(j,r) = sum(i,OUT_COMM, VFA(i,j,r));
   2290    
   2291   Coefficient
   2292       FSIZE_OUT # size of OUT_COMM set #;
   2293   Formula
   2294       FSIZE_OUT = sum(i,OUT_COMM, 1);
   2295    
   2296   Coefficient (all,i,OUT_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2297       FSHOUT(i,j,r) # share of i in total costs of j in r #;
   2298   Formula (all,i,OUT_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG: VFATOT(j,r) = 0.0)
   2299       FSHOUT(i,j,r) = 1.0 / FSIZE_OUT;
   2300   Formula (all,i,OUT_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG: VFATOT(j,r) > 0.0)
   2301       FSHOUT(i,j,r) = VFA(i,j,r) / VFATOT(j,r);
   2302    
   2303   Equation ZEROPROFITS # industry zero pure profits condition #
   2304   (all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2305       ps(j,r) + ao(j,r)
   2306           = sum(i,OUT_COMM, FSHOUT(i,j,r) * [pf(i,j,r) - af(i,j,r)])
   2307               + profitslack(j,r);
   2308   !<
   2309       Industry zero pure profits condition (HT 6).  This condition permits us to
   2310       determine the endogenous output level for each of the non-endowment
   2311       sectors, excepting when profitslack is itself endogenous.  The level of
   2312       activity in the endowment sectors is exogenously determined.
   2313   >!
   2314    
   2315   Equation OUTFDEMAND
   2316   # sector demands for factor-energy subproduct and intermediate inputs #
   2317   (all,i,OUT_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2318       qf(i,j,r)= -af(i,j,r) + qo(j,r) - ao(j,r)
   2319           - ESUBT(j) * [pf(i,j,r) - af(i,j,r) - ps(j,r) - ao(j,r)];
   2320    
   2321    
   2322   !<
   2323       3-11. Output Taxation
   2324       ---------------------
   2325   >!
   2326    
   2327   Equation OUTPUTPRICES
   2328   # Eq'n links pre- and post-tax supply prices for all industries.  (HT 15) #
   2329   (all,i,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2330       ps(i,r) = to(i,r) + pm(i,r);
   2331   !<
   2332       This equation links pre- and post-tax supply prices for all industries.
   2333       This captures the effect of output taxes.  TO(i,r) < 1 in the case of a
   2334       tax.  (HT 15)
   2335   >!
   2336    
   2337   Equation TOUTRATIO
   2338   # change in ratio of output tax payments to regional income #
   2339   (all,r,REG)
   2340       100.0 * INCOME(r) * del_taxrout(r) + TOUT(r) * y(r)
   2341           = sum(i,PROD_COMM,
   2342               VOA(i,r) * [-to(i,r)] + PTAX(i,r) * [pm(i,r) + qo(i,r)]);
   2343    
   2344    
   2345   !<
   2346       ---------------------------------------
   2347       4. Investment, Global Bank, and Savings
   2348       ---------------------------------------
   2349    
   2350       Capital stock and rate of return equations follow.  They correspond to the
   2351       Investment Equations of Table 8 in Hertel and Tsigas.
   2352    
   2353       4-0. Module-Specific Variables
   2354       4-1. Equations of Notational Convenience
   2355       4-2. Rate of Return Equations
   2356       4-3. Capital Accumulation
   2357       4-4. Global Bank
   2358       4-5. Price Index of Aggregate Global Composite Capital Goods
   2359       4-6. Price of Saving
   2360   >!
   2361    
   2362    
   2363   !<
   2364       4-0. Module-Specific Variables
   2365       ------------------------------
   2366    
   2367       only used in this Investment, Global Bank and Savings module
   2368   >!
   2369    
   2370   Variable (all,r,REG)
   2371       rental(r) # rental rate on capital = ps("capital",r) #;
   2372   Variable (all,r,REG)
   2373       ke(r) # end-of-period capital stock in r #;
   2374   Variable (all,r,REG)
   2375       rore(r) # expected net rate of return on capital stock in r #;
   2376   Variable (all,r,REG)
   2377       rorc(r) # current net rate of return on capital stock in r #;
   2378   Variable (all,r,REG)
   2379       qcgds(r) # output of capital goods sector = qo("cgds",r) #;
   2380    
   2381    
   2382   !<
   2383       4-1. Equations of Notational Convenience
   2384       ----------------------------------------
   2385   >!
   2386    
   2387   Variable (all,r,REG)
   2388       ksvces(r) # capital services = qo("capital",r) #;
   2389   Equation KAPSVCES
   2390   # eq'n defines a variable for capital services (HT 52) #
   2391   (all,r,REG)
   2392       ksvces(r)
   2393           = sum(h,ENDWC_COMM, [VOA(h,r) / sum(k,ENDWC_COMM, VOA(k,r))] * qo(h,r));
   2394   !<
   2395       This equation defines a variable for capital services, for convenience.
   2396       (There is really only one capital services item.) (HT 52)
   2397   >!
   2398    
   2399   Equation KAPRENTAL
   2400   # eq'n defines a variable for capital rental rate (HT 53) #
   2401   (all,r,REG)
   2402       rental(r)
   2403           = sum(h,ENDWC_COMM, [VOA(h,r) / sum(k,ENDWC_COMM, VOA(k,r))] * ps(h,r));
   2404    
   2405   Equation CAPGOODS
   2406   # eq'n defines a variable for gross investment (HT 54) #
   2407   (all,r,REG)
   2408       qcgds(r)
   2409           = sum(h,CGDS_COMM, [VOA(h,r) / REGINV(r)] * qo(h,r));
   2410   !<
   2411       This equation defines a variable for gross investment, for convenience.
   2412       There is really only one capital goods item.
   2413   >!
   2414    
   2415   Equation PRCGOODS
   2416   # eq'n defines the price of cgds (HT 55) #
   2417   (all,r,REG)
   2418       pcgds(r) = sum(h,CGDS_COMM, [VOA(h,r) / REGINV(r)] * ps(h,r));
   2419    
   2420   Equation KBEGINNING
   2421   # associates change in cap. services w/ change in cap. stock (HT 56) #
   2422   (all,r,REG)
   2423       kb(r) = ksvces(r);
   2424   !<
   2425       This equation associates any change in capital services during the period
   2426       with a change in capital stock.  Full capacity utilization is assumed.
   2427   >!
   2428    
   2429   Coefficient (ge 0)(all,r,REG)
   2430       VKB(r) # value of beginning-of-period capital stock in region r #;
   2431   Update (all,r,REG)
   2432       VKB(r) = pcgds(r) * kb(r);
   2433   Read
   2434       VKB from file GTAPDATA header "VKB";
   2435   !<
   2436       VKB(r) is used only in this sub-module, so its data are read here.  The
   2437       associated variables, pcgds(r) and kb(r), are used across modules, so they
   2438       have been defined as common variables.
   2439   >!
   2440    
   2441   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   2442       INVKERATIO(r)
   2443       # ratio of gross investment to end-of-period capital stock in r #;
   2444   Formula (all,r,REG)
   2445       INVKERATIO(r) = REGINV(r) / [VKB(r) + NETINV(r)];
   2446    
   2447   Equation KEND
   2448   # Ending capital stock equals beginning stock plus net investment.  (HT 10) #
   2449   (all,r,REG)
   2450       ke(r) = INVKERATIO(r) * qcgds(r) + [1.0 - INVKERATIO(r)] * kb(r);
   2451    
   2452    
   2453   !<
   2454       4-2. Rate of Return Equations
   2455       -----------------------------
   2456   >!
   2457    
   2458   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   2459       GRNETRATIO(r) # ratio of GROSS/NET rates of return on capital in r #;
   2460   Formula (all,r,REG)
   2461       GRNETRATIO(r)
   2462           = sum(h,ENDWC_COMM, VOA(h,r))
   2463           / [sum(h,ENDWC_COMM, VOA(h,r)) - VDEP(r)];
   2464   !<
   2465       NOTE: VOA("capital",r) is GROSS returns to capital.
   2466   >!
   2467   Equation RORCURRENT
   2468   # current rate of return on capital in region r (HT 57) #
   2469   (all,r,REG)
   2470       rorc(r) = GRNETRATIO(r) * [rental(r) - pcgds(r)];
   2471    
   2472   Coefficient (parameter)(all,r,REG)
   2473       RORFLEX(r)
   2474       # flexibility of expected net ROR on capital stock in r wrt investment #;
   2475   Read
   2476       RORFLEX from file GTAPPARM header "RFLX";
   2477   !<
   2478       RORFLEX is the flexibility of the expected net rate of return on the
   2479       capital stock, in region r, with respect to investment.  If a region's
   2480       capital stock increases by 1%, then it is expected that the net rate of
   2481       return on capital will decline by RORFLEX %.  A larger absolute value for
   2482       this parameter will reduce the tendency of international investment flows
   2483       to respond to changes in expected rates of return.
   2484   >!
   2485    
   2486   Equation ROREXPECTED
   2487   # expected rate of return depends on the current return and investment (HT 58) #
   2488   (all,r,REG)
   2489       rore(r) = rorc(r) - RORFLEX(r) * [ke(r) - kb(r)];
   2490    
   2491    
   2492   !<
   2493       4-3. Capital Accumulation
   2494       -------------------------
   2495    
   2496       based on the theory laid out in GTAP Technical Paper #7
   2497   >!
   2498    
   2499   Variable (all,i,ENDWC_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2500       EXPAND(i,r) # change in investment levels relative to endowment stock #;
   2501   Equation BALDWIN
   2502   # change in investment levels relative to endowment stock #
   2503   (all,i,ENDWC_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2504       EXPAND(i,r) = qcgds(r) - qo(i,r);
   2505    
   2506    
   2507   !<
   2508       4-4. Global Bank
   2509       ----------------
   2510   >!
   2511    
   2512   Coefficient (integer,parameter)
   2513       RORDELTA
   2514       # binary coefficient to switch mechanism of allocating investment funds #;
   2515   Read
   2516       RORDELTA from file GTAPPARM header "RDLT";
   2517   !<
   2518       RORDELTA is a binary coefficient which determines the mechanism of
   2519       allocating investment funds across regions.  When RORDELTA = 1, investment
   2520       funds are allocated across regions to equate the change in the expected
   2521       rates of return (i.e., rore(r)).  When RORDELTA = 0, investment funds are
   2522       allocated across regions to maintain the existing composition of capital
   2523       stocks.
   2524   >!
   2525    
   2526   Variable
   2527       rorg # global net rate of return on capital stock #;
   2528   Variable (all,r,REG)
   2529       cgdslack(r) # slack variable for qcgds(r) #;
   2530   !<
   2531       This is exogenous, unless the user wishes to exogenously fix the level of
   2532       gross investment in a region, in which case it can be swapped with
   2533       cgdslack.
   2534   >!
   2535   Equation RORGLOBAL
   2536   # either gross investment or expected rate of return in region r (HT 59) #
   2537   (all,r,REG)
   2538       RORDELTA * rore(r)
   2539       + [1 - RORDELTA]
   2540       * [[REGINV(r) / NETINV(r)] * qcgds(r) - [VDEP(r) / NETINV(r)] * kb(r)]
   2541           = RORDELTA * rorg + [1 - RORDELTA] * globalcgds + cgdslack(r);
   2542   !<
   2543       This equation determines either gross investment or the expected rate of
   2544       return in each region, depending on the setting for the binary RORDELTA
   2545       parameter.
   2546   >!
   2547    
   2548   Equation GLOBALINV
   2549   # either expected global rate of return or global net investment (HT 11) #
   2550       RORDELTA * globalcgds + [1 - RORDELTA] * rorg
   2551           = RORDELTA
   2552           * sum(r,REG,
   2553               [REGINV(r) / GLOBINV] * qcgds(r) - [VDEP(r) / GLOBINV] * kb(r))
   2554           + [1 - RORDELTA] * sum(r,REG, [NETINV(r) / GLOBINV] * rore(r));
   2555   !<
   2556       This equation computes either the change in global net investment (when
   2557       RORDELTA = 1), or the change in the expected global rate of return on
   2558       capital (when RORDELTA = 0).
   2559   >!
   2560    
   2561    
   2562   !<
   2563       4-5. Price Index of Aggregate Global Composite Capital Goods
   2564       ------------------------------------------------------------
   2565   >!
   2566    
   2567   Equation PRICGDS
   2568   # eq'n generates a price index for the aggregate global cgds composite (HT 60) #
   2569       pcgdswld = sum(r,REG, [NETINV(r) / GLOBINV] * pcgds(r));
   2570    
   2571    
   2572   !<
   2573       4-6. Price of Saving
   2574       --------------------
   2575   >!
   2576    
   2577   Variable (all,r,REG)
   2578       psaveslack(r) # slack variable for the savings price equation #;
   2579   !<
   2580       This is exogenous under the normal closure.  However, in order to
   2581       replicate simulations from the GTAP book, where there was a single savings
   2582       price, psaveslack may be swapped with psave in order to fix the latter.
   2583       In this case, pcgdswld must be the numeraire so that each region faces the
   2584       same price of savings.
   2585   >!
   2586    
   2587   Equation SAVEPRICE
   2588   # savings price #
   2589   (all,r,REG)
   2590       psave(r)
   2591           = pcgds(r)
   2592           + sum(s,REG, [[NETINV(s) - SAVE(s)] / GLOBINV] * pcgds(s))
   2593           + psaveslack(r);
   2594   !<
   2595       In contrast to the GTAP book, the price of savings is now region-specific
   2596       and it changes at the same rate as the price of regional investment, plus
   2597       an adjustment factor which accounts for the fact that savings and
   2598       investment are not equal at the regional level.
   2599   >!
   2600    
   2601    
   2602   !<
   2603       ----------------------
   2604       5. International Trade
   2605       ----------------------
   2606    
   2607       5-1. Export Prices
   2608       5-2. Demand for Imports
   2609   >!
   2610    
   2611    
   2612   !<
   2613       5-1. Export Prices
   2614       ------------------
   2615   >!
   2616    
   2617   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2618       tx(i,r) # dest.-gen. change in subsidy on exports of i from r #;
   2619   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2620       txs(i,r,s) # dest.-spec. change in subsidy on exports of i from r to s #;
   2621   !<
   2622       The variable txs captures changes in the power of bilateral export taxes.
   2623       However, the presence of a destination-generic export subsidy shift (tx)
   2624       also permits the user to swap a single export tax shock with another
   2625       target variable.  It is most naturally swapped with the variable qo to
   2626       insulate domestic producers from the world market.
   2627   >!
   2628    
   2629   Equation EXPRICES
   2630   # eq'n links agent's and world prices (HT 27) #
   2631   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2632       pfob(i,r,s) = pm(i,r) - tx(i,r) - txs(i,r,s);
   2633    
   2634   Equation TEXPRATIO
   2635   # change in ratio of export tax payments to regional income #
   2636   (all,r,REG)
   2637       100.0 * INCOME(r) * del_taxrexp(r) + TEX(r) * y(r)
   2638           = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(s,REG,
   2639               VXMD(i,r,s) * [-tx(i,r) - txs(i,r,s)]
   2640               + XTAXD(i,r,s) * [pfob(i,r,s) + qxs(i,r,s)]));
   2641    
   2642    
   2643   !<
   2644       5-2. Demand for Imports
   2645       -----------------------
   2646    
   2647       Composite Imports Nest: Table 3 of Hertel and Tsigas
   2648   >!
   2649    
   2650   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   2651       tm(i,s) # source-gen. change in tax on imports of i into s #;
   2652   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2653       tms(i,r,s) # source-spec. change in tax on imports of i from r into s #;
   2654   !<
   2655       The variable tms captures changes in the power of bilateral import taxes.
   2656       However, the presence of a source-generic import tariff shift (tm) also
   2657       permits the user to swap a single import tariff shock with another target
   2658       variable.  In particular, to insulate domestic producers from import price
   2659       changes, it may be swapped with the relative price variable pr -- see
   2660       below.
   2661   >!
   2662    
   2663   Equation MKTPRICES
   2664   # eq'n links domestic and world prices (HT 24) #
   2665   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2666       pms(i,r,s) = tm(i,s) + tms(i,r,s) + pcif(i,r,s);
   2667    
   2668   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2669       MSHRS(i,r,s) # share of imports from r in import bill of s at mkt prices #;
   2670   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2671       MSHRS(i,r,s) = VIMS(i,r,s) / sum(k,REG, VIMS(i,k,s));
   2672   Equation DPRICEIMP
   2673   # price for aggregate imports (HT 28) #
   2674   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   2675       pim(i,s) = sum(k,REG, MSHRS(i,k,s) * [pms(i,k,s) - ams(i,k,s)]);
   2676    
   2677   Variable (orig_level=1.0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2678       pr(i,r) # ratio of domestic to imported prices in r #;
   2679   Equation PRICETGT
   2680   # eq'n defines target price ratio to be attained via the variable levy (HT 25) #
   2681   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   2682       pr(i,s) = pm(i,s) - pim(i,s);
   2683   !<
   2684       This equation defines the target price ratio to be attained via the
   2685       variable levy.  This price ratio is the ratio of domestic to average
   2686       imported goods' price.  Note that the way this price ratio is defined, it
   2687       includes intraregional imports as well.  In most applications, regions
   2688       will represent groups of individual countries.  However, in the case of
   2689       the EU, this is problematic, since recent versions of the database have
   2690       incorporated intra-EU trade flows.  Therefore, when aggregated to the EU
   2691       level, the composite import price includes both intra-EU and outside
   2692       imports.  So some modification is needed to handle the EU case.
   2693   >!
   2694    
   2695   Coefficient (parameter)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   2696       ESUBM(i)
   2697       # region-generic el. of sub. among imports of i in Armington structure #;
   2698   Read
   2699       ESUBM from file GTAPPARM header "ESBM";
   2700    
   2701   Equation IMPORTDEMAND
   2702   # regional demand for disaggregated imported commodities by source (HT 29)  #
   2703   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2704       qxs(i,r,s)
   2705           = -ams(i,r,s) + qim(i,s)
   2706           - ESUBM(i) * [pms(i,r,s) - ams(i,r,s) - pim(i,s)];
   2707    
   2708   Equation TIMPRATIO
   2709   # change in ratio of import tax payments to regional income #
   2710   (all,r,REG)
   2711       100.0 * INCOME(r) * del_taxrimp(r) + TIM(r) * y(r)
   2712           = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(s,REG,
   2713               VIMS(i,s,r) * [tm(i,r) + tms(i,s,r)]
   2714               + MTAX(i,s,r) * [pcif(i,s,r) + qxs(i,s,r)]));
   2715    
   2716    
   2717   !<
   2718       -----------------------------------
   2719       6. International Transport Services
   2720       -----------------------------------
   2721    
   2722       6-0. Module-Specific Variables and Coefficients
   2723       6-1. Demand for Global Transport Services
   2724       6-2. Supply of Transport Services
   2725   >!
   2726    
   2727    
   2728   !<
   2729       6-0. Module-Specific Variables and Coefficients
   2730       -----------------------------------------------
   2731    
   2732       only used in this International Transport Services module
   2733   >!
   2734    
   2735   Variable (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2736       qtmfsd(m,i,r,s) # international usage margin m on i from r to s #;
   2737   !<
   2738       International margin usage, by Margin, Freight, Source, and Destination,
   2739       i.e., the percent change in usage of m in transport of i from r to s.
   2740   >!
   2741   Variable (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2742       atmfsd(m,i,r,s) # tech change in m's shipping of i from region r to s #;
   2743   !<
   2744       Technical progress in shipping by Margin, Freight, Source, and
   2745       Destination.  This is endogenous and driven by the following mode-,
   2746       product-, source-, and destination-specific determinants.
   2747   >!
   2748   Variable (all,m,TRAD_COMM)
   2749       atm(m) # tech change in mode m, worldwide #;
   2750   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   2751       atf(i) # tech change shipping of i, worldwide #;
   2752   Variable (all,r,REG)
   2753       ats(r) # tech change shipping from region r #;
   2754   Variable (all,s,REG)
   2755       atd(s) # tech change shipping to s #;
   2756   Variable (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2757       atall(m,i,r,s) # tech change in m's shipping of i from region r to s #;
   2758   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2759       ptrans(i,r,s) # cost index for international transport of i from r to s #;
   2760   !<
   2761       average cost index for margin services used in getting i from r to s
   2762   >!
   2763   Variable (all,m,MARG_COMM)
   2764       qtm(m) # global margin usage #;
   2765   Variable (all,m,MARG_COMM)
   2766       pt(m) # price of composite margins services, type #;
   2767   !<
   2768       price index for commodity m in margin services usage
   2769   >!
   2770    
   2771   Coefficient (ge 0) (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2772       VTMFSD(m,i,r,s)
   2773       # int'l margin usage, by margin, freight, source, and destination #;
   2774   Update (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2775       VTMFSD(m,i,r,s) = pt(m) * qtmfsd(m,i,r,s);
   2776   Read
   2777       VTMFSD from file GTAPDATA header "VTWR";
   2778    
   2779   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2780       VTFSD(i,r,s) # aggregate value of svces in the shipment of i from r to s #;
   2781   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2782       VTFSD(i,r,s) = sum(m,MARG_COMM, VTMFSD(m,i,r,s));
   2783   !<
   2784       In a balanced data base, (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG),
   2785       VIWS(i,r,s) = VXWD(i,r,s) + VTFSD(i,r,s).
   2786   >!
   2787    
   2788   Coefficient (all,m,MARG_COMM)
   2789       VTMUSE(m) # international margin services usage, by type #;
   2790   Formula (all,m,MARG_COMM)
   2791       VTMUSE(m) = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(r,REG, sum(s,REG, VTMFSD(m,i,r,s))));
   2792    
   2793   Coefficient (all,m,MARG_COMM)
   2794       VTMPROV(m) # international margin services provision #;
   2795   Formula (all,m,MARG_COMM)
   2796       VTMPROV(m) = sum(r,REG, VST(m,r));
   2797   !<
   2798       In a balanced data base, VTMPROV = VTMUSE.
   2799   >!
   2800    
   2801   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   2802       VTRPROV(r) # international margin supply, by region #;
   2803   Formula (all,r,REG)
   2804       VTRPROV(r) = sum(m,MARG_COMM, VST(m,r));
   2805    
   2806   Coefficient
   2807       VT # international margin supply #;
   2808   Formula
   2809       VT = sum(m,MARG_COMM, sum(r,REG, VST(m,r)));
   2810    
   2811    
   2812   !<
   2813       6-1. Demand for Global Transport Services
   2814       -----------------------------------------
   2815   >!
   2816    
   2817   Equation QTRANS_MFSD
   2818   # bilateral demand for transport services  #
   2819   (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2820       qtmfsd(m,i,r,s) = qxs(i,r,s) - atmfsd(m,i,r,s);
   2821   !<
   2822       This equation computes the bilateral demand for international
   2823       transportation services.  It reflects the fact that the demand for
   2824       services along any particular route is proportional to the quantity of
   2825       merchandise shipped [i.e., QXS(i,r,s)].  It is here that we introduce the
   2826       potential for input-augmenting tech change, atmfsd(m,i,r,s), which is
   2827       commodity- and route-specific.  Thus, in the levels:
   2828               ATMFSD(m,i,r,s) * QTMFSD(m,i,r,s) = QXS(i,r,s)
   2829       where QTMFSD is the amount of composite margins services m used along this
   2830       route.  Technological improvements are reflected by atmfsd(i,r,s) > 0, and
   2831       these reduce the margins services required for this i,r,s triplet.  Tech.
   2832       change also dampens the cost of shipping, thereby lowering the CIF price
   2833       implied by a given FOB value (see 6-2).
   2834   >!
   2835    
   2836   Coefficient (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2837       VTMUSESHR(m,i,r,s) # share of i,r,s usage in global demand for m #;
   2838   Formula (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2839       VTMUSESHR(m,i,r,s) = VTFSD(i,r,s) / VT;
   2840   Formula
   2841       (all,m,MARG_COMM: VTMUSE(m) <> 0.0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2842       VTMUSESHR(m,i,r,s) = VTMFSD(m,i,r,s) / VTMUSE(m);
   2843    
   2844   Equation TRANS_DEMAND
   2845   # global demand for margin m #
   2846   (all,m,MARG_COMM)
   2847       qtm(m)
   2848           = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(r,REG, sum(s,REG,
   2849             VTMUSESHR(m,i,r,s) * qtmfsd(m,i,r,s))));
   2850    
   2851    
   2852   !<
   2853       6-2. Supply of Transport Services
   2854       ---------------------------------
   2855   >!
   2856    
   2857   Coefficient (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2858       VTSUPPSHR(m,r) # share of region r in global supply of margin m #;
   2859   Formula (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2860       VTSUPPSHR(m,r) = VTRPROV(r) / VT;
   2861   Formula (all,m,MARG_COMM: VTMPROV(m) <> 0.0)(all,r,REG)
   2862       VTSUPPSHR(m,r) = VST(m,r) / VTMPROV(m);
   2863    
   2864   Equation PTRANSPORT
   2865   # generate price index for composite transportation services #
   2866   (all,m,MARG_COMM)
   2867       pt(m) = sum(r,REG, VTSUPPSHR(m,r) * pm(m,r));
   2868   !<
   2869       This equation generates a price index for transportation services based on
   2870       zero profits.  NOTE:
   2871       (1) Sales to international transportation are not subject to export tax.
   2872           This is why we base the costs to the transport sector on market prices
   2873           of the goods sold to international transportation.
   2874       (2) We assume that the supply shares for margin services are uniform
   2875           across freight, source of freight, and destination.
   2876       (cf. HT#7)
   2877   >!
   2878    
   2879   Coefficient
   2880       VTUSE # international margin services usage #;
   2881   Formula
   2882       VTUSE
   2883           = sum(m,MARG_COMM, sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(r,REG, sum(s,REG,
   2884               VTMFSD(m,i,r,s)))));
   2885    
   2886   Coefficient (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2887       VTFSD_MSH(m,i,r,s) # share of margin m in cost of getting i from r to s #;
   2888   Formula (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2889           (all,s,REG: VTFSD(i,r,s) > 0.0)
   2890       VTFSD_MSH(m,i,r,s) = VTMFSD(m,i,r,s) / VTFSD(i,r,s);
   2891   Formula (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2892           (all,s,REG: VTFSD(i,r,s) = 0.0)
   2893       VTFSD_MSH(m,i,r,s) = VTMUSE(m) / VTUSE;
   2894    
   2895   Equation TRANSCOSTINDEX
   2896   #  generates flow-specific modal average cost of transport index (cf. HT7) #
   2897   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2898       ptrans(i,r,s)
   2899           = sum(m,MARG_COMM, VTFSD_MSH(m,i,r,s) * [pt(m) - atmfsd(m,i,r,s)]);
   2900    
   2901   Equation TRANSTECHANGE
   2902   #  generates flow-specific average rate of technical change #
   2903   (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2904       atmfsd(m,i,r,s) = atm(m) + atf(i) + ats(r) + atd(s) + atall(m,i,r,s);
   2905    
   2906   Equation TRANSVCES
   2907   # generate demand for regional supply of global transportation service (HT 61) #
   2908   (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   2909       qst(m,r) = qtm(m) + [pt(m) - pm(m,r)];
   2910   !<
   2911       This equation generates the international transport sector's derived
   2912       demand for regional supplies of transportation services.  It reflects a
   2913       unitary elasticity of substitution between transportation services inputs
   2914       from different regions.
   2915   >!
   2916    
   2917   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2918       VIWSCOST(i,r,s) # value of imports calculated as total cost of imports #;
   2919   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2920       VIWSCOST(i,r,s) = VXWD(i,r,s) + VTFSD(i,r,s);
   2921    
   2922   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) default 1;
   2923   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2924       FOBSHR(i,r,s) # FOB share in VIW #;
   2925   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2926       FOBSHR(i,r,s) = VXWD(i,r,s) / VIWSCOST(i,r,s);
   2927   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) off;
   2928    
   2929   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) default 1;
   2930   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2931       TRNSHR(i,r,s) # transport share in VIW #;
   2932   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2933       TRNSHR(i,r,s) = VTFSD(i,r,s) / VIWSCOST(i,r,s);
   2934   Zerodivide (zero_by_zero) off;
   2935    
   2936   Equation FOBCIF
   2937   # eq'n links FOB and CIF prices for good i shipped from region r to s (HT 26') #
   2938   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   2939       pcif(i,r,s)
   2940          = FOBSHR(i,r,s) * pfob(i,r,s)
   2941          + TRNSHR(i,r,s) * ptrans(i,r,s);
   2942   !<
   2943       This equation links export and import prices for each commodity/route
   2944       triplet.  Note that technical change is embodied in ptrans(i,r,s) which is
   2945       now a cost index, as opposed to (HT 26') where it represented the price of
   2946       margins services.
   2947   >!
   2948    
   2949    
   2950   !<
   2951       --------------------------------
   2952       7. International Emissions Trade
   2953       --------------------------------
   2954   >!
   2955    
   2956   Variable (all,r,REG)
   2957       gco2q(r) # emissions quota #;
   2958   Coefficient (ge 0) (all,r,REG)
   2959       CO2Q(r) # emissions quota (millions of tonnes of CO2) #;
   2960   Update (all,r,REG)
   2961       CO2Q(r) = gco2q(r);
   2962   Read
   2963       CO2Q from file GTAPDATA header "CO2Q";
   2964    
   2965   Variable (all,r,REG)
   2966       pemp(r) # power of emissions purchases#;
   2967   Equation PEMPURCH(all,r,REG)
   2968       pemp(r) = gco2t(r) - gco2q(r);
   2969    
   2970   Equation EMTRADING
   2971   # net emissions trading revenue #
   2972   (all,r,REG)
   2973       DVCO2TRA(r)
   2974           = CO2Q(r) * NCTAXLEV(r) * 0.01 * gco2q(r)
   2975           - CO2T(r) * NCTAXLEV(r) * 0.01 * gco2t(r)
   2976           + [CO2Q(r) - CO2T(r)] * NCTAXB(REGTOBLOC(r));
   2977    
   2978   Variable (all,b,BLOC)
   2979       gco2tb(b) # carbon dioxide emissions #;
   2980   Variable (all,b,BLOC)
   2981       gco2qb(b) # emissions quota#;
   2982    
   2983   Equation TOTALEMISSIONSB # CO2 emissions #
   2984   (all,b,BLOC)
   2985       CO2TB(b) * gco2tb(b) = sum(r,REG: REGTOBLOC(r) = b, CO2T(r) * gco2t(r));
   2986    
   2987   Coefficient (all,b,BLOC)
   2988       CO2QB(b) # emissions quota (millions of tonnes of CO2)#;
   2989   Formula (all,b,BLOC)
   2990       CO2QB(b) = sum(r, REG: REGTOBLOC(r)=b, CO2Q(r));
   2991   Equation EMISSQUOTA # emissions quota #
   2992   (all,b,BLOC)
   2993       CO2QB(b) * gco2qb(b) = sum(r, REG: REGTOBLOC(r) = b, CO2Q(r) * gco2q(r));
   2994    
   2995   Variable (all,b,BLOC)
   2996       pempb(b) # power of emissions purchases#;
   2997   Equation PEMPURCHB(all,b,BLOC)
   2998       pempb(b) = gco2tb(b) - gco2qb(b);
   2999    
   3000    
   3001   !<
   3002       ---------------------
   3003       8. Regional Household
   3004       ---------------------
   3005    
   3006       8-0. Module-Specific Coefficients
   3007       8-1. Supply of Sluggish Endowments by the Regional Household
   3008       8-2. Carbon Dioxide Emissions
   3009       8-3. Carbon Tax Rate
   3010       8-4. Computation of Regional Income
   3011       8-5. Regional Household Demand System
   3012       8-6. Aggregate Utility
   3013   >!
   3014    
   3015    
   3016   !<
   3017       8-0. Module-Specific Coefficients
   3018       ---------------------------------
   3019    
   3020       only used in this Regional Household module
   3021   >!
   3022    
   3023   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   3024       XSHRPRIV(r) # private expenditure share in regional income #;
   3025   Formula (all,r,REG)
   3026       XSHRPRIV(r) = PRIVEXP(r) / INCOME(r);
   3027    
   3028   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   3029       XSHRGOV(r) # government expenditure share in regional income #;
   3030   Formula (all,r,REG)
   3031       XSHRGOV(r) = GOVEXP(r) / INCOME(r);
   3032    
   3033   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   3034       XSHRSAVE(r) # saving share in regional income #;
   3035   Formula (all,r,REG)
   3036       XSHRSAVE(r) = SAVE(r) / INCOME(r);
   3037    
   3038   Variable (all,r,REG)(all,i,CTAX_COMM)
   3039       gco2(r,i) # carbon dioxide emissions #;
   3040   Variable (all,r,REG)
   3041       dppriv(r) # private consumption distribution parameter #;
   3042   Variable (all,r,REG)
   3043       dpgov(r) # government consumption distribution parameter #;
   3044   Variable (all,r,REG)
   3045       dpsave(r) # saving distribution parameter #;
   3046   Variable (all,r,REG)
   3047       uelas(r) # elasticity of cost of utility wrt utility #;
   3048    
   3049    
   3050   !<
   3051       8-1. Supply of Endowments by the Regional Household
   3052       ---------------------------------------------------
   3053   >!
   3054    
   3055   Equation FACTORINCPRICES
   3056   # eq'n links pre- and post-tax endowment supply prices (HT 15) #
   3057   (all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3058       ps(i,r) = to(i,r) + pm(i,r);
   3059    
   3060   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   3061       TINC(r) # income tax payments in r #;
   3062   Formula (all,r,REG)
   3063       TINC(r) = sum(i,ENDW_COMM, PTAX(i,r));
   3064    
   3065   Equation TINCRATIO
   3066   # change in ratio of income tax payments to regional income #
   3067   (all,r,REG)
   3068       100.0 * INCOME(r) * del_taxrinc(r) + TINC(r) * y(r)
   3069           = sum(i,ENDW_COMM,
   3070               VOA(i,r) * [-to(i,r)] + PTAX(i,r) * [pm(i,r) + qo(i,r)]);
   3071    
   3072   Coefficient (all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3073       REVSHR(i,j,r);
   3074   Formula (all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3075       REVSHR(i,j,r) = VFM(i,j,r) / sum(k,PROD_COMM, VFM(i,k,r));
   3076   Equation ENDW_PRICE
   3077   # eq'n generates the composite price for sluggish endowments (HT 50) #
   3078   (all,i,ENDWS_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3079       pm(i,r) = sum(k,PROD_COMM, REVSHR(i,k,r) * pmes(i,k,r));
   3080    
   3081   Coefficient (parameter)(all,i,ENDW_COMM)
   3082       ETRAE(i)
   3083       # elst. of transformation for sluggish primary factor endowments #;
   3084   Read
   3085       ETRAE from file GTAPPARM header "ETRE";
   3086   !<
   3087       ETRAE is the elasticity of transformation for sluggish primary factor
   3088       endowments.  It is non-positive, by definition.
   3089   >!
   3090   Equation ENDW_SUPPLY
   3091   # eq'n distributes the sluggish endowments across sectors (HT 51) #
   3092   (all,i,ENDWS_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3093       qoes(i,j,r) = qo(i,r) - endwslack(i,r) + ETRAE(i) * [pm(i,r) - pmes(i,j,r)];
   3094    
   3095    
   3096   !<
   3097       8-2. Carbon Dioxide Emissions
   3098       -----------------------------
   3099   >!
   3100    
   3101   Equation PDEMISSIONS
   3102   # carbon dioxide emissions from private consumption of domestic product #
   3103   (all, i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3104       gco2pd(i,r) = qpd(i,r);
   3105    
   3106   Equation PIEMISSIONS
   3107   # carbon dioxide emissions from private consumption of imports #
   3108   (all,i, TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3109       gco2pm(i,r) = qpm(i,r);
   3110    
   3111   Equation GDEMISSIONS
   3112   # carbon dioxide emissions from government consumption of domestic product #
   3113   (all,i, TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3114       gco2gd(i,r) = qgd(i,r);
   3115    
   3116   Equation GIEMISSIONS
   3117   # carbon dioxide emissions from government consumption of imports #
   3118   (all, i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3119       gco2gm(i,r) = qgm(i,r);
   3120    
   3121   Equation FDEMISSIONS
   3122   # carbon dioxide emissions from firms' usage of domestic product #
   3123   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3124       gco2fd(i,j,r) = qfd(i,j,r);
   3125    
   3126   Equation FIEMISSIONS
   3127   # carbon dioxide emissions from firms' usage of imports #
   3128   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3129       gco2fm(i,j,r) = qfm(i,j,r);
   3130    
   3131   Equation CEMISSIONS # carbon dioxide emissions #
   3132   (all,r,REG)(all,i,CTAX_COMM)
   3133       CO2(r,i) * gco2(r,i) = sum(j,PROD_COMM, CO2IF(i,j,r) * gco2fm(i,j,r)
   3134           + CO2DF(i,j,r) * gco2fd(i,j,r))
   3135           + CO2DG(i,r) * gco2gd(i,r) + CO2IG(i,r) * gco2gm(i,r)
   3136           + CO2DP(i,r) * gco2pd(i,r) + CO2IP(i,r) * gco2pm(i,r);
   3137    
   3138   Equation TOTALEMISSIONS # carbon dioxide emissions #
   3139   (all,r,REG)
   3140       CO2T(r) * gco2t(r) = sum(i,CTAX_COMM, CO2(r,i) * gco2(r,i));
   3141    
   3142   Variable
   3143       gco2tw # total world emissions #;
   3144   Equation WORLDEMISS # total world emissions #
   3145       sum(r,REG, CO2T(r)) * gco2tw = sum(r,REG, CO2T(r) * gco2t(r));
   3146    
   3147    
   3148   !<
   3149       8-3. Carbon Tax Rate
   3150       --------------------
   3151    
   3152       RCTAXB and NCTAXB represent changes in real and nominal carbon tax
   3153       rates.  The real rate is defined as the nominal rate deflated by the income
   3154       deflator.
   3155   >!
   3156    
   3157   Variable (change)(all,r,REG)
   3158       RCTAX(r) # real carbon tax rate (1997 USD per tonne of CO2) #;
   3159   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   3160       PIND(r) # income deflator #;
   3161   Update (all,r,REG)
   3162       PIND(r) = p(r);
   3163   Formula (initial) (all,r,REG)
   3164       PIND(r) = 1.0;
   3165   Equation REALTAXCH
   3166   # real carbon tax rate #
   3167   (all,r,REG)
   3168       RCTAX(r) = [1.0 / PIND(r)]
   3169           * [NCTAXB(REGTOBLOC(r)) - 0.01 * NCTAXLEV(r) * p(r)];
   3170    
   3171   Variable (orig_level = 1.0)(all,b,BLOC)
   3172       pb(b) # income deflator #;
   3173    
   3174   Coefficient (all,b,BLOC)
   3175       INCOMEB(b) # Net income in bloc #;
   3176   Formula (all,b,BLOC)
   3177       INCOMEB(b) = sum(r,REG: REGTOBLOC(r) = b, INCOME(r));
   3178   Equation PIND_b # income deflator #
   3179   (all,b,BLOC)
   3180       INCOMEB(b) * pb(b) = sum(r,REG: REGTOBLOC(r) = b, INCOME(r) * p(r));
   3181    
   3182   Variable (change)(all,r,BLOC)
   3183       RCTAXB(r) # real carbon tax rate (1997 USD per tonne of CO2) #;
   3184   Coefficient (all,b,BLOC)
   3185       PINDB(b) # income deflator #;
   3186   Update (all,b,BLOC)
   3187       PINDB(b) = pb(b);
   3188   Formula (initial) (all,b,BLOC)
   3189       PINDB(b) = 1.0;
   3190   Coefficient (all,b,BLOC)
   3191       NCTAXLEVB(b) # nominal carbon tax rate (current USD per tonne of CO2) #;
   3192   Formula (all,b,BLOC)
   3193       NCTAXLEVB(b) = sum(r,REG: REGTOBLOC(r) = b, NCTAXLEV(r) * CO2T(r))
   3194           / CO2TB(b);
   3195   Equation REALTAXCHB
   3196   # real carbon tax rate #
   3197   (all,b,BLOC)
   3198       RCTAXB(b) = [1.0 / PINDB(b)]
   3199           * [NCTAXB(b) - 0.01 * NCTAXLEVB(b) * pb(b)];
   3200    
   3201   Variable (change) (all,r,REG)
   3202       del_ctgshr(r) # government share of carbon tax payments/permits revenue #;
   3203   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   3204       CTGSHARE(r) # government share of carbon tax payments/permits revenue #;
   3205   Update (change) (all,r,REG)
   3206       CTGSHARE(r) = del_ctgshr(r);
   3207   Read
   3208       CTGSHARE from file GTAPDATA header "GSHR";
   3209    
   3210   Equation TCRATIO
   3211   # change in ratio of carbon tax payments/permit rent to regional income #
   3212   (all,r,REG)
   3213       100.0 * INCOME(r) * del_ctaxr(r)
   3214           + CTGSHARE(r) * NCTAXLEV(r) * CO2Q(r) * y(r)
   3215           = 100.0 * NCTAXLEV(r) * CO2Q(r) * del_ctgshr(r)
   3216               + 100.0 * CTGSHARE(r) * CO2Q(r) * NCTAXB(REGTOBLOC(r))
   3217               + CTGSHARE(r) * NCTAXLEV(r) * CO2Q(r) * gco2q(r);
   3218    
   3219    
   3220   !<
   3221       8-4. Computation of Regional Income
   3222       -----------------------------------
   3223   >!
   3224    
   3225   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   3226       FY(r) # primary factor income in r net of depreciation #;
   3227   Formula (all,r,REG)
   3228       FY(r) = sum(i,ENDW_COMM, VOM(i,r)) - VDEP(r);
   3229   Variable (all,r,REG)
   3230       fincome(r) # factor income at market prices net of depreciation #;
   3231   Equation FACTORINCOME
   3232   # factor income at market prices net of depreciation #
   3233   (all,r,REG)
   3234       FY(r) * fincome(r)
   3235           = sum(i,ENDW_COMM, VOM(i,r) * [pm(i,r) + qo(i,r)])
   3236           - VDEP(r)  * [pcgds(r) + kb(r)];
   3237    
   3238   Variable (change)(all,r,REG)
   3239       del_indtaxr(r) # change in ratio of indirect taxes to INCOME in r #;
   3240   Equation DINDTAXRATIO
   3241   # change in ratio of indirect taxes to INCOME in r #
   3242   (all,r,REG)
   3243       del_indtaxr(r)
   3244           = del_taxrpc(r) + del_taxrgc(r) + del_taxriu(r) + del_taxrfu(r)
   3245           + del_taxrout(r) + del_taxrexp(r) + del_taxrimp(r);
   3246    
   3247   Variable (change)(all,r,REG)
   3248       del_tnctaxr(r) # change in ratio of carbon-exclusive taxes to INCOME in r #;
   3249   Equation DNCTAXRATIO
   3250   # change in ratio of carbon-exclusive taxes to INCOME in r #
   3251   (all,r,REG)
   3252       del_tnctaxr(r)
   3253           = del_taxrpc(r) + del_taxrgc(r) + del_taxriu(r) + del_taxrfu(r)
   3254           + del_taxrout(r) + del_taxrexp(r) + del_taxrimp(r) + del_taxrinc(r);
   3255    
   3256   Variable (change)(all,r,REG)
   3257       del_ttaxr(r) # change in ratio of total taxes to INCOME in r #;
   3258   Equation DTAXRATIO
   3259   # change in ratio of total taxes to INCOME in r #
   3260   (all,r,REG)
   3261       del_ttaxr(r) = del_tnctaxr(r) + del_ctaxr(r);
   3262    
   3263   !<
   3264      This variable can be swapped with the commodity- and source-generic
   3265      consumption tax shift, tp(r), in order to generate a tax replacement
   3266      scenario, whereby taxes remain a constant share of national income.
   3267   >!
   3268    
   3269   Variable (all,r,REG)
   3270       incomeslack(r) # slack variable in the expression for regional income #;
   3271   !<
   3272       This is exogenous, unless the user wishes to fix regional income.
   3273   >!
   3274    
   3275   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   3276       INDTAX(r) # indirect tax receipts in r #;
   3277   Formula (all,r,REG)
   3278       INDTAX(r) = TPC(r) + TGC(r) + TIU(r) + TFU(r) + TOUT(r) + TEX(r) + TIM(r);
   3279    
   3280   Equation REGIONALINCOME
   3281   # regional income = sum of primary factor income and indirect tax receipts #
   3282   (all,r,REG)
   3283       INCOME(r) * y(r)
   3284           = FY(r) * fincome(r)
   3285           + 100.0 * INCOME(r) * del_indtaxr(r)
   3286           + INDTAX(r) * y(r)
   3287           + CO2Q(r) * NCTAXLEV(r) * gco2q(r)
   3288           + 100.0 * CO2Q(r) * NCTAXB(REGTOBLOC(r))
   3289           + INCOME(r) * incomeslack(r);
   3290   !<
   3291       This equation computes regional income as the sum of primary factor
   3292       payment and indirect tax receipts.  The first term computes the change in
   3293       endowment income, net of depreciation.  The second and third terms compute
   3294       the change in ordinary indirect tax revenue.  The fourth term computes the
   3295       revenues/expenditures from carbon emissions trading.  The fifth term
   3296       computes revenue from carbon taxes.
   3297   >!
   3298    
   3299    
   3300   !<
   3301       8-5. Regional Household Demand System
   3302       -------------------------------------
   3303   >!
   3304    
   3305   Variable (all,r,REG)
   3306       dpav(r) # average distribution parameter shift, for EV calc. #;
   3307   Equation DPARAV
   3308   # average distribution parameter shift #
   3309   (all,r,REG)
   3310       dpav(r)
   3311           = XSHRPRIV(r) * dppriv(r)
   3312           + XSHRGOV(r) * dpgov(r)
   3313           + XSHRSAVE(r) * dpsave(r);
   3314    
   3315   Equation UTILITELASTIC
   3316   # elasticity of cost of utility wrt utility #
   3317   (all,r,REG)
   3318       uelas(r) = XSHRPRIV(r) * uepriv(r) - dpav(r);
   3319    
   3320   Equation PRIVCONSEXP
   3321   # private consumption expenditure #
   3322   (all,r,REG)
   3323       yp(r) - y(r) = -[uepriv(r) - uelas(r)] + dppriv(r);
   3324    
   3325   Equation GOVCONSEXP
   3326   # government consumption expenditure #
   3327   (all,r,REG)
   3328       yg(r) - y(r) = uelas(r) + dpgov(r);
   3329    
   3330   Equation SAVING
   3331   # saving #
   3332   (all,r,REG)
   3333       psave(r) + qsave(r) - y(r) = uelas(r) + dpsave(r);
   3334    
   3335    
   3336   !<
   3337       8-6. Aggregate Utility
   3338       ----------------------
   3339   >!
   3340   Equation PRICEINDEXREG
   3341       # price index for disposition of income by regional household #
   3342       (all,r,REG)
   3343       p(r)
   3344           = XSHRPRIV(r) * ppriv(r)
   3345           + XSHRGOV(r) * pgov(r)
   3346           + XSHRSAVE(r) * psave(r);
   3347    
   3348   Variable (all,r,REG)
   3349       au(r) # input-neutral shift in utility function #;
   3350   Variable (all,r,REG)
   3351       dpsum(r) # sum of the distribution parameters #;
   3352    
   3353   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   3354       DPARSUM(r) # sum of distribution parameters #;
   3355   Read
   3356       DPARSUM from file GTAPDATA header "DPSM";
   3357   Update (all,r,REG)
   3358       DPARSUM(r) = dpsum(r);
   3359    
   3360   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   3361       UTILELAS(r) # elasticity of cost of utility wrt utility #;
   3362   Formula (all,r,REG)
   3363       UTILELAS(r)
   3364           = [UELASPRIV(r) * XSHRPRIV(r) + XSHRGOV(r) + XSHRSAVE(r)] / DPARSUM(r);
   3365    
   3366   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   3367       DPARPRIV(r) # private consumption distribution parameter #;
   3368   Formula (all,r,REG)
   3369       DPARPRIV(r) = UELASPRIV(r) * XSHRPRIV(r) / UTILELAS(r);
   3370    
   3371   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   3372       DPARGOV(r) # government consumption distribution parameter #;
   3373   Formula (all,r,REG)
   3374       DPARGOV(r) = XSHRGOV(r) / UTILELAS(r);
   3375    
   3376   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   3377       DPARSAVE(r) # saving distribution parameter #;
   3378   Formula (all,r,REG)
   3379       DPARSAVE(r) = XSHRSAVE(r) / UTILELAS(r);
   3380    
   3381   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   3382       UTILPRIV(r) # utility from private consumption #;
   3383   Formula (initial)(all,r,REG)
   3384       UTILPRIV(r) = 1.0;
   3385   Update (all,r,REG)
   3386       UTILPRIV(r) = up(r);
   3387    
   3388   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   3389       UTILGOV(r) # utility from government consumption #;
   3390   Formula (initial)(all,r,REG)
   3391       UTILGOV(r) = 1.0;
   3392   Update (all,r,REG)
   3393       UTILGOV(r) = ug(r);
   3394    
   3395   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   3396       UTILSAVE(r) # utility from saving #;
   3397   Formula (initial)(all,r,REG)
   3398       UTILSAVE(r) = 1.0;
   3399   Update (change) (all,r,REG)
   3400       UTILSAVE(r) = [[qsave(r) - pop(r)] / 100] * UTILSAVE(r);
   3401    
   3402   Variable (all,r,REG)
   3403       u(r) # per capita utility from aggregate hhld expend. in region r #;
   3404   Equation UTILITY
   3405   # regional household utility #
   3406   (all,r,REG)
   3407       u(r)
   3408           = au(r)
   3409           + DPARPRIV(r) * loge(UTILPRIV(r)) * dppriv(r)
   3410           + DPARGOV(r) * loge(UTILGOV(r)) * dpgov(r)
   3411           + DPARSAVE(r) * loge(UTILSAVE(r)) * dpsave(r)
   3412           + [1.0 / UTILELAS(r)] * [y(r) - pop(r) - p(r)];
   3413    
   3414   Equation DISTPARSUM
   3415   # sum of the distribution parameters #
   3416   (all,r,REG)
   3417       DPARSUM(r) * dpsum(r)
   3418           = DPARPRIV(r) * dppriv(r)
   3419           + DPARGOV(r) * dpgov(r)
   3420           + DPARSAVE(r) * dpsave(r);
   3421    
   3422    
   3423   !<
   3424       -------------------------
   3425       9. Equilibrium Conditions
   3426       -------------------------
   3427    
   3428       9-1. Market Clearing Conditions
   3429       9-2. Walras' Law
   3430   >!
   3431    
   3432    
   3433   !<
   3434       9-1. Market Clearing Conditions
   3435       -------------------------------
   3436   >!
   3437    
   3438   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3439       SHRDFM(i,j,r) # share of dom. prod. i used by sector j in r at mkt prices #;
   3440   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3441       SHRDFM(i,j,r) = VDFM(i,j,r) / VDM(i,r);
   3442    
   3443   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3444       SHRDPM(i,r) # share of domestic prod. of i used by private hhlds in r #;
   3445   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3446       SHRDPM(i,r) = VDPM(i,r) / VDM(i,r);
   3447    
   3448   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3449       SHRDGM(i,r) # share of imports of i used by gov't hhlds in r #;
   3450   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3451       SHRDGM(i,r) = VDGM(i,r) / VDM(i,r);
   3452    
   3453   Variable (orig_level=VDM)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3454       qds(i,r) # domestic sales of commodity i in r #;
   3455   Equation MKTCLDOM
   3456   # eq'n assures market clearing for domestic sales (HT 3) #
   3457   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3458       qds(i,r)
   3459           = sum(j,PROD_COMM, SHRDFM(i,j,r) * qfd(i,j,r))
   3460           + SHRDPM(i,r) * qpd(i,r)
   3461           + SHRDGM(i,r) * qgd(i,r);
   3462    
   3463   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3464       SHRDM(i,r) # share of domestic sales of i in r #;
   3465   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3466       SHRDM(i,r) = VDM(i,r) / VOM(i,r);
   3467    
   3468   Coefficient (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3469       SHRST(m,r) # share of sales of m to global transport services in r #;
   3470   Formula (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3471       SHRST(m,r) = VST(m,r) / VOM(m,r);
   3472    
   3473   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   3474       SHRXMD(i,r,s) # share of export sales of i to s in r #;
   3475   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)(all,s,REG)
   3476       SHRXMD(i,r,s) = VXMD(i,r,s) / VOM(i,r);
   3477    
   3478   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3479       tradslack(i,r) # slack variable in tradeables market clearing condition #;
   3480   !<
   3481       This is exogenous unless the user wishes to specify the price of
   3482       tradeables exogenously, in which case the analysis becomes partial
   3483       equilibrium and walraslack must be exogenized.
   3484   >!
   3485    
   3486   Equation MKTCLTRD_MARG
   3487   # eq'n assures market clearing for margins commodities (HT 1) #
   3488   (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3489       qo(m,r)
   3490           = SHRDM(m,r) * qds(m,r)
   3491           + SHRST(m,r) * qst(m,r)
   3492           + sum(s,REG, SHRXMD(m,r,s) * qxs(m,r,s))
   3493           + tradslack(m,r);
   3494   Equation MKTCLTRD_NMRG
   3495   # eq'n assures market clearing for the non-margins commodities (HT 1) #
   3496   (all,i,NMRG_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3497       qo(i,r)
   3498           = SHRDM(i,r) * qds(i,r)
   3499           + sum(s,REG, SHRXMD(i,r,s) * qxs(i,r,s))
   3500           + tradslack(i,r);
   3501    
   3502   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3503       VIM(i,r) # value of imports of commodity i in r at domestic market prices #;
   3504   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3505       VIM(i,r) = sum(j,PROD_COMM, VIFM(i,j,r)) + VIPM(i,r) + VIGM(i,r);
   3506    
   3507   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3508       SHRIFM(i,j,r) # share of import i used by sector j in r  #;
   3509   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3510       SHRIFM(i,j,r) = VIFM(i,j,r) / VIM(i,r);
   3511    
   3512   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3513       SHRIPM(i,r) # share of import i used by private hhlds in r #;
   3514   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3515       SHRIPM(i,r) = VIPM(i,r) / VIM(i,r);
   3516    
   3517   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3518       SHRIGM(i,r) # the share of import i used by gov't hhlds in r #;
   3519   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3520       SHRIGM(i,r) = VIGM(i,r) / VIM(i,r);
   3521    
   3522   Equation MKTCLIMP
   3523   # eq'n assures mkt clearing for imported goods entering each region (HT 2) #
   3524   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3525       qim(i,r)
   3526           = sum(j,PROD_COMM, SHRIFM(i,j,r) * qfm(i,j,r))
   3527           + SHRIPM(i,r) * qpm(i,r)
   3528           + SHRIGM(i,r) * qgm(i,r);
   3529    
   3530   Coefficient (all,i,ENDWM_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3531       SHREM(i,j,r) # share of mobile endowment i used by sector j at mkt prices #;
   3532   Formula (all,i,ENDWM_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3533       SHREM(i,j,r) = VFM(i,j,r) / VOM(i,r);
   3534    
   3535   Equation MKTCLENDWM
   3536   # eq'n assures mkt clearing for perfectly mobile endowments in each r (HT 4) #
   3537   (all,i,ENDWM_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3538       qo(i,r) = sum(j,PROD_COMM, SHREM(i,j,r) * qfe(i,j,r)) + endwslack(i,r);
   3539   !<
   3540       This equation assures market clearing for perfectly mobile endowments (HT 4)
   3541   >!
   3542    
   3543   Equation MKTCLENDWS
   3544   # eq'n assures mkt clearing for imperfectly mobile endowments in each r (HT 5)#
   3545   (all,i,ENDWS_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3546       qoes(i,j,r) = qfe(i,j,r);
   3547   !<
   3548       This equation assures market clearing for sluggish endowments (HT 5)
   3549   >!
   3550    
   3551    
   3552   !<
   3553       9-2. Walras' Law
   3554       ----------------
   3555   >!
   3556    
   3557   Variable
   3558       walras_sup # supply in omitted market--global supply of cgds composite #;
   3559   Equation WALRAS_S
   3560   # Extra eq'n computes change in supply in the omitted market. #
   3561       walras_sup = pcgdswld + globalcgds;
   3562   !<
   3563       This is an extra equation which simply computes change in supply in the
   3564       omitted market.  (modified from HT 12 to reflect the value as opposed to
   3565       quantity change, in light of the new treatment of psave(r))
   3566   >!
   3567    
   3568   Variable
   3569       walras_dem # demand in the omitted market--global demand for savings #;
   3570   Equation WALRAS_D
   3571   # Extra eq'n computes change in demand in the omitted market. #
   3572       GLOBINV * walras_dem = sum(r,REG, SAVE(r) * [psave(r) + qsave(r)]);
   3573   !<
   3574       This is an extra equation which simply computes change in demand in the
   3575       omitted market.  (modified from HT 13 to reflect the value as opposed to
   3576       quantity change)
   3577   >!
   3578    
   3579   Variable
   3580       walraslack # slack variable in the omitted market #;
   3581   !<
   3582       This is endogenous under normal, GE closure.  If the GE links are broken,
   3583       then this must be swapped with the numeraire, thereby forcing global
   3584       savings to explicitly equal global investment.
   3585   >!
   3586   Equation WALRAS
   3587   # Check Walras' Law.  Value of "walraslack" should be zero. (HT 14) #
   3588       walras_sup = walras_dem + walraslack;
   3589   !<
   3590       This equation checks Walras' Law.  The value of walraslack should be zero
   3591       in any GE simulation.  (HT 14)
   3592   >!
   3593    
   3594    
   3595   !<
   3596       ==========
   3597       Appendices
   3598       ==========
   3599    
   3600       A. Summary Indices
   3601       B. Equivalent Variation
   3602       C. Welfare Decomposition
   3603       D. Terms of Trade Decomposition
   3604   >!
   3605    
   3606    
   3607   !<
   3608       ------------------
   3609       A. Summary Indices
   3610       ------------------
   3611    
   3612       The following equations calculate many useful summary statistics.  They do
   3613       not generally affect the equilibrium structure of the model, although they
   3614       do include the equation for the usual numeraire variable, "pfactwld". Some
   3615       are documented in Hertel and Tsigas, many are new.
   3616    
   3617       A-0. Appendix-Specific Variables and Coefficients
   3618       A-1. Factor Price Indices
   3619       A-2. Regional Terms of Trade
   3620       A-3. GDP Indices (Value, Price and Quantity)
   3621       A-4. Aggregate Trade Indices (Value, Price and Quantity)
   3622       A-5. Trade Balance Indices
   3623       A-6. Real Energy Price Index
   3624   >!
   3625    
   3626    
   3627   !<
   3628       A-0. Appendix-Specific Variables and Coefficients
   3629       -------------------------------------------------
   3630    
   3631       only used in this Summary Indices appendix
   3632   >!
   3633    
   3634   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   3635       vxwfob(i,s) # value of merchandise regional exports, by commodity, FOB #;
   3636   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   3637       viwcif(i,s) # value of merchandise regional imports, by commodity, CIF #;
   3638   Variable (all,r,REG)
   3639       vxwreg(r) # value of merchandise exports, by region #;
   3640   Variable (all,r,REG)
   3641       viwreg(r) # value of merchandise imports, by region, at world prices #;
   3642    
   3643   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3644       VXW(i,r) # value of exports by comm. i and region r at FOB prices #;
   3645   Formula (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3646       VXW(m,r) = sum(s,REG, VXWD(m,r,s)) + VST(m,r);
   3647   Formula (all,i,NMRG_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3648       VXW(i,r) = sum(s,REG, VXWD(i,r,s));
   3649    
   3650   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   3651       VXWREGION(r) # value of exports by region r at FOB prices #;
   3652   Formula (all,r,REG)
   3653       VXWREGION(r) = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, VXW(i,r));
   3654    
   3655   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   3656       VIW(i,s) # value of commodity imports i into s at CIF prices #;
   3657   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   3658       VIW(i,s) = sum(r,REG, VIWS(i,r,s));
   3659   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   3660       VIWREGION(r) # value of commodity imports by region r at CIF prices #;
   3661   Formula (all,r,REG)
   3662       VIWREGION(r) = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, VIW(i,r));
   3663    
   3664    
   3665   !<
   3666       A-1. Factor Price Indices
   3667       -------------------------
   3668   >!
   3669    
   3670   Variable (orig_level=1.0)(all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3671       pfactreal(i,r) # ratio of return to primary factor i to CPI in r #;
   3672   Equation REALRETURN
   3673   # eq'n defines the real rate of return to primary factor i in region r #
   3674   (all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   3675       pfactreal(i,s) = pm(i,s) - ppriv(s);
   3676   !<
   3677       This equation defines the real rate of return to primary factor i in
   3678       region r (new).
   3679   >!
   3680    
   3681   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   3682       VENDWREG(r) # value of primary factors, at mkt prices, by region #;
   3683   Formula (all,r,REG)
   3684       VENDWREG(r) = sum(i,ENDW_COMM, VOM(i,r));
   3685    
   3686   Variable (orig_level=1.0)(all,r,REG)
   3687       pfactor(r) # market price index of primary factors, by region #;
   3688   Equation PRIMFACTPR
   3689   # computes % change in price index of primary factors, by region #
   3690   (all,r,REG)
   3691       VENDWREG(r) * pfactor(r) = sum(i,ENDW_COMM, VOM(i,r) * pm(i,r));
   3692    
   3693   Coefficient
   3694       VENDWWLD # value of primary factors, at mkt prices, worldwide #;
   3695   Formula
   3696       VENDWWLD = sum(r,REG, VENDWREG(r));
   3697   Variable (orig_level=1.0)
   3698       pfactwld # world price index of primary factors #;
   3699   Equation PRIMFACTPRWLD
   3700   # computes % change in global price index of primary factors #
   3701       VENDWWLD * pfactwld = sum(r,REG, VENDWREG(r) * pfactor(r));
   3702    
   3703    
   3704   !<
   3705       A-2. Regional Terms of Trade
   3706       ----------------------------
   3707    
   3708       The next three equations correspond to Table 10 of Hertel and Tsigas on
   3709       Regional Terms of Trade.
   3710   >!
   3711    
   3712   Variable (orig_level=1.0)(all,r,REG)
   3713       psw(r) # index of prices received for tradeables produced in r #;
   3714   Equation REGSUPRICE
   3715   # estimate change in index of prices received for tradeables i produced in r #
   3716   (all,r,REG)
   3717       VXWREGION(r) * psw(r)
   3718           = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(s,REG, VXWD(i,r,s) * pfob(i,r,s)))
   3719           + sum(m,MARG_COMM, VST(m,r) * pm(m,r));
   3720   !<
   3721       This equation estimates the change in the index of prices received for
   3722       tradeable products produced in r.  (modified from HT 64 to eliminate the
   3723       investment component)
   3724   >!
   3725    
   3726   Variable (orig_level=1.0)(all,r,REG)
   3727       pdw(r) # index of prices paid for tradeables used in region r #;
   3728   Equation REGDEMPRICE
   3729   # estimate change in index of prices paid for tradeable products used in r #
   3730   (all,r,REG)
   3731       VIWREGION(r) * pdw(r)
   3732           = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(k,REG, VIWS(i,k,r) * pcif(i,k,r)));
   3733   !<
   3734       This equation estimates the change in the index of prices paid for
   3735       tradeable products used in r.  (modified from HT 65 to eliminate savings)
   3736   >!
   3737    
   3738   Variable (orig_level=1.0)(all,r,REG)
   3739       tot(r) # terms of trade for region r: tot(r) = psw(r) - pdw(r) #;
   3740   Equation TOTeq
   3741   # terms of trade equation computed as difference in psw and pdw (HT 66) #
   3742   (all,r,REG)
   3743       tot(r) = psw(r) - pdw(r);
   3744    
   3745    
   3746   !<
   3747       A-3. GDP Indices (Value, Price and Quantity)
   3748       --------------------------------------------
   3749   >!
   3750    
   3751   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   3752       GDP(r) # Gross Domestic Product in region r #;
   3753   Formula (all,s,REG)
   3754       GDP(s)
   3755           = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, VPAT(i,s))
   3756           + sum(i,TRAD_COMM, VGAT(i,s))
   3757           + sum(k,CGDS_COMM, VOA(k,s))
   3758           + sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(r,REG, VXWD(i,s,r)))
   3759           + sum(m,MARG_COMM, VST(m,s))
   3760           - sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(r,REG, VIWS(i,r,s)));
   3761    
   3762   !<
   3763       Gross Domestic Product in region r.  Trade is valued at FOB and CIF
   3764       prices.
   3765   >!
   3766    
   3767   Variable (all,r,REG)
   3768       vgdp(r) # change in value of GDP #;
   3769   Equation VGDP_r
   3770   # change in value of GDP (HT 70) #
   3771   (all,r,REG)
   3772       GDP(r) * vgdp(r)
   3773           = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, VGAT(i,r) * [qgt(i,r) + pgt(i,r)])
   3774           + sum(i,TRAD_COMM, VPAT(i,r) * [qpt(i,r) + ppt(i,r)])
   3775           + REGINV(r) * [qcgds(r) + pcgds(r)]
   3776           + sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(s,REG, VXWD(i,r,s) * [qxs(i,r,s) + pfob(i,r,s)]))
   3777           + sum(m,MARG_COMM, VST(m,r) * [qst(m,r) + pm(m,r)])
   3778           - sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(s,REG,
   3779               VIWS(i,s,r) * [qxs(i,s,r) + pcif(i,s,r)]));
   3780    
   3781   Variable (orig_level=1.0)(all,r,REG)
   3782       pgdp(r) # GDP price index #;
   3783   Equation PGDP_r
   3784   # GDP price index (HT 71) #
   3785   (all,r,REG)
   3786       GDP(r) * pgdp(r)
   3787           = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, VGAT(i,r) * pgt(i,r))
   3788           + sum(i,TRAD_COMM, VPAT(i,r) * ppt(i,r))
   3789           + REGINV(r) * pcgds(r)
   3790           + sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(s,REG, VXWD(i,r,s) * pfob(i,r,s)))
   3791           + sum(m,MARG_COMM, VST(m,r) * pm(m,r))
   3792           - sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(s,REG, VIWS(i,s,r) * pcif(i,s,r)));
   3793    
   3794   Variable (orig_level=GDP)(all,r,REG)
   3795       qgdp(r) # GDP quantity index #;
   3796   Equation QGDP_r
   3797   # GDP quantity index #
   3798   (all,r,REG)
   3799       GDP(r) * qgdp(r)
   3800           = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, VGAT(i,r) * qgt(i,r))
   3801           + sum(i,TRAD_COMM, VPAT(i,r) * qpt(i,r))
   3802           + REGINV(r) * qcgds(r)
   3803           + sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(s,REG, VXWD(i,r,s) * qxs(i,r,s)))
   3804           + sum(m,MARG_COMM, VST(m,r) * qst(m,r))
   3805           - sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(s,REG, VIWS(i,s,r) * qxs(i,s,r)));
   3806   !<
   3807       modified from HT 72 for use with AnalyzeGE
   3808   >!
   3809    
   3810   Variable (all,i,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3811       compvalad(i,r) # composition of value added for good i and region r #;
   3812   Equation COMPVALADEQ
   3813   # track change in composition of value added #
   3814   (all,i,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3815       compvalad(i,r) = qo(i,r) - qgdp(r);
   3816    
   3817    
   3818   !<
   3819       A-4. Aggregate Trade Indices (Value, Price and Quantity)
   3820       --------------------------------------------------------
   3821   >!
   3822    
   3823    
   3824   !<
   3825       Common Variables and Coefficients
   3826       Value Indices for Aggregate Trade
   3827       Price Indices for Aggregate Trade
   3828       Quantity Indices for Aggregate Trade
   3829   >!
   3830    
   3831    
   3832   !<
   3833       Common Variables and Coefficients
   3834       .................................
   3835    
   3836       only used in this Aggregate Trade Indices section
   3837   >!
   3838    
   3839   Variable (orig_level=1.0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3840       pxw(i,r) # aggregate exports price index of i from region r #;
   3841    
   3842   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   3843       VXWCOMMOD(i) # value of world exports by commodity i at FOB prices #;
   3844   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   3845       VXWCOMMOD(i) = sum(r,REG, VXW(i,r));
   3846    
   3847   Coefficient
   3848       VXWLD # value of commodity exports, FOB, globally #;
   3849   Formula
   3850       VXWLD = sum(r,REG, VXWREGION(r));
   3851    
   3852   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   3853       VIWCOMMOD(i) # global value of commodity imports, CIF, by commodity #;
   3854   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   3855       VIWCOMMOD(i) = sum(r,REG, VIW(i,r));
   3856    
   3857   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3858       PW_PM(i,r) # ratio of world to domestic prices #;
   3859   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3860       PW_PM(i,r) = sum(s,REG, VXWD(i,r,s)) / sum(s,REG, VXMD(i,r,s));
   3861   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3862       VOW(i,r) # value of output in r at FOB including transportation services #;
   3863   Formula (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3864       VOW(m,r) = VDM(m,r) * PW_PM(m,r) + sum(s,REG, VXWD(m,r,s)) + VST(m,r);
   3865   Formula (all,i,NMRG_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3866       VOW(i,r) = VDM(i,r) * PW_PM(i,r) + sum(s,REG, VXWD(i,r,s));
   3867    
   3868   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   3869       VWOW(i) # value of world supply at world prices for i #;
   3870   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   3871       VWOW(i) = sum(r,REG, VOW(i,r));
   3872    
   3873   Coefficient (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   3874       VWOU(i) # value of world output of i at user prices #;
   3875   Formula (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   3876       VWOU(i) = sum(s,REG, VPAT(i,s) + VGAT(i,s)
   3877           + sum(j,PROD_COMM, VFAD(i,j,s)));
   3878    
   3879    
   3880   !<
   3881       Value Indices for Aggregate Trade
   3882       .................................
   3883   >!
   3884    
   3885   Equation VREGEX_ir_MARG
   3886   # the change in FOB value of exports of m from r #
   3887   (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3888       VXW(m,r) * vxwfob(m,r)
   3889           = sum(s,REG, VXWD(m,r,s) * [qxs(m,r,s) + pfob(m,r,s)])
   3890           + VST(m,r) * [qst(m,r) + pm(m,r)];
   3891   Equation VREGEX_ir_NMRG
   3892   # the change in FOB value of exports of commodity i from r (HT 73) #
   3893   (all,i,NMRG_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3894       VXW(i,r) * vxwfob(i,r)
   3895           = sum(s,REG, VXWD(i,r,s) * [qxs(i,r,s) + pfob(i,r,s)]);
   3896    
   3897   Equation VREGEX_r
   3898   # computes % change in value of merchandise exports, by region (HT 75) #
   3899   (all,r,REG)
   3900       VXWREGION(r) * vxwreg(r) = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, VXW(i,r) * vxwfob(i,r));
   3901    
   3902   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   3903       vxwcom(i) # value of global merchandise exports by commodity #;
   3904   Equation VWLDEX_i
   3905   # computes % change in FOB value of global exports, by commodity (HT 77) #
   3906   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   3907       VXWCOMMOD(i) * vxwcom(i) = sum(r,REG, VXW(i,r) * vxwfob(i,r));
   3908    
   3909   Variable
   3910       vxwwld # value of world trade #;
   3911   Equation VWLDEX
   3912   # computes % change in value of global exports (HT 79) #
   3913       VXWLD * vxwwld = sum(r,REG, VXWREGION(r) * vxwreg(r));
   3914    
   3915   Equation VREGIM_is
   3916   # the change in CIF value of imports of commodity i into s (HT 74) #
   3917   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   3918       VIW(i,s) * viwcif(i,s)
   3919           = sum(r,REG, VIWS(i,r,s) * [pcif(i,r,s) + qxs(i,r,s)]);
   3920    
   3921   Equation VREGIM_s
   3922   # computes % change in value of imports, CIF basis, by region (HT 76) #
   3923   (all,s,REG)
   3924       VIWREGION(s) * viwreg(s) = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, VIW(i,s) * viwcif(i,s));
   3925    
   3926   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   3927       viwcom(i) # value of global merchandise imports i, at world prices #;
   3928   Equation VWLDIM_i
   3929   # computes % change in value of global imports, by commodity (HT 78) #
   3930   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   3931       VIWCOMMOD(i) * viwcom(i) = sum(s,REG, VIW(i,s) * viwcif(i,s));
   3932    
   3933   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   3934       valuew(i) # value of world supply of good i #;
   3935   Equation VWLDOUT
   3936   # change in value of world output of comm. i at FOB prices (HT 80) #
   3937   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   3938       VWOW(i) * valuew(i) = sum(r,REG, VOW(i,r) * [pxw(i,r) + qo(i,r)]);
   3939    
   3940   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   3941       valuewu(i) # value of world supply of good i at user prices #;
   3942   Equation VWLDOUTUSE
   3943   # change in value of world output of commodity i at user prices #
   3944   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   3945       VWOU(i) * valuewu(i)
   3946           = sum(s,REG, VPAT(i,s) * [ppt(i,s) + qpt(i,s)]
   3947           + VGAT(i,s) * [pgt(i,s) + qgt(i,s)]
   3948           + sum(j,PROD_COMM, VFAD(i,j,s) * [pft(i,j,s) + qft(i,j,s)]));
   3949    
   3950    
   3951   !<
   3952       Price Indices for Aggregate Trade
   3953       .................................
   3954   >!
   3955    
   3956   Equation PREGEX_ir_MARG
   3957   # change in FOB price index of exports of m from r #
   3958   (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3959       VXW(m,r) * pxw(m,r)
   3960           = sum(s,REG, VXWD(m,r,s) * pfob(m,r,s)) + VST(m,r) * pm(m,r);
   3961    
   3962   Equation PREGEX_ir_NMRG
   3963   # change in FOB price index of exports of commodity i from r (HT 81) #
   3964   (all,i,NMRG_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3965       VXW(i,r) * pxw(i,r) = sum(s,REG, VXWD(i,r,s) * pfob(i,r,s));
   3966    
   3967   Variable (orig_level=1.0)(all,r,REG)
   3968       pxwreg(r) # price index of merchandise exports, by region #;
   3969   Equation PREGEX_r
   3970   # computes % change in price index of exports, by region (HT 83) #
   3971   (all,r,REG)
   3972       VXWREGION(r) * pxwreg(r) = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, VXW(i,r) * pxw(i,r));
   3973    
   3974   Variable (orig_level=1.0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   3975       pxwcom(i) # price index of global merchandise exports by commodity #;
   3976   Equation PWLDEX_i
   3977   # computes % change in price index of exports, by commodity (HT 85) #
   3978   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   3979       VXWCOMMOD(i) * pxwcom(i) = sum(r,REG, VXW(i,r) * pxw(i,r));
   3980    
   3981   Variable (orig_level=1.0)
   3982       pxwwld # price index of world trade #;
   3983   Equation PWLDEX
   3984   # computes % change in price index of global exports (HT 87) #
   3985       VXWLD * pxwwld = sum(r,REG, VXWREGION(r) * pxwreg(r));
   3986    
   3987   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   3988       piw(i,r) # world price of composite import i in region r #;
   3989   Equation PREGIM_is
   3990   # change in CIF price index of imports of commodity i into s (HT 82) #
   3991   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   3992       VIW(i,s) * piw(i,s) = sum(r,REG, VIWS(i,r,s) * pcif(i,r,s));
   3993    
   3994   Variable (orig_level=1.0)(all,r,REG)
   3995       piwreg(r) # price index of merchandise imports, by region #;
   3996   Equation PREGIM_s
   3997   # computes % change in price index of imports, by region (HT 84) #
   3998   (all,s,REG)
   3999       VIWREGION(s) * piwreg(s) = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, VIW(i,s) * piw(i,s));
   4000    
   4001   Variable (orig_level=1.0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   4002       piwcom(i) # price index of global merchandise imports by commodity #;
   4003   Equation PWLDIM_i
   4004   # computes % change in price index of imports, by commodity (HT 86) #
   4005   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   4006       VIWCOMMOD(i) * piwcom(i) = sum(s,REG, VIW(i,s) * piw(i,s));
   4007    
   4008   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   4009       pw(i) # world price index for total good i supplies #;
   4010   Equation PWLDOUT
   4011   # change in index of world prices, FOB, for total production of i (HT 88) #
   4012   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   4013       VWOW(i) * pw(i) = sum(r,REG, VOW(i,r) * pxw(i,r));
   4014    
   4015   Variable (orig_level=1.0)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   4016       pwu(i) # world price index for total good i supplies at user prices #;
   4017   Equation PWLDUSE
   4018   # change in index of user prices for deflating world production of i #
   4019   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   4020       VWOU(i) * pwu(i)
   4021           = sum(s,REG, VPAT(i,s) * ppt(i,s)
   4022           + VGAT(i,s) * pgt(i,s)
   4023           + sum(j,PROD_COMM, VFAD(i,j,s) * pft(i,j,s)));
   4024    
   4025    
   4026   !<
   4027       Quantity Indices for Aggregate Trade
   4028       ....................................
   4029   >!
   4030   Variable (orig_level=VXW)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4031       qxw(i,r) # aggregate exports of i from region r, FOB weights #;
   4032   Equation QREGEX_ir_MARG
   4033   # change in volume of exports of margin commodity m from r #
   4034   (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4035       VXW(m,r) * qxw(m,r)
   4036           = sum(s,REG, VXWD(m,r,s) * qxs(m,r,s)) + VST(m,r) * qst(m,r);
   4037   Equation QREGEX_ir_NMRG
   4038   # change in volume of exports of non-margin commodity i from r #
   4039   (all,i,NMRG_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4040       VXW(i,r) * qxw(i,r) = sum(s,REG, VXWD(i,r,s) * qxs(i,r,s));
   4041   !<
   4042       modified from HT 89 for use with AnalyzeGE
   4043   >!
   4044    
   4045   Variable (orig_level=VXWREGION)(all,r,REG)
   4046       qxwreg(r) # volume of merchandise exports, by region #;
   4047   Equation QREGEX_r
   4048   # computes % change in quantity index of exports, by region #
   4049   (all,r,REG)
   4050       VXWREGION(r) * qxwreg(r) = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, VXW(i,r) * qxw(i,r));
   4051   !<
   4052       modified from HT 91 for use with AnalyzeGE
   4053   >!
   4054    
   4055   Variable (orig_level=VXWCOMMOD)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   4056       qxwcom(i) # volume of global merchandise exports by commodity #;
   4057   Equation QWLDEX_i
   4058   # computes % change in quantity index of exports, by commodity #
   4059   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   4060       VXWCOMMOD(i) * qxwcom(i) = sum(r,REG, VXW(i,r) * qxw(i,r));
   4061   !<
   4062       modified from HT 93 for use with AnalyzeGE
   4063   >!
   4064    
   4065   Variable (orig_level=VXWLD)
   4066       qxwwld # volume of world trade #;
   4067   Equation QWLDEX
   4068   # computes % change in quantity index of global exports #
   4069       VXWLD * qxwwld = sum(r,REG, VXWREGION(r) * qxwreg(r));
   4070   !<
   4071       modified from HT 95 for use with AnalyzeGE
   4072   >!
   4073    
   4074   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   4075       qiw(i,s) # aggregate imports of i into region s, CIF weights #;
   4076   Equation QREGIM_is
   4077   # change in volume of imports of commodity i into s #
   4078   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   4079       VIW(i,s) * qiw(i,s) = sum(r,REG, VIWS(i,r,s) * qxs(i,r,s));
   4080   !<
   4081       modified from HT 90 for use with AnalyzeGE
   4082   >!
   4083    
   4084   Variable (orig_level=VIWREGION)(all,r,REG)
   4085       qiwreg(r) # volume of merchandise imports, by region #;
   4086   Equation QREGIM_s
   4087   # computes % change in quantity index of imports, by region #
   4088   (all,s,REG)
   4089       VIWREGION(s) * qiwreg(s) = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, VIW(i,s) * qiw(i,s));
   4090   !<
   4091       modified from HT 92 for use with AnalyzeGE
   4092   >!
   4093    
   4094   Variable (orig_level=VIWCOMMOD)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   4095       qiwcom(i) # volume of global merchandise imports by commodity #;
   4096   Equation QWLDIM_i
   4097   # computes % change in quantity index of imports, by commodity #
   4098   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   4099       VIWCOMMOD(i) * qiwcom(i) = sum(s,REG, VIW(i,s) * qiw(i,s));
   4100   !<
   4101       modified from HT 94 for use with AnalyzeGE
   4102   >!
   4103    
   4104   Variable (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   4105       qow(i) # quantity index for world supply of good i #;
   4106   Equation QWLDOUT
   4107   # change in index of world production of i #
   4108   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   4109       VWOW(i) * qow(i) = sum(r,REG, VOW(i,r) * qo(i,r));
   4110   !<
   4111       modified from HT 96 for use with AnalyzeGE
   4112   >!
   4113    
   4114   Variable (orig_level=VWOU)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   4115       qowu(i) # quantity index for world supply of good i at user prices #;
   4116   Equation QWLDOUTU
   4117   # change in index of world production of i evaluated at user prices #
   4118   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)
   4119       VWOU(i) * qowu(i)
   4120           = sum(s,REG, VPAT(i,s) * qpt(i,s)
   4121           + VGAT(i,s) * qgt(i,s)
   4122           + sum(j,PROD_COMM, VFAD(i,j,s) * qft(i,j,s)));
   4123    
   4124    
   4125   !<
   4126       A-5. Trade Balance Indices
   4127       --------------------------
   4128   >!
   4129    
   4130   Variable (change)(all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4131       DTBALi(i,r) # change in trade balance by i and by r, $ US million #;
   4132   !<
   4133       A positive value indicates that the change in exports exceeds the change
   4134       in imports.
   4135   >!
   4136   Equation TRADEBAL_i
   4137   # computes change in trade balance by commodity and by region (HT 97) #
   4138   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4139       DTBALi(i,r)
   4140           = [VXW(i,r) / 100] * vxwfob(i,r) - [VIW(i,r) / 100] * viwcif(i,r);
   4141    
   4142   Variable (change)(all,r,REG)
   4143       DTBAL(r) # change in trade balance X - M, $ US million #;
   4144   Equation TRADEBALANCE
   4145   # computes change in trade balance (X - M), by region (HT 98) #
   4146   (all,r,REG)
   4147       DTBAL(r)
   4148           = [VXWREGION(r) / 100] * vxwreg(r) - [VIWREGION(r) / 100] * viwreg(r);
   4149    
   4150   !<
   4151       The balance on current account is equal to the sum of the ordinary trade
   4152       balance and net emissions trading revenue.
   4153   >!
   4154   Variable (change) (all,r,REG)
   4155       DTBALCTRA(r) # balance on current account #;
   4156   Equation TRAEMTRADBAL # balance on current account #
   4157   (all,r,REG)
   4158       DTBALCTRA(r) = DTBAL(r) + DVCO2TRA(r);
   4159    
   4160   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   4161       TBALCTRA(r) # balance on current account #;
   4162   Formula (all,r,REG)
   4163       TBALCTRA(r) = VXWREGION(r) - VIWREGION(r)
   4164           + [CO2Q(r) - CO2T(r)] * NCTAXLEV(r);
   4165    
   4166   Variable (change)(all,r,REG)
   4167       DBALCAR(r)
   4168       # change in ratio of current account balance to regional income #;
   4169   Equation DBALCARATIO
   4170   # change in ratio of trade balance to regional income #
   4171   (all,r,REG)
   4172       100 * INCOME(r) * DBALCAR(r) = 100 * DTBALCTRA(r) - TBALCTRA(r) * y(r);
   4173    
   4174   !<
   4175       In order to maintain homogeneity in the presence of a fixed trade balance,
   4176       it is useful to have a nominal variable which this is measured against.
   4177       The next equation provides this, and we recommend users fix DTBALR instead
   4178       of fixing DTBAL in future simulations.  The strategy is the same one used
   4179       above for taxes.
   4180   >!
   4181    
   4182   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   4183       TBAL(r) # trade balance for region r #;
   4184   Formula (all,r,REG)
   4185       TBAL(r) = VXWREGION(r) - VIWREGION(r);
   4186    
   4187   Variable (change)(all,r,REG)
   4188       DTBALR(r) # change in ratio of trade balance to regional income #;
   4189   Equation DTBALRATIO
   4190   # change in ratio of trade balance to regional income #
   4191   (all,r,REG)
   4192       100 * INCOME(r) * DTBALR(r) = 100 * DTBAL(r) - TBAL(r) * y(r);
   4193    
   4194    
   4195   !<
   4196       A-6. Real Energy Price Index
   4197       ----------------------------
   4198    
   4199       The real energy price index is a Divisia index of user prices of energy,
   4200       deflated by the GDP deflator.
   4201   >!
   4202    
   4203   Coefficient (all,i,EGY_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4204       TOTDEM(i,r) # energy usage at agents' prices #;
   4205   Formula (all,i,EGY_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4206       TOTDEM(i,r) = sum{j,PROD_COMM, VDFA(i,j,r)}
   4207           + sum{j,PROD_COMM, VIFA(i,j,r)} + VDPA(i,r) + VIPA(i,r) + VDGA(i,r)
   4208           + VIGA(i,r);
   4209    
   4210   Variable (all,i,EGY_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4211       vdem(i,r) # money value of energy usage at agents' prices #;
   4212   Equation TOTVALEN
   4213   # money value of energy usage at agents' prices #
   4214   (all,i,EGY_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4215       TOTDEM(i,r) * vdem(i,r) =
   4216           sum{j,PROD_COMM, VDFA(i,j,r)*[pfd(i,j,r) + qfd(i,j,r)]}
   4217           + sum{j,PROD_COMM, VIFA(i,j,r)*[pfm(i,j,r) + qfm(i,j,r)]}
   4218           + VDPA(i,r)*[ppd(i,r) + qpd(i,r)] + VIPA(i,r)*[ppm(i,r) + qpm(i,r)]
   4219           + VDGA(i,r)*[pgd(i,r) + qgd(i,r)] + VIGA(i,r)*[pgm(i,r) + qgm(i,r)];
   4220    
   4221   Variable (all,i,EGY_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4222       qdem(i,r) # agents'-prices-weighted energy usage quantity index #;
   4223   Equation TOTQUAEN
   4224   # agents'-prices-weighted energy usage quantity index #
   4225   (all,i,EGY_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4226       TOTDEM(i,r) * qdem(i,r) =
   4227           sum{j,PROD_COMM, VDFA(i,j,r)*qfd(i,j,r)}
   4228           + sum{j,PROD_COMM, VIFA(i,j,r)*qfm(i,j,r)}
   4229           + VDPA(i,r)*qpd(i,r) + VIPA(i,r)*qpm(i,r)
   4230           + VDGA(i,r)*qgd(i,r) + VIGA(i,r)*qgm(i,r);
   4231    
   4232   Variable (all,i,EGY_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4233       apen(i,r) # real energy price index #;
   4234   Equation AVPRICE
   4235   # real energy price index #
   4236   (all,i,EGY_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4237       apen(i,r) = vdem(i,r) - qdem(i,r) - pgdp(r);
   4238    
   4239    
   4240   !<
   4241       -----------------------
   4242       B. Equivalent Variation
   4243       -----------------------
   4244    
   4245       B-0. Appendix-Specific Variables and Coefficients
   4246       B-1. Government Consumption Shadow Demand System
   4247       B-2. Private Consumption Shadow Demand System
   4248       B-3. Regional Household Shadow Demand System
   4249       B-4. Equivalent Variation
   4250    
   4251       This appendix calculates equivalent variation "EV" and world equivalent
   4252       variation, "WEV", by determining the income "yev" that would be required
   4253       to achieve the current actual utility level "u" in a shadow demand system
   4254       in which prices are fixed.
   4255    
   4256       Section B-2 calculates the utility elasticity of private consumption
   4257       expenditure, "ueprivev", within a shadow demand system for private
   4258       consumption, for use in section B-3.  B-3 calculates private consumption
   4259       expenditure "ypev" for use in B-2, and regional income "yev" for use in
   4260       B-4, within a shadow demand system for the regional household.  B-4
   4261       calculates "EV" and "WEV".
   4262   >!
   4263    
   4264    
   4265   !<
   4266       B-0. Appendix-Specific Variables and Coefficients
   4267       -------------------------------------------------
   4268    
   4269       only used in this Equivalent Variation section of the Summary Indices
   4270       appendix
   4271   >!
   4272    
   4273   Variable (all,r,REG)
   4274       uelasev(r)
   4275       # elasticity of cost of utility wrt utility, for EV calc. #;
   4276   Variable (all,r,REG)
   4277       ueprivev(r)
   4278       # utility elasticity of private consn expenditure, for EV calc. #;
   4279   Variable (all,r,REG)
   4280       ugev(r) # per capita utility from gov't expend., for EV calc. #;
   4281   Variable (all,r,REG)
   4282       upev(r) # per capita utility from private expend., for EV calc. #;
   4283   Variable (all,r,REG)
   4284       qsaveev(r) # total quantity of savings demanded, for EV calc. #;
   4285   Variable (all,r,REG)
   4286       yev(r) # regional household income in region r, for EV calc. #;
   4287   Variable (all,r,REG)
   4288       ypev(r)
   4289       # private consumption expenditure in region r, for EV calc. #;
   4290   Variable (all,r,REG)
   4291       ygev(r)
   4292       # government consumption expenditure in region r, for EV calc. #;
   4293    
   4294   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   4295       INCOMEEV(r) # regional income, for EV calc. #;
   4296   Formula (initial) (all,r,REG)
   4297       INCOMEEV(r) = INCOME(r);
   4298   Update (all,r,REG)
   4299       INCOMEEV(r) = yev(r);
   4300    
   4301   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   4302       UTILPRIVEV(r) # utility from private consumption, for EV calcs #;
   4303   Formula (initial) (all,r,REG)
   4304       UTILPRIVEV(r) = UTILPRIV(r);
   4305   Update (all,r,REG)
   4306       UTILPRIVEV(r) = upev(r);
   4307    
   4308   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   4309       UTILGOVEV(r) # utility from private consumption, for EV calcs #;
   4310   Formula (initial) (all,r,REG)
   4311       UTILGOVEV(r) = UTILGOV(r);
   4312   Update (all,r,REG)
   4313       UTILGOVEV(r) = ugev(r);
   4314    
   4315   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   4316       UTILSAVEEV(r) # utility from private consumption, for EV calcs #;
   4317   Formula (initial) (all,r,REG)
   4318       UTILSAVEEV(r) = UTILSAVE(r);
   4319   Update (change) (all,r,REG)
   4320       UTILSAVEEV(r) = [[qsaveev(r) - pop(r)] / 100] * UTILSAVEEV(r);
   4321    
   4322    
   4323   !<
   4324       B-1. Government Consumption Shadow Demand System
   4325       ------------------------------------------------
   4326   >!
   4327    
   4328   Equation GOVUSHD
   4329   # utility from government consumption in r #
   4330   (all,r,REG)
   4331       ygev(r) - pop(r) = ugev(r);
   4332    
   4333    
   4334   !<
   4335       B-2. Private Consumption Shadow Demand System
   4336       ---------------------------------------------
   4337   >!
   4338    
   4339   Variable (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4340       qpev(i,r)
   4341       # private hhld demand for commodity i in region r, for EV calc. #;
   4342    
   4343   Coefficient (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4344       VPAEV(i,r)
   4345       # private hhld expend. on i in r valued at agent's prices, for EV calc. #;
   4346   Formula (initial) (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4347       VPAEV(i,r) = VPA(i,r);
   4348   Update (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4349       VPAEV(i,r) = qpev(i,r);
   4350    
   4351   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   4352       VPAREGEV(r) # private consumption expenditure in region r, for EV calc. #;
   4353   Formula (all,r,REG)
   4354       VPAREGEV(r) = sum(i,UP_COMM, VPAEV(i,r));
   4355   !<
   4356       VPAREGEV should agree with PRIVEXPEV.
   4357   >!
   4358    
   4359   Coefficient (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4360       CONSHREV(i,r)
   4361       # share of private hhld consn devoted to good i in r, for EV calc. #;
   4362   Formula (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4363       CONSHREV(i,r) = VPAEV(i,r) / VPAREGEV(r);
   4364   Coefficient (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4365       EYEV(i,r)
   4366       # expend. elast. of private hhld demand for i in r, for EV calc. #;
   4367   Formula (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4368       EYEV(i,r)
   4369           = [1.0 / sum(n,UP_COMM, CONSHREV(n,r) * INCPAR(n,r))]
   4370           * [INCPAR(i,r) * [1.0 - ALPHA(i,r)]
   4371               + sum(n,UP_COMM, CONSHREV(n,r) * INCPAR(n,r) * ALPHA(n,r))]
   4372           + ALPHA(i,r)
   4373           - sum(n,UP_COMM, CONSHREV(n,r) * ALPHA(n,r));
   4374    
   4375   Equation PRIVDMNDSEV
   4376       # private hhld demands for composite commodities, for EV calc. #
   4377       (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4378       qpev(i,r) - pop(r) = EYEV(i,r) * [ypev(r) - pop(r)];
   4379   !<
   4380       Prices are held constant for the EV calculation and so do not appear here.
   4381   >!
   4382    
   4383   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   4384       UELASPRIVEV(r)
   4385       # elast. of cost wrt utility from private consn, for EV calc. #;
   4386   Formula (all,r,REG)
   4387       UELASPRIVEV(r) = sum(i,UP_COMM, CONSHREV(i,r) * INCPAR(i,r));
   4388    
   4389   Equation PRIVATEUEV
   4390   # computation of utility from private consumption in r (HT 45) #
   4391   (all,r,REG)
   4392       ypev(r) - pop(r) = UELASPRIVEV(r) * upev(r);
   4393    
   4394   Coefficient (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4395       XWCONSHREV(i,r)
   4396       # expansion-parameter-weighted consumption share, for EV calc. #;
   4397   Formula (all,i,UP_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4398       XWCONSHREV(i,r) = CONSHREV(i,r) * INCPAR(i,r) / UELASPRIVEV(r);
   4399    
   4400   Equation UTILELASPRIVEV
   4401       # elasticity of cost wrt utility from private consn, for EV calc. #
   4402       (all,r,REG)
   4403       ueprivev(r)
   4404           = sum(i,UP_COMM, XWCONSHREV(i,r) * [qpev(i,r) - ypev(r)]);
   4405   !<
   4406       Prices are held constant for the EV calculation and so do not appear here.
   4407   >!
   4408    
   4409    
   4410   !<
   4411    
   4412       B-3. Regional Household Shadow Demand System
   4413       --------------------------------------------
   4414   >!
   4415    
   4416   Variable (all,r,REG)
   4417       ysaveev(r) # NET savings expenditure, for EV calc. #;
   4418    
   4419   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   4420       PRIVEXPEV(r)
   4421       # private consumption expenditure in region r, for EV calc. #;
   4422   Formula (initial) (all,r,REG)
   4423       PRIVEXPEV(r) = PRIVEXP(r);
   4424   Update (all,r,REG)
   4425       PRIVEXPEV(r) = ypev(r);
   4426   !<
   4427       PRIVEXPEV should agree with VPAREGEV.
   4428   >!
   4429    
   4430   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   4431       GOVEXPEV(r)
   4432       # government consumption expenditure in region r, for EV calc. #;
   4433   Formula (initial) (all,r,REG)
   4434       GOVEXPEV(r) = GOVEXP(r);
   4435   Update (all,r,REG)
   4436       GOVEXPEV(r) = ygev(r);
   4437    
   4438   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   4439       SAVEEV(r)
   4440       # saving in region r, for EV calc. #;
   4441   Formula (initial) (all,r,REG)
   4442       SAVEEV(r) = SAVE(r);
   4443   Update (all,r,REG)
   4444       SAVEEV(r) = ysaveev(r);
   4445    
   4446   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   4447       XSHRPRIVEV(r)
   4448       # private expenditure share in regional income, for EV calc. #;
   4449   Formula (all,r,REG)
   4450       XSHRPRIVEV(r) = PRIVEXPEV(r) / INCOMEEV(r);
   4451    
   4452   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   4453       XSHRGOVEV(r)
   4454       # government expenditure share in regional income, for EV calc. #;
   4455   Formula (all,r,REG)
   4456       XSHRGOVEV(r) = GOVEXPEV(r) / INCOMEEV(r);
   4457    
   4458   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   4459       XSHRSAVEEV(r) # saving share in regional income, for EV calc. #;
   4460   Formula (all,r,REG)
   4461       XSHRSAVEEV(r) = SAVEEV(r) / INCOMEEV(r);
   4462    
   4463   Variable (all,r,REG)
   4464       dpavev(r) # average distribution parameter shift, for EV calc. #;
   4465   Equation DPARAVEV
   4466   # average distribution parameter shift, for EV calc. #
   4467       (all,r,REG)
   4468       dpavev(r)
   4469           = XSHRPRIVEV(r) * dppriv(r)
   4470           + XSHRGOVEV(r) * dpgov(r)
   4471           + XSHRSAVEEV(r) * dpsave(r);
   4472    
   4473   Equation UTILITELASTICEV
   4474       # elasticity of cost of utility wrt utility, for EV calc. #
   4475       (all,r,REG)
   4476       uelasev(r) = XSHRPRIV(r) * ueprivev(r) - dpavev(r);
   4477    
   4478   Equation PCONSEXPEV
   4479   # private consumption expenditure, for EV calc. #
   4480       (all,r,REG)
   4481       ypev(r) - yev(r) = -[ueprivev(r) - uelasev(r)] + dppriv(r);
   4482    
   4483   Equation GOVCONSEXPEV
   4484   # government consumption expenditure #
   4485   (all,r,REG)
   4486       ygev(r) - yev(r) = uelasev(r) + dpgov(r);
   4487    
   4488   Equation SAVINGEV
   4489   # saving #
   4490   (all,r,REG)
   4491       ysaveev(r) - yev(r) = uelasev(r) + dpsave(r);
   4492    
   4493   Equation SAVEUEV
   4494   # saving #
   4495   (all,r,REG)
   4496       qsaveev(r) = ysaveev(r);
   4497    
   4498   !<
   4499       Note that because psave doesn't change, qsaveev moves with ysaveev.
   4500   >!
   4501    
   4502   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   4503       UTILELASEV(r)
   4504       # elasticity of cost of utility wrt utility, for EV calc. #;
   4505   Formula (initial) (all,r,REG)
   4506       UTILELASEV(r) = UTILELAS(r);
   4507   Update (all,r,REG)
   4508       UTILELASEV(r) = uelasev(r);
   4509    
   4510   Equation INCOME_EQUIV
   4511   # equivalent income #
   4512   (all,r,REG)
   4513       u(r)
   4514           = au(r)
   4515           + DPARPRIV(r) * loge(UTILPRIVEV(r)) * dppriv(r)
   4516           + DPARGOV(r) * loge(UTILGOVEV(r)) * dpgov(r)
   4517           + DPARSAVE(r) * loge(UTILSAVEEV(r)) * dpsave(r)
   4518           + [1.0 / UTILELASEV(r)] * [yev(r) - pop(r)];
   4519    
   4520    
   4521   !<
   4522       B-4. Equivalent Variation
   4523       -------------------------
   4524   >!
   4525    
   4526   Variable (change)(all,r,REG)
   4527       EV(r) # equivalent variation, $ US million #;
   4528   Equation EVREG
   4529   # regional EV (HT 67) #
   4530   (all,r,REG)
   4531       EV(r) = [INCOMEEV(r) / 100] * yev(r);
   4532    
   4533   Variable (change)
   4534       WEV # equivalent variation for the world #;
   4535   Equation EVWLD
   4536   # EV for the world (HT 68) #
   4537       WEV = sum(r,REG, EV(r));
   4538    
   4539    
   4540   !<
   4541       ------------------------
   4542       C. Welfare Decomposition
   4543       ------------------------
   4544       See GTAP Technical Paper No. 5 for derivation and interpretation.
   4545   >!
   4546    
   4547   Coefficient (all,r,REG)
   4548       EVSCALFACT(r) # equivalent variation scaling factor #;
   4549   Formula (all,r,REG)
   4550       EVSCALFACT(r) = [UTILELASEV(r) / UTILELAS(r)] * [INCOMEEV(r) / INCOME(r)];
   4551    
   4552   Coefficient (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   4553       VTMD(m,s) # aggregate value of svce m in shipments to s #;
   4554   Formula (all,m,MARG_COMM)(all,s,REG)
   4555       VTMD(m,s) = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(r,REG, VTMFSD(m,i,r,s)));
   4556    
   4557   Variable (linear,change)(all,r,REG)
   4558       EV_ALT(r) # regional EV computed in alternative way #;
   4559   Equation EV_DECOMPOSITION
   4560   # decomposition of Equivalent Variation #
   4561   (all,r,REG)
   4562       EV_ALT(r)
   4563           = -[0.01 * UTILELASEV(r) * INCOMEEV(r)]
   4564           * [DPARPRIV(r) * loge(UTILPRIVEV(r) / UTILPRIV(r)) * dppriv(r)
   4565               + DPARGOV(r) * loge(UTILGOVEV(r) / UTILGOV(r)) * dpgov(r)
   4566               + DPARSAVE(r) * loge(UTILSAVEEV(r) / UTILSAVE(r)) * dpsave(r)]
   4567           + [0.01 * EVSCALFACT(r)]
   4568           * [(100.0 * DVCO2TRA(r))
   4569               + sum(i,NSAV_COMM, PTAX(i,r) * [qo(i,r) - pop(r)])
   4570               + sum(i,ENDW_COMM, sum(j,PROD_COMM,
   4571                     ETAX(i,j,r) * [qfe(i,j,r) - pop(r)]))
   4572               + sum(j,PROD_COMM, sum(i,TRAD_COMM,
   4573                     [IFTAX(i,j,r) + IFCTAX(i,j,r)] * [qfm(i,j,r) - pop(r)]))
   4574               + sum(j,PROD_COMM, sum(i,TRAD_COMM,
   4575                     [DFTAX(i,j,r) + DFCTAX(i,j,r)] * [qfd(i,j,r) - pop(r)]))
   4576               + sum(i,TRAD_COMM,
   4577                   [IPTAX(i,r) + IPCTAX(i,r)] * [qpm(i,r) - pop(r)])
   4578               + sum(i,TRAD_COMM,
   4579                   [DPTAX(i,r) + DPCTAX(i,r)] * [qpd(i,r) - pop(r)])
   4580               + sum(i,TRAD_COMM,
   4581                   [IGTAX(i,r) + IGCTAX(i,r)] * [qgm(i,r) - pop(r)])
   4582               + sum(i,TRAD_COMM,
   4583                   [DGTAX(i,r) + DGCTAX(i,r)] * [qgd(i,r) - pop(r)])
   4584               + sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(s,REG, XTAXD(i,r,s) * [qxs(i,r,s) - pop(r)]))
   4585               + sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(s,REG, MTAX(i,s,r) * [qxs(i,s,r) - pop(r)]))
   4586               + sum(i,ENDW_COMM, VOA(i,r) * [qo(i,r) - pop(r)])
   4587               - VDEP(r) * [kb(r) - pop(r)]
   4588               + sum(i,PROD_COMM, VOA(i,r) * ao(i,r))
   4589               + sum(j,PROD_COMM, sum(i,FIRM_COMM, VFA(i,j,r) * af(i,j,r)))
   4590               + sum(m,MARG_COMM, sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(s,REG,
   4591                   VTMFSD(m,i,s,r) * atmfsd(m,i,s,r))))
   4592               + sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(s,REG, VIMS(i,s,r) * ams(i,s,r)))
   4593               + sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(s,REG, VXWD(i,r,s) * pfob(i,r,s)))
   4594               + sum(m,MARG_COMM, VST(m,r) * pm(m,r))
   4595               + NETINV(r) * pcgds(r)
   4596               - sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(s,REG, VXWD(i,s,r) * pfob(i,s,r)))
   4597               - sum(m,MARG_COMM, VTMD(m,r) * pt(m))
   4598               - SAVE(r) * psave(r)]
   4599           + 0.01 * INCOMEEV(r) * pop(r);
   4600    
   4601   Variable (linear,change)
   4602       WEV_ALT # expression for WEV computed in alternative way #;
   4603   Equation WORLDEV
   4604   # Equivalent Variation for the world #
   4605       WEV_ALT = sum(r,REG, EV_ALT(r));
   4606    
   4607   Variable (linear,change) (all,r,REG)
   4608       CNTco2trd(r) # contribution to regional EV of carbon trading #;
   4609   Equation CONT_EV_CO2TR
   4610   (all,r,REG)
   4611       CNTco2trd(r) = EVSCALFACT(r)
   4612           * (DVCO2TRA(r) - 0.01 * (CO2Q(r) - CO2T(r)) * NCTAXLEV(r) * pxwwld);
   4613    
   4614   Variable (linear,change) (all,r,REG)
   4615       CNTdpar(r) # contribution to EV of change in distribution parameters #;
   4616   Equation CNT_WEV_dpar
   4617   (all,r,REG)
   4618       CNTdpar(r)
   4619           = -0.01 * UTILELASEV(r) * INCOMEEV(r)
   4620           * [DPARPRIV(r) * loge(UTILPRIVEV(r) / UTILPRIV(r)) * dppriv(r)
   4621               + DPARGOV(r) * loge(UTILGOVEV(r) / UTILGOV(r)) * dpgov(r)
   4622               + DPARSAVE(r) * loge(UTILSAVEEV(r) / UTILSAVE(r)) * dpsave(r)];
   4623    
   4624   Variable (linear,change) (all,r,REG)
   4625       CNTpopr(r) # contribution to EV in region r of change in population #;
   4626   Equation CONT_EV_pop
   4627   (all,r,REG)
   4628       CNTpopr(r) = 0.01 * INCOMEEV(r) * pop(r);
   4629    
   4630   Variable (linear,change) (all,r,REG)
   4631       CNTqor(r) # contribution to EV in region r of output changes #;
   4632   Equation CONT_EV_qor
   4633   (all,r,REG)
   4634       CNTqor(r)
   4635           = sum(i,NSAV_COMM,
   4636               0.01 * EVSCALFACT(r) * PTAX(i,r) * [qo(i,r) - pop(r)]);
   4637    
   4638   Variable (linear,change) (all,i,NSAV_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4639       CNTqoir(i,r)
   4640       # contribution to EV of changes in output of NSAV_COMM i in reg. r #;
   4641   Equation CONT_EV_qoir
   4642   (all,i,NSAV_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4643       CNTqoir(i,r) = PTAX(i,r) * [0.01 * EVSCALFACT(r)] * [qo(i,r) - pop(r)];
   4644    
   4645   Variable (linear,change) (all,r,REG)
   4646       CNTqfer(r)
   4647       # cont. to EV of changes in use of all ENDW_COMM in all ind. in reg. r #;
   4648   Equation CONT_EV_qfer
   4649   (all,r,REG)
   4650       CNTqfer(r)
   4651           = sum(i,ENDW_COMM, sum(j,PROD_COMM,
   4652               ETAX(i,j,r) * [0.01 * EVSCALFACT(r)] * [qfe(i,j,r) - pop(r)]));
   4653    
   4654   Variable (linear,change) (all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4655       CNTqfeir(i,r)
   4656       # contribution to EV of changes in use of ENDW_COMM i in all ind. in r #;
   4657   Equation CONT_EV_qfeir
   4658   (all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4659       CNTqfeir(i,r)
   4660           = sum(j,PROD_COMM,
   4661               ETAX(i,j,r) * [0.01 * EVSCALFACT(r)] * [qfe(i,j,r) - pop(r)]);
   4662    
   4663   Variable (linear,change) (all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4664       CNTqfeijr(i,j,r)
   4665       # cont. to EV of changes in use of ENDW_COMM i in ind. j of reg. r #;
   4666   Equation CONT_EV_qfeijr
   4667   (all,i,ENDW_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4668       CNTqfeijr(i,j,r)
   4669           = ETAX(i,j,r) * [0.01 * EVSCALFACT(r)] * [qfe(i,j,r) - pop(r)];
   4670    
   4671   Variable (linear,change) (all,r,REG)
   4672       CNTqfmr(r)
   4673       # cont. to EV of changes in use of imported int. in all ind. in reg. r #;
   4674   Equation CONT_EV_qfmr
   4675   (all,r,REG)
   4676       CNTqfmr(r)
   4677           = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(j,PROD_COMM,
   4678               [IFTAX(i,j,r) + IFCTAX(i,j,r)] * [0.01 * EVSCALFACT(r)]
   4679                   * [qfm(i,j,r) - pop(r)]));
   4680    
   4681   Variable (linear,change) (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4682       CNTqfmir(i,r)
   4683       # cont. to EV of changes in use of imported int. i in all ind. in r #;
   4684   Equation CONT_EV_qfmir
   4685   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4686       CNTqfmir(i,r)
   4687           = sum(j,PROD_COMM,
   4688               [IFTAX(i,j,r) + IFCTAX(i,j,r)] * [0.01 * EVSCALFACT(r)]
   4689                   * [qfm(i,j,r) - pop(r)]);
   4690    
   4691   Variable (linear,change) (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4692       CNTqfmijr(i,j,r)
   4693       # cont. to EV of changes in use of imported int. i in ind. j of reg. r #;
   4694   Equation CONT_EV_qfmijr
   4695   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4696       CNTqfmijr(i,j,r)
   4697           = [IFTAX(i,j,r) + IFCTAX(i,j,r)] * [0.01 * EVSCALFACT(r)]
   4698               * [qfm(i,j,r) - pop(r)];
   4699    
   4700   Variable (linear,change) (all,r,REG)
   4701       CNTqfdr(r)
   4702       # cont. to EV of changes in use of domestic int. in all ind. in reg. r #;
   4703   Equation CONT_EV_qfdr
   4704   (all,r,REG)
   4705       CNTqfdr(r)
   4706           = sum(i,TRAD_COMM, sum(j,PROD_COMM,
   4707               [DFTAX(i,j,r) + DFCTAX(i,j,r)] * [0.01 * EVSCALFACT(r)]
   4708                   * [qfd(i,j,r) - pop(r)]));
   4709    
   4710   Variable (linear,change) (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4711       CNTqfdir(i,r)
   4712       # contribution to EV of changes in use of domestic i in all ind. in r #;
   4713   Equation CONT_EV_qfdir
   4714   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4715       CNTqfdir(i,r)
   4716           = sum(j,PROD_COMM,
   4717               [DFTAX(i,j,r) + DFCTAX(i,j,r)] * [0.01 * EVSCALFACT(r)]
   4718                   * [qfd(i,j,r) - pop(r)]);
   4719    
   4720   Variable (linear,change) (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4721       CNTqfdijr(i,j,r)
   4722       # cont. to EV of changes in use of domestic int. i in ind. j of reg. r #;
   4723   Equation CONT_EV_qfdijr
   4724   (all,i,TRAD_COMM)(all,j,PROD_COMM)(all,r,REG)
   4725       CNTqfdijr(i,j,r)
   4726           = [DFTAX(i,j,r) + DFCTAX(i,j,r)] * [0.01 * EVSCALFACT(r)]
   4727               * [qfd(i,j,r) - pop(r)];
   4728    
   4729   Variable (linear,change) (all,r,REG)
   4730       CNTqpmr(r)
